title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook baby limas as directed on package.
Drain, saving liquid to add as part of the 1/2 cup water.
In a saucepan, combine the onion, red and green pepper and water.
Heat through until vegetables are tenderized.
Blend sour cream and curry powder into the onion and pepper mixture.
Add baby lima beans next.
Place this mixture into a small casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs with 1 tablespoon melted butter and mix well.
Fold in crumbled bacon and sprinkle this mixture on top of lima bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes until topping is golden brown.

title: rose punch
directions: In a large bowl, combine wine, grenadine and lemon juice. Stir in ginger ale.
Spoon 1 pint raspberry sherbet into punch. Makes 22 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: homemade sausage with sage
directions: Mix pork thoroughly with remaining ingredients; shape into 12 to 15 patties. Fry in skillet for 8 minutes on each side until browned.
Yields 8 to 12 servings.

title: granola
directions: Pour maple syrup over other ingredients; mix very well. Spread onto cookie sheets and bake, stirring several times, until golden brown.
Add raisins and chopped, unsulfured, dried apricots once cooled.

title: chili con queso
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Add chopped vegetables. Serve from chafing dish or heated tray (needs to be served warm). Serve with taco chips.

title: ratatouille
directions: In a skillet, place a very small amount of oil or spray with nonstick spray.
Saute garlic, bell pepper and onion until tender. Add zucchini and yellow squash.
Add tomatoes and sauce and cook 5 minutes on medium-low heat.
Add Minute rice and cover.
Simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: banana pineapple nut cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center and add eggs, pineapple, nuts, bananas, oil and vanilla. Stir, but do not beat.
Only takes a few stirs to mix well.
Bake in
a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until well done.
Let cool 10 minutes before turning out of pan.

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Blend softened cream cheese, sugar, eggs, vanilla and lemon rind.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a spring-form pan.

title: pineapple upside-down cake(you will flip for this cake.)
directions: In a large bowl, combine shortening and salt, then gradually add sugar.
Cream well.
Add egg and beat.
Sift flour and baking powder together, and then add to mixture.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients until soft dough forms.
Drop by spoonful into boiling stew.
Cook uncovered over low heat 10 minutes.
Cover and cook 10 minutes more.
Makes 10 to 12 dumplings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine 1/4 cup brown sugar, 2 teaspoons orange juice and 2 teaspoons butter; mix and set aside to use for glaze topping.
Whip potatoes until smooth; beat in eggs.
Add remaining sugar, orange juice and butter.
Add salt, cloves and cinnamon; mix well and pour into a 1 1/2 quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle pecans on top.
Pour glaze topping over pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Top with orange slices and marshmallows.
Place under broiler until marshmallows are delicately browned.
Yields 6 servings.

title: cherry yum-yum
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix graham cracker crumbs and margarine together. Spread half of the mixture in a long square container. Mix cream cheese and blend with sugar, cold milk and both packages of Dream Whip.
Blend to stiff.
Put half of the mixture on top of crumbs.
Put both cans of pie filling on next.
Put remaining cream mixture on next, then remaining crumbs.
Chill for 24 hours.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms and soups.
Cook egg noodles until tender.
Just before serving, add sour cream to soup and meat mixture.
Heat thoroughly, but do not boil.
Serve over noodles.
This recipe will serve 4 people.

title: apple crunch
directions: Place sliced apples in a large baking dish. Combine flour, cinnamon, oats and sugar; cut butter into mix. Sprinkle mixture over apples and press down slightly. Drizzle milk slowly over topping. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: daughtry's banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased 9 x 5 loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Test with toothpick.
Let set for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: excellent breakfast casserole
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch greased pan with 8 slices of bread.
Top with ham, cheese, onion, green pepper and lastly the remaining 8 pieces of bread.
Whip together the eggs, salt, pepper, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and milk.
Pour over sandwiches.
Let stand overnight in the fridge before baking.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Top with potato chips and dribble melted butter over all.

title: pudding quick style
directions: Sift flour and sugar together until lumps are out into a large bowl.
Pour milk in and stir good on high for 4 minutes.
Take out and stir with whisk or fork.
Add eggs (beaten) into milk mixture. Stir again and good for 3 more minutes.
Stir briskly and cook for 1 more minute.
Take out and stir in vanilla and butter.
You can add coconut and make a Coconut Creme Pie or add bananas to make a Banana Pudding.
Just add vanilla wafers and, ooh, it is so good!

title: rice and artichoke salad
directions: Cook chicken Rice-A-Roni as directed on package and cool. Chop and drain artichoke hearts; reserve oil.
Mix chopped ingredients with cooled rice.
Mix mayonnaise, curry powder and oil from artichoke hearts; test amount of oil as you add so that dressing is not too thin.
Mix mayonnaise mixture with rest of ingredients and chill.

title: lemon crackers
directions: Cream sugar and shortening until fluffy.
Add flavoring and eggs and continue to beat.
Dissolve ammonia in milk.
Sift salt and flour together and add alternately with milk.
Add only enough flour to make a medium soft dough.
Chill in refrigerator for a few hours or overnight.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place one inch apart on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 375° until golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: round steak italiano(crockery cooking)
directions: Coat steak with salt, oregano and pepper.
Put in crock-pot, pour spaghetti sauce over, cover and cook 7 to 9 hours.
Turn control on high.
Add small onions; cover.
Cook on high until all is hot (10 minutes).
Serve with Italian green beans, (fava) toasted garlic bread with cheese or serve over noodles or spaghetti.
Serves 4.

title: marie's seafoam salad]
directions: Note:
All ingredients may be doubled for larger table setting.

title: lo-cal seafood salad
directions: Blend ingredients together and let sit in refrigerator for 2 to 3 hours for flavors to blend.
If you prefer taste over calorie count, Good Seasons Italian salad dressing from package is better.

title: ruffles and dogs
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain.
In large saucepan, combine tomato sauce, hot dogs, sugar, mustard, chili powder and Worcestershire sauce; simmer, covered, 15 minutes.
Add noodles and cheese; heat thoroughly.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: craig claiborne's chicken cordon bleu
directions: Have the cheese and ham ready for the filling.
Place the chicken breasts between sheets of plastic wrap and pound lightly with a flat mallet to make them larger.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Spoon 1 tablespoon of shredded cheese in the center of each chicken breast.
Cover with 1 rectangle of ham.
Spoon another tablespoon of cheese on top of each piece of ham.
Fold the edges of the chicken breasts over to enclose the filling.
Place the stuffed chicken breasts briefly in the freezer before breading them.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, oil, sugar and flour together first.
Add other ingredients to that mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 325° in 2 loaf pans.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute onions, celery, garlic and mushrooms in margarine until soft.
Add flour and stir until well blended.
Add chicken stock slowly and stir until thickened.
Add cheese, soup, tomatoes and peas; stir until cheese melts.
Add chicken and spaghetti and mix well with other ingredients.
Place in greased casserole and refrigerate overnight.
Put into cold oven and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut up chicken and add remaining ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick of butter and crush 1 stack of saltines. Mix and sprinkle on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° until bubbly. This is excellent served with noodles.

title: easy no bake cheese cake
directions: Mix the cream cheese, Cool Whip and sugar together.
Pour into pie shell; refrigerate overnight.
Top with the fruit pie filling.

title: russian dressing
directions: Combine in a jar and shake well.

title: divinity candy
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in double boiler and bring quickly to a boil.
Reduce heat and cook until a small amount dropped in cold water forms a clear, hard crystal ball.

title: marcilla's elegant cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: ranch snack mix
directions: In large bowls combine the pretzels, Bugles, cashews and crackers. Sprinkle with dressing mix; toss gently to combine. Drizzle with oil; toss until well coated. Store in airtight container.

title: sausage balls
directions: Blend all together good.
Roll out into small balls and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes or until balls are puffed and golden brown.
You may want to place the mixture in a plastic food bag and roll out as needed.
Yields approximately 100.

title: california chicken salad
directions: Mix cream with mayonnaise.
Do not peel apple, cut in half and remove core.
Place peel side next to cutter when chopping apple. Sprinkle lemon juice over chicken and apple, mixing lightly. Combine remaining ingredients, using only enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Add chicken, apple and toss slightly together.
Serve cold with mayonnaise.
Serves 4.

title: seafood dip
directions: Mix well and chill.

title: creamy hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in an airtight container.
Use
cup
of mixture to a mug.
Fill cup with boiling water.
Top with marshmallows, if desired.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Add water and salt to roast.
Place over low heat and slowly heat to boiling. Cover and simmer 2-3 hours.
Skim off excess fat. Add vegetables and cook another 30 minutes or until veggies are tender.
Yield 2 quarts.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix vegetables in large bowl.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Remove fat from chicken broth (approximately 3 quarts) used to cook chicken and add celery, onion, bell pepper, garlic, pimento, tomato sauce, Ro-Tel and mushrooms.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Add chicken.
Adjust amount of broth if required to cook a large package of long spaghetti.
Just before spaghetti is done, add 1 can of cream of mushroom soup (mix with small amount of broth before adding to mixture).

title: boy scout hash
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Combine meat, soup, onion, tomato sauce and pepper and simmer 35 minutes in a large skillet.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on rolls.

title: classic rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Cool slightly. Blend all ingredients thoroughly.
Chill.

title: barbecue roasts
directions: Combine all ingredients in roaster.
Cook at 325° for approximately 6 hours.
Remove bones and fat.
Shred meat and return to mixture.
Serve on hamburger buns.

title: super iced chocolate cappuccino
directions: In blender container, place syrup and coffee. Blend on high speed. Add ice cream. Cover and blend until smooth. Serve immediately over ice. Top with whipped cream and ground cinnamon, if desired. Yields about 6 (6 ounce) servings.

title: bishop cake
directions: Make bread mix as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour. Makes 1 loaf.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Add these to dry ingredients.
Pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes, then turn out onto cooling racks.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and egg.
Add buttermilk alternately with combined flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix until smooth.
Add vanilla.
Toss rhubarb with flour.
Add to mixture.
Spread in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hash brown skillet breakfast
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; drain and reserve drippings.
Heat drippings and add hash browns.
Cook over medium heat until browned.
Mix together eggs and milk and pour over potatoes.
Top with cheese and crumble bacon and sprinkle on top.
Cover and cook over low-medium heat for 10 to 15 minutes until done.
Cut in wedges.
Makes 6 servings.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix together as for pie crust.
Grease an 8-inch square or rectangle shallow pan.
Fill bottom of pan with sliced apples (the more apples the better).
Put topping over the apples as evenly as possible.
Bake at 325° until the apples are done (approximately 25 minutes).
May be served plain or with ice cream or milk.

title: lemon dream pie
directions: Prepare whipped topping mix as directed on package.
Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Add ice cubes; stir constantly until gelatin is thickened, about 2 to 3 minutes. Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whip, blend in whipped topping; whip until smooth.
Chill, if necessary, until mixture will mound.
Spoon into pie shell.
Chill 2 hours.
Garnish with lemon slices, if desired.

title: jalapeno squash casserole
directions: Cook squash
in water until tender; reserve liquid.
Prepare cornbread mix per package directions.
Crumble half of the cornbread into a 2-quart casserole.
Mix egg, liquid, squash, pimento and peppers.
Add to crumbled cornbread.
Mix well.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Melt chocolate; add milk and margarine.
In a large bowl, mix together peanuts and marshmallows; fold in chocolate mixture.

title: italian style catfish
directions: Heat 2 teaspoons of oil in medium saucepan; stir in onion and garlic.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Stir in tomato juice, wine, Italian seasoning and crushed red peppers.
Simmer until reduced to a thick sauce, about 7 to 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add diced tomatoes and parsley.
Rinse catfish.
Pat dry with paper towels.
Season with salt and pepper.
Coat with cornmeal.

title: apple dip
directions: Cream mixture together and dip apples.

title: corned beef soup
directions: In a large pot, put tomatoes.
Pour in about 5 cans of water. Add onion, potatoes and corned beef.
When potatoes are almost done, add noodles.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Ready in about 30 minutes.
Great with cornbread!

title: sliced sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes.
Cool.
In pie shell put 2 tablespoons of sugar and 3 tablespoons of flour.
Slice potatoes and layer on top of sugar and flour (one layer).
Sprinkle remaining sugar over potatoes.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle cinnamon.
Mix water and milk.
Pour over potatoes.
Don't overfill. Bake at 350° until pie bubbles and browns.

title: sweet potato dressing
directions: Chop seasonings.
Cook pork thoroughly.
Drop in chopped livers and oysters.
Simmer a little while.
Add seasoning and simmer until tender.
Mash in potatoes.
Cook about 10 minutes longer on low fire.

title: angel wings
directions: Add salt to egg yolks, then beat egg yolks and eggs until thick and lemon colored. Add sugar, butter and rum.
Beat until well mixed. Fold in flour and knead until the dough blisters. Transfer to a well floured board.
Cut in half.
Roll each half until it is very thin.
Cut into 4-inch long by 2-inch wide strips.
Slit each strip in the center and pull one end through the slit.
Drop into hot oil and fry until lightly browned. Drain on paper towel. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: mardi gras kings bread ring
directions: Soften yeast cake in water.
Pour hot milk over sugar, shortening (melted) and cool to lukewarm.
Beat in 1 cup of the flour to make a stiff dough.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups candied fruits, reserving remainder to decorate cake ring.

title: peanut butter crisps
directions: Freeze bread; trim and cut strips like fingers.
Put in stove and crisp.
Do not brown.
Mix together Wesson oil and peanut butter.
Warm on low heat.
Crush graham crackers.
Roll bread in mixture and then roll in cracker crumbs.
Crisp or warm on rack 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chocolate dessertfort collins, colorado
directions: Mix flour and oleo well; add nuts.
Press into 9 X 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Chill.

title: watermelon delight
directions: Remove seeds from watermelon and cantaloupe and scoop out pulp with melon scoop.
Add the grapes and peaches and mix.
Cut jagged edge around rim of watermelon half and place fruit mixture in watermelon.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: thick white sauce
directions: Melt butter or margarine. Remove from heat. Add flour; stir until smooth. Add salt, then hot milk gradually, stirring constantly. Cook and stir until smooth and thick, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chocolate mousse cake
directions: Combine Kahlua, water and gelatin in saucepan; cook over low heat for 3 minutes, or until gelatin dissolves.
Add chocolate chips; stir over low heat until blended.
Add room temperature egg yolks; set aside.

title: death by chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Coarsely chop 8 squares of chocolate; set aside.
Microwave remaining 8 squares of chocolate in large bowl on high for 1-2 minutes.
Stir until melted and smooth.
Stir in sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder; (I mix these two together in a separate bowl and then add to the mixture).
Stir in remaining reserved chopped chocolate and nuts.
Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake about 12 minutes or until cookies are puffed and feel set to the touch.
Cool on cookie sheet one minute.
Transfer to wire rack to cool completely.
Yield:
approximately 1 1/2 doz.

title: bubbles
directions: Stir all ingredients in a large plastic container.

title: potato soup
directions: In large kettle, cook potatoes, carrots and celery in water until tender; drain, reserving liquid.
In same kettle, saute onion in oleo until soft.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add milk, stirring until thickened.
Stir in cooked vegetables.
Add 1 cup or more of reserved liquid until soup is desired consistency.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: old-fashioned chocolate frosting
directions: Over low heat, melt margarine.
Add cocoa, milk, Karo and sugar.
Mix well.
Let come to rolling boil and boil for 2 minutes. Remove from heat and let cool.
Add vanilla.
Beat until right consistency to spread.

title: strawberry angel food dessert
directions: Break up cake.
Put into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Dissolve jello in 2 1/2 cups boiling water.
Add salt, sugar and frozen strawberries.
Stir until cool.
Fold in prepared whipped cream. Pour mixture over cake.
Cool in refrigerator.
Enjoy.

title: fresh peach pound cake
directions: In bowl, mix all ingredients together in order listed.
Pour into greased and floured 10 inch pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350 degrees.
Let cool completely.
Spoon peach cream cheese frosting on top and drizzle on sides.

title: cheese wild rice spinach
directions: In a large bowl, mix first 4 ingredients.
Bring water to a boil.
Add spinach, onion and margarine.
Continue boiling about 5 minutes.
Pour this over rice mixture.
Stir and cover tightly. Bake 30 minutes at 375°, then remove from oven and stir in cubed cheese.
Bake, uncovered, for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add egg and vanilla. Add dry ingredients gradually. Roll out 1/8-inch thick.
Cut out. Bake at 350° for 11 minutes. Melt chocolate chips and vegetable shortening. Dip cookies & let cool on wax paper.

title: baked pork chops and stuffing
directions: Brown chops over medium heat, turning once.
Place in single layer in shallow dish.
Mix together the bread cubes and poultry seasoning.
Top each chop with mixture.
Combine soup and 1/2 cup water in frying pan used for browning chops.
Pour over stuffing and chops.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 hour until chops are tender.

title: cabbage hot tamales
directions: Mix hamburger meat, pork sausage, chili powder, rice, salt, tomatoes and garlic.
Set aside.
Wash cabbage.
Pour hot water over cabbage until it will separate the leaves.
Put a small amount of meat mixture in each leaf.
Roll up, placing in a large pot.
When completed, pour tomato juice over them.
Cook until rice and meat are done, about 1 hour.

title: nuts and bolts
directions: Mix the cereals, pretzels and salted nuts in a large covered roaster.
Melt the fats together and add Worcestershire sauce. Mix lightly through cereal mixture.
Add Accent and garlic salt and toss mixture.
Put cover on roaster; place in a 225° oven for 2 hours.
Mix every 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix spices and salt with sugar; add to sweet potatoes.
Stir until well mixed; add milk slowly to eggs.
Combine the two mixtures and pour into unbaked pie shells.
Place in hot oven for 5 minutes, reduce heat and bake until custard is set.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: easy ice cream
directions: Mix well and put into your hand crank or electric freezer. Freeze.

title: quick round dish pumpkin pie
directions: Mix in blender all ingredients except cinnamon.
Pour in pie pan.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave oven about 15 to 20 seconds, depending on heating variations of your microwave. Stir together Cool Whip and cream cheese, then add your powdered sugar. Mix this together until smooth. Set this aside until crust is made.

title: applesauce meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Form into balls, roll in flour, then brown in oil.
Place in a covered casserole.
Mix catsup and water and pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Makes 20 to 25 meatballs.

title: orange cappuccino mix
directions: In a small bowl, combine sugar with orange extract.
Stir and blend with a fork until no trace of extract moisture remains.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir.
Sift to blend thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 cup mix.

title: easy pie crust
directions: Re-sift the flours and salt together.
Beat with a fork the oil and ice water until emulsified.
Pour over flour all at once, tossing lightly to mix.
Form quickly into a ball, handling as little as possible.
Divide in half and roll out each half between sheets of waxed paper or heavy plastic.
Remove top paper and fit loosely into pie pan.
For single baked crust, prick bottom and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 2 crusts.
Very good.

title: onion salad
directions: Dissolve jello; set aside.
Combine rest of ingredients and add jello.
Pour into 9 x 9 dish and let set.

title: frozen strawberry delight
directions: Puree strawberries in electric blender.
Combine condensed milk and whipped topping; stir until well blended.
Stir in strawberries, pineapple and lemon juice.
Spoon mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Freeze until firm.
Let stand at room temperature 15 minutes before serving.

title: kathy lou's brown sugar pound cake(yields 1 cake)
directions: Put butter and eggs out night before making cake.
Cream butter, shortening and sugars.
Cream and cream and cream, until very fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Mix flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into well-greased tube pan.
Bake in oven preheated to 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Heat water and milk to lukewarm.
Mix together the salt and sugar; add milk and water.
Add shortening.
Add flour (enough to make a stiff dough).
Let rise in warm place until double in size. Punch down and knead.
Shape into rolls or loaves.
Put to rise again until double.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: down home crab cakes
directions: Combine mayonnaise and egg in a large bowl; mix in the next 5 ingredients.
Stir in crabmeat and 1 to 1 1/4 cups breadcrumbs or enough to hold mixture together.
Shape into 8 patties.
Coat patties with remaining breadcrumbs.
Heat butter and oil in a large heavy skillet; add crab cakes in batches and fry until lightly browned on both sides.
Serve with tartar sauce.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Combine the graham cracker crumbs, honey and oil.
Mix well and press into a 9-inch pie pan.
In a mixing bowl, beat together the eggs and egg white until foamy.
Add all other ingredients. Beat until smooth and creamy.
Pour into the crust and bake at 350° until slightly browned and firm in the center, about 45 minutes.
Yields 10 servings.

title: roasted chicken breast
directions: Combine marinade ingredients and pour over chicken breasts. Marinate for 4 hours. Drain and bake chicken for 30 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: oven barbecued beef brisket
directions: Sprinkle both sides of the brisket with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cook, covered, with no water at 325°, allowing 1 hour per pound. Before last hour of cooking, remove brisket and slice. Return to pan and add barbecue sauce mixed with water. Almost cover meat with sauce. Cook 1 hour longer, covered. Serves 8 to 10.

title: jean's cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water; add orange juice and juice from pineapple with enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Let stand in refrigerator until it begins to congeal.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and nuts.
Mix and pour in mold and let congeal.
Delicious.

title: rice-a-roni salad
directions: Cook Rice-A-Roni according to package directions; cool.
Mix remaining ingredients with the rice and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: reese's peanut butter cup
directions: Cream butter, peanut butter and both sugars.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Cream into first mixture. Form into 1-inch balls (walnut size).
Put in tassie pans.
Leave in balls.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven; press Reese's cup into baked cookie until crust is even with top of Reese's cup.
Cool in pans for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: barbecued beans 'n beef
directions: Combine meat, salt and pepper.
Shape into 24 tiny meat balls. Saute in hot oil.
Combine vinegar, water, brown sugar, mustard, pepper, salt, onion salt, cayenne pepper, lemon juice, onion and butter in saucepan.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Add ketchup and Worcestershire sauce.

title: framer's breakfast
directions: In a skillet, cook onion in butter until tender.
Add potatoes, water and 1/2 teaspoon of salt.
Cover and cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Stir occasionally.
Beat together eggs, milk, 1/2 teaspoon salt and dash of pepper; stir in ham or bacon bits.
Pour over potato mixture. Cook, without stirring, until mixture begins to set on the bottom and around the edges.

Use spatula to lift and fold partially covered egg mixture so the uncooked portion flows underneath. Continue cooking over medium heat for about 4 minutes or until eggs are cooked but still glossy and moist.
Delicious!
Serves 6 or 8.

title: two minute hawaiian pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a store bought pie crust (suggest butter flavor).
Top with cherries and coconut.

title: letha's spanish rice
directions: Cook rice 20 minutes; drain. Add all ingredients and cook slowly until juice of tomatoes is absorbed. Serve hot.

title: sugarless date drops
directions: Cream butter and set aside.
Grind dates.
Blend with eggs and vanilla to make a paste.
Stir in dates and butter into batter. Add flour, milk powder, oats, raisins, chips, sunflower seeds and pecans.
Mix and drop by spoonfuls 1/2-inch apart on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° in regular oven for 10 to 15 minutes or conventional oven for 7 1/2 minutes to 10 minutes, until peak begins to brown.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: plum blossom chicken
directions: Brown chicken breasts in butter in a heavy skillet.
Stir curry powder into pan juices; sprinkle Beau Monde over chicken. Blend jam and sherry.
Pour over chicken.
Place lemon slices on chicken breasts.
Cover and simmer 35 to 45 minutes.
Remove chicken to warm serving platter; boil pan juices to reduce slightly.
Spoon over chicken to serve.

title: cream cheese cookies
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Blend in egg yolk and vanilla. Add dry cake mix, 1/3 at a time, mixing well after each addition. If mixer is used, add the last third by hand.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet so cookies will not run together during baking, approximately 2 inches apart.
Take a pecan half and push down into top of each ball.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Store covered.

title: fruit filled french toast
directions: Toss sliced berries with 1/4 cup sugar.
Let stand 30 minutes.

title: mrs. d's meat loaf
directions: Beat egg.
Add tomato soup; mix.
Add stuffing mix, hamburg, salt and pepper.
Pour into bread pan or loaf pan.
Top with bacon, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: noodle-potato soup
directions: Use medium pot to cook the potatoes. Use medium pan to cook noodles until done. Cut up onion, peppers and celery and add to potatoes. Take medium bowl and mix flour and milk until thick. When potatoes, onion, peppers and celery are done, add thickening to potatoes and stir until mixed well. Add noodles and stir until mixed.

title: orange chiffon cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar together.
Mix together other ingredients.
Fold in egg whites. Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: baked rice pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Place in a 2-quart casserole dish, coated with nonstick spray. Bake 30 minutes.
Stir and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: sugar-free chocolate cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and beat just until blended.
Pour into well-greased and floured 13 x 9-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done. Serves 24. Exchange:
1/2 bread, 1 fat.
Calories per serving:

title: homemade pizza
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients; beat vigorously, about 20 strokes.
Allow dough to rest (about 5 minutes) while preparing sauce.

title: aunt grace's fried chicken
directions: Cut up fryers and wash.
Dip into flour with seasoning and then into milk and back into paper bag with flour mixture.
Then drop into deep oil very hot.
Cover with lid.
Cook until done.

title: cracklin cornbread
directions: Mix
cornmeal
and flour.
Add egg and milk.
Stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in cracklins.
Heat a well-greased
10-inch cast-iron skillet until good and hot. Pour batter
into
skillet.
Bake
at
450° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown the chicken on all sides in the bacon drippings or butter in a large, heavy skillet.
Remove the chicken to a platter.
Cook the onions slowly in the fat remaining in the skillet for 5 minutes.
Stir in the flour and cook, stirring until the flour turns a light brown.
Add the ham or sausages, chicken and tomatoes.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 minutes.
Add the chicken stock, rice, garlic, green pepper and seasonings.
Cover tightly and simmer 20 more minutes.
Do not stir.
Gently push the shrimp down into the rice and simmer 2 or 3 minutes until the shrimp turn pink.
If the jambalaya seems dry when done, add a few tablespoons of hot chicken stock.
Makes 8 servings.

title: a. j.'s cookies
directions: Mix butter, sugar and egg yolk well.
Add vanilla; mix well. Gradually add flour, mixing well.
Roll into small balls or drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes.
Fun to decorate.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Mix all juices, soda and water.
Then add last 2 ingredients.

title: baked clams oreganoto
directions: Mix in enough bread crumbs for consistency to be moist, but not dripping.
Spoon into clam shells.
Do not smooth tops.
Rough tops make more desirable browning.
Place in pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes or more until tops are browned and crusty.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: curried fruit
directions: Note:
Any combination of fruit can be used.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly grease with shortening a 10 x 1/2-inch pie plate.

Cook crumbled beef and onion in skillet until brown, about 10 minutes. Drain, then stir in salt and pepper. Spread beef mixture in pie plate and sprinkle evenly with cheese. Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour evenly into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown and knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before cutting. Garnish with pickle slice and catsup, if desired.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat the ingredients.
Line pie crust with pecans.
Pour filling over pecans and bake at 350° for about 50 to 55 minutes.

title: abagail adams' champagne punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in hot tea in small bowl.
Add orange juice, lemon rind, lemon juice and rum; chill.
Just before serving, pour rum mixture and champagne over ice in a punch bowl.
Garnish with fresh orange slices and mint, if desired.
Yields 2 quarts.

title: cajun chicken wings
directions: Rinse chicken with cold water and pat dry.

Cut off and discard joint tip of each wing and half wings at the main joint. In food processor or blender, combine cayenne, paprika, garlic powder, oregano, thyme, onion powder, salt and white and black peppers.
Process until well blended.
With machine on, slowly pour in oil and process until a thick paste forms.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions, peppers and salt.
Add water to cover vegetables.
Let stand 12 hours; drain.
Combine sugar, vinegar and celery seed; bring to a boil.
Pour over vegetables and cool.
Pack in plastic freezer containers; seal airtight and freeze.

title: snowflakes
directions: Cream margarine, cream cheese and sugar well.
Beat in egg yolk, vanilla and grated orange rind.
Blend in flour, salt and cinnamon.
Fill cookie press.
Form cookies on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: In a microwave bowl, combine sugar and syrup.
Cook on High for 4 minutes.
Add nuts.
Stir and cook on High for 4 minutes. Add margarine and vanilla; cook on High 1 minute.
Stir and add baking soda.
Stir until foamy.
Spread on a greased cookie sheet, cool and crack up.

title: stuffed pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops and pour off drippings.
Place in a baking dish.
Lightly mix bread crumbs, onion, melted butter, poultry seasoning and 1/4 cup water.
Divide into 4 equal parts and place a mound of stuffing on each pork chop.
Blend soup and 1/3 cup water.
Pour over stuffing.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast mixture and buttermilk.
Roll and cut out.
Cook at 450° until brown.
This dough may be covered and refrigerated for several days and used as needed.

title: jones' burgers
directions: After mixing first 8 ingredients, form into patties about the size of 2 hamburgers.
Mix catsup and brown sugar together in small bowl.
Place patties on shallow pan, then spoon the catsup and brown sugar mixture over each.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: barbecued sauerkraut
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add all other ingredients to browned meat.
This can be made in slow cooker or in oven.	Bake 1 hour at 350° in oven; about 4 hours if using slow cooker.

title: healthy heart stir-fried chicken
directions: Heat oil in heavy skillet or wok.
Stir-fry chicken 2 to 3 minutes. Add onion, carrot, pepper and celery.
Stir-fry 3 minutes. Stir in water chestnuts, broth and soy sauce. Cook 3 minutes. Blend sugar, cornstarch and water. Add to chicken and stir until thickened. Serve over rice.

title: lime cucumber salad
directions: Combine Jell-O with boiling water and let cool.
Whip in lemon juice and salad dressing until smooth.
Stir in cottage cheese, cucumber and onion.
May pour in a mold or pretty glass bowl. Very summery flavor!

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water, then add cold water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Place in refrigerator until partially set, then add cakes which have been broken into small chunks, about the size of walnuts.
Pour mixture into mold or tube pan and return to refrigerator until firm.
Remove from pan or mold and frost with whipped cream.
(May use Cool Whip if preferred.)

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar, cinnamon and butter with hands.
Save 1 cup crumblies and set aside.
Add applesauce, baking soda and boiling water.
Mix with spoon.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Top with crumblies.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: jagersalat
directions: Cook unpeeled potatoes.
Cook Polish sausage.
Cool before adding to salat.
Mix all ingredients with potatoes.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Beat margarine and shortening until smooth and shiny.
Add sugar gradually and continue to beat until very smooth and fluffy. Add eggs one at a time beating after each one.
Add flour and baking powder alternating with the milk.
Add flavorings.
Pour into 10-inch greased Bundt pan.
Put in cold oven.
Bake at 325°. Remove from pan while warm.

title: creamy dijon pasta with vegetables
directions: In a large pot of boiling salted water, cook fusilli until just tender, 10 to 12 minutes.
Drain well.
Add cream cheese and milk to pot.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until cream cheese is melted and well blended with milk.
Add pasta and toss to coat.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Stir in mustard, ham, vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are very hot and crisp-tender, 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve topped with a sprinkling of grated Parmesan cheese.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix well all ingredients; shape into balls size of walnut and place in a shallow pan one layer in each pan.
(You can make bigger meatballs.)
Make sauce with 3 cups catsup, 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder; mix well and pour over meatballs.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
Freezes well; better if made the day before.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Grease a 9 x 1 1/4-inch or a 10 x 1 1/4-inch pie plate.
Blend all ingredients 1 minute on high in blender.
Pour into pie plate. Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Sprinkle beef cubes with flour that has been mixed with seasoning.
Toss with Wesson oil in 3-quart casserole or baking pan.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 30 minutes, until brown.
Stir once.
Add vegetables, tomatoes and water.
Cover and bake 1 3/4 hours at 350° or until tender.

title: chile con queso
directions: In a medium skillet, cook onion in butter or margarine until tender, but not brown.
Stir in tomatoes, chili peppers and salt. Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.
Add cheese a little at a time until cheese is completely melted.
Serve immediately with tortilla chips or corn chips.
This can be prepared ahead of time by leaving out the cheese and later microwave with cheese, stirring frequently.

title: lasagna
directions: Lightly brown beef and onion.
Add tomatoes (put through blender or cut with edge of spoon), tomato paste, water, parsley, salt, sugar, garlic powder, pepper and oregano.
Simmer uncovered, stirring occasionally, about 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook lasagna as directed; drain.

title: dinner in a skillet
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add uncooked rice and diced beef. Saute over low heat until rice is golden brown, stirring occasionally.
Dissolve bouillon cube in hot juice, add onion, pimiento, salt, liquid and pepper to rice mixture.
Blend lightly, cover.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed and rice is dry and fluffy.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream butter, shortening and sugar; add egg yolks.
Add flour and soda, alternating with buttermilk.
Add other ingredients except egg whites.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes in 3 greased and floured 8-inch pans.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt.
Add eggs, butter, milk and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in large casserole.
Cover with cheese and onion rings or potato chips.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: butterscotch granola cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, salt, baking powder and baking soda; set aside.
In a large bowl, combine butter, honey and brown sugar; beat until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in butterscotch morsels, oats, walnuts, raisins and wheat germ.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Allow to stand 2 minutes before removing from cookie sheets; cool completely.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/4-inch cookies.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Brown Rice-A-Roni in butter. Add celery and onion. Add broth and seasoning and mix.
Let simmer 20 minutes. Add cheese and chicken. Serves 6 to 8.

title: mystery dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric crock-pot (except hot dogs).
Stir several times until melted and mixed.
Add hot dogs and let simmer at least 1 hour.

title: strawberry ice cream soda
directions: Put ice cream in glass. Fill glass with strawberry soda.

title: grandmother durham's gingerbread
directions: Add soda to boiling water; mix all other ingredients in order given.
Pour batter into 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: ice cream sandwiches
directions: Beat egg, shortening, butter, vanilla and one-half of cake mix until smooth.
Stir in remaining cake mix until smooth.
Roll dough out and cut into squares.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hamburg soup
directions: Brown and drain meat in large kettle.
Add all but potatoes and cook until vegetables are nearly done.
Add potatoes last 20 minutes.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Boil sugar, margarine and milk for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and immediately add peanut butter, oats, cocoa and vanilla.
Drop from teaspoon onto wax paper until cool.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Saute pecans in 1/4 cup butter until light brown and crunchy, set aside.
Combine eggs, brown sugar and 1 cup of whole milk in top of double boiler.
Place over simmering water and beat with electric mixer until thickens, approximately 5 minutes. Beat in 1/4 cup batter.
Add a little at a time and continue to beat 5 to 7 minutes.
Let this cool after adding pecans.
I put in refrigerator/freezer for 30 minutes.
Add can milk and Eagle Brand milk.
Mix well. Pour into 1 gallon freezer.
Add whole milk to fill line.
Freeze.
Yields 4 quarts.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage over low heat until done and a crumbly consistency; drain and set aside.
Spread butter on bread and cut into cubes.
Place bread in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle sausage on bread and cheese on top of sausage.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Beat well and pour over cheese.
Chill 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: fri-chick pot pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour in pie crust, top with other crust. Slice top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix orange jello with 1 cup hot water, stir until dissolved. Mix pineapple juice with enough water to equal 1 cup, add to jello.
Allow to set until almost jelled.
Add shredded carrots, crushed pineapple and chopped pecans.
Put in mold and place in refrigerator until set.

title: brown swiss soup
directions: Melt butter in saucepan and add onion; cook until tender.
Add beef broth and water and bring to a boil.
Stir in brown gravy mix and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Divide into small ovenproof soup bowls.
Place a piece of French bread with Swiss cheese on top. Bake at 450° for about 3 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain the oranges and pineapple and pour in the bowl.
Add the sliced bananas and defrosted strawberries.
Coat everything with the peach pie filling.
The preserves in the pie filling keeps the bananas from turning brown.
Refrigerate until chilled and serve.

title: rice and mushroom casserole
directions: Melt butter, then mix all ingredients together with butter and bake at 375° for 1 hour or until all liquid is gone.

title: copper penny carrots
directions: Cook carrots; drain.
Cut onion into rings.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour over carrots and onion. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve hot or cold.
Keeps well.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple-cheese dip
directions: Drain pineapple, but not dry. Mix sugar, flour and cheese. Sprinkle over pineapple. Crumble crackers and sprinkle over pineapple mixture. Melt margarine and pour over top. Bake 30 minutes at 300 degrees.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix and pour into greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Mix thoroughly and
bake
at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool and top with 2nd layer.

title: nut bread
directions: *If using self-rising flour, omit baking powder and salt.

title: date balls
directions: Mix well and cook over low heat, stirring constantly, for 10 minutes.
Add 2 cups Rice Krispies.
Cool.
Form in small balls and dip in coconut.

title: *onions au gratin
directions: Peel onions and slice 1/4-inch thick.
Saute onions, garlic and mushrooms in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Arrange half of the onions in a buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with half the Swiss and Parmesan cheeses.
Top with remaining onions and cheese.
Dissolve bouillon cube in water. Pour over onions.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes.
Garnish with chopped parsley.
Good with either meat or poultry.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Let cream cheese become room temperature.
Dice chipped meat and onion.
Mix with cream cheese.
Add garlic.
Mix well.
Roll into a ball or use as a cheese spread.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: mint tea punch
directions: Pour 5 cups boiling water over tea bags; add mint sprigs. Cover and steep 5 minutes. Stir in sugar; steep 5 more minutes. Remove tea bags. Pour tea through a fine wire-mesh strainer into a pitcher, discarding mint sprigs. Stir in concentrates and 6 3/4 cups water. Chill. Serve over ice. Garnish, if desired.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Wrap 6 or 8 green beans with bacon; secure with a toothpick. Place in a casserole dish.
Repeat until you run out of green beans.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Spoon barbecue sauce over beans and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: warm winter punch
directions: In a large soup pot, heat apple juice with cinnamon candies until they melt.
Serve from your crock-pot.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: Mix and make into balls. Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cream cheese bars(yields 24 bars)
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and one egg in food processor.
Press into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and two eggs in food processor.
Pour over first mix.
Top with nuts, if desired.
Bake in oven preheated to 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool before slicing into bars.

title: individual tourtieres
directions: Fry meat and onion until pink is gone.
Add next 5 ingredients. Open packet crescent rolls; leave for 1/2 hour until workable.
Use one-half crescent roll for each tourtiere.
Place meat mixture size of golf ball on dough and work it up around meat.
Bake in 425° oven about 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 16.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together in salad bowl.
Then make dressing.

title: broccoli-pasta salad
directions: Combine broccoli, cauliflower, pepper, celery, tomato, cheese and onions.
Blend together mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and powdered sugar.
Pour over vegetables and toss until well coated. Add pasta and stir in gently until coated.
Makes a large salad and is better after it sets for 24 hours.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Spray 9 1/2 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix the ingredients; then stir in gently 4 hard-boiled eggs, chopped.
Cook at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, if casserole, or until pastry shells are brown if using pastry.

title: chicken marengo
directions: Brown chicken lightly in oil; drain.
Combine remaining ingredients; blend well and pour over chicken.
Simmer 35 to 40 minutes or until tender.

title: grapefruit pineapple salad
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar.
Dissolve gelatin in 1/4 cup water.
Add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Add to mixture.
Combine well.
Add crushed pineapple, grapefruit sections and juice and walnuts or pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: elaine's layered salad
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole, layer the lettuce, bell pepper, green onion, celery and peas.
Spread as a layer the mayonnaise, sugar and Cheddar cheese.
Crumble crisp bacon on top.
Make a day ahead and store in refrigerator.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Cream together the brown sugar and butter.
Add the egg.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Add and mix with sugar and butter.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased 8-inch square tin.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
Cut into squares.
Yields 16.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into small pieces.
Add onion slices, almonds and bacon.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise and vinegar. Pour over the vegetables.
Chill and serve.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except apples and last 3 ingredients well. Add apples and stir with spoon.
Pour in an 11 x 7 x 2-inch pan or tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sole gratin
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place mushrooms in ungreased 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of salt and pepper. Arrange fish fillets over mushrooms; sprinkle with remaining salt and pepper.
Pour wine around fish.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over top of fish.
Bake, uncovered, until fish fillets flake easily with fork (15 to 20 minutes).
Makes 4 servings, each containing 215 calories, 9 grams fat and 35 milligrams cholesterol.

title: sweet potato french fries
directions: Wash potatoes, scrubbing skin well.
Slice into french fries size potatoes.
Preheat oven 425° - 450°.
Spray baking sheet with Pam.

title: quick hamburger casserole
directions: Press hamburger in bottom of an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Put undiluted soup over hamburger.
Cover with Cheddar cheese.
Now place Tater Tots on top of cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: new zealand plum sauce(use for basting meat)
directions: Boil until tender.
Strain and bottle; the sauce doesn't have to be pressure sealed.
Use brown or green bottles.
Pour in liquid and screw on cap.
Store in dark place.
The longer it stands or is stored the better the taste.
If you have a blender, put the pitted plums through the blender and omit the strain.

title: broccoli-chicken quiche
directions: Prepare broccoli per package.
Drain well.
Place in bottom of pie shell.
Next, layer chicken, Swiss and Cheddar.

title: espresso gelido
directions: Stir instant coffee into hot coffee in medium size bowl. Heat sugar and 1/2 cup water in small saucepan. Pour sugar syrup into coffee mixture. Place in freezer until partially frozen, about 4 hours. Remove from freezer. Stir in remaining ingredients. Freeze sherbet in ice cream maker according to manufacturer's directions. Makes about 1 1/2 quarts.

title: black bean dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in the bottom of pie plate.
Add black beans and rotel over cream cheese.
Add cheese on top. Bake 20 minutes at 325 degrees.
Serve with tostados.

title: easy, quick and light muffins!
directions: Mix 2 ingredients together. Pour into muffin cups and bake! Tastes like pineapple upside-down cake!

title: mexican rice
directions: Heat oil in heavy saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in rice and cook about 1 minute.
Stir in onion and garlic and saute about 3 minutes, stirring frequently, until onion is translucent.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Increase heat to high and bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff rice and serve.

title: double pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar with beaten eggs.
Add pecans, margarine, syrup and vanilla; beat until blended well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in preheated oven.
Makes 2 pies.

title: jalapeno peppers
directions: Cut peppers from top down, halfway.
Soak 24 hours in brine that will float an egg (using plain salt).
Sterilize jars and place a few small pieces of garlic, 1 tablespoon of sugar and 1 teaspoon of olive oil in each jar.
Pack peppers in jar.

title: "lo-cal" pizza and bread dough
directions: In a bowl measure 3 cups of flour, yeast, salt and sugar.
Mix well.
Slowly add 2 cups warm water.
Stir.
Add another cup of flour and mix well.
Turn out on a floured counter and add the remaining flour.
Knead for 5 minutes.
This will make three 12-inch pizzas or 1 pizza and a good-sized loaf of bread.
Divide dough.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple well, reserving all juice.
Add juice to gelatin in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in water.
Heat to boiling, stirring to dissolve gelatin.
Remove from heat.
Blend in cranberry sauce.
Add lemon juice, peel and nutmeg.
Chill until mixture thickens slightly.

title: turkey chili
directions: Heat the oil in a large nonstick saucepan over medium heat. Add the onion; saute for 5 minutes.
Add the garlic, carrot, celery, sweet pepper and hot pepper; saute for 5 minutes.
Stir in chili powder, cumin and fennel seed; saute for 1 minute.
Add the tomatoes with their juice and chicken broth, breaking up the tomatoes with a wooden spoon.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium-low.
Add the turkey.
Simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until the turkey is tender.
Stir in corn.
Simmer for 10 minutes, until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in the cilantro and serve. Makes 4 servings.
Contains 299 calories and 7 grams of fat per serving.

title: sweet and sour chicken with vegetables
directions: In a medium skillet or wok, heat oil.
Saute chicken and onion for 5 to 6 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Stir in vegetables and sweet and sour sauce.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together.
Place in 9 x 13-inch pan. Top with crushed cornflakes and butter mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: In iron skillet, mix sugar and cocoa.
Add just enough milk to moisten, then add rest of milk and oleo; cook until it begins to thicken, about 30 minutes, over medium heat.

title: kelli's broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain. Melt cheese and butter. Mix all ingredients together and place in 9 x 13 casserole dish. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach and press out liquid.
Combine spinach, mayonnaise, sour cream, onion, water chestnuts and soup mix. Cover and chill several hours.
Serve with crackers or chips or hollow out a round loaf of unsliced rye or pumpernickel bread and fill with dip.
Cut up hollowed out bread to use as dippers.

title: chicken-pepper macaroni
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese by package directions.
Stir in remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.

title: applesauce bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; mix well.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Mix with dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Place into preheated 325° oven and bake.
Insert toothpick; when comes out clean bread is done.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Put chicken, soup and broth in casserole dish.
Mix flour, butter and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until brown.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Add eggs and oil. Stir in vanilla, pineapple, bananas and pecans.
Pour into 2 well-greased pans.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: oatmeal blueberry muffins
directions: In large bowl, stir together flour, oats and sugar.
Set aside.
In small bowl, mix egg, water and oil.
Add all at once to oat mixture, stirring just until moistened.
Stir in blueberries. Spoon in greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Blend sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle over batter.
Bake at 400° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Yield: 1 dozen.

title: apple crunch
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in 11 x 17-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle on 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix brown sugar, flour and butter to a paste; drop over apples and smooth out gently.
It will not be an even topping.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes; take out and top with pecans.
Bake another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; mix sugar, shortening, salt and boiling water.
Add flour; cover with greased wax paper and put in refrigerator.
Roll out and let rise when needed.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: cabbage scramble
directions: Wash cabbage and chop in small pieces. Season with salt, pepper and oregano or herb of your choice.

title: quick and easy chicken dish
directions: Parboil your chicken, then break it up in a baking pan.
Mix in a bowl the can of soup and sour cream; pour over chicken.
Then put the stuffing on the top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serve cranberry sauce on side.
Serves 4.
Enjoy!

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add soup and cheese. Melt together.
Add celery, rice and broccoli.
Put in buttered casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cake box cookies
directions: Mix together cake mix, eggs and oil, then add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto a cookie sheet.
Place in a preheated 350° oven for 9 to 11 minutes. Cookies will be soft when they come out.
Don't overcook.
Cool for a few minutes in pan, then transfer with a spatula to a plate to finish cooling.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Roll and cut as desired.
Bake on middle rack of oven at 450° for 10 minutes.
Dough may be covered and refrigerated for a week.
Use as needed.

title: danish puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Measure first cup of flour into bowl.
Cut in butter.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water and mix with fork. Round into a ball and divide in half.
Pat dough with hands into 2 long strips, 12 x 3-inches.
Strips should be 3-inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.

title: strawberry special
directions: Mix in large container, stirring after each addition. Mix well and put in a 13 x 9-inch dish.
Sprinkle some of the nuts over the top. Freeze.
Thaw 15 minutes before serving.

title: golden eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant in boiling salted water for 10 minutes; drain. Combine remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 1-quart casserole. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Good.

title: favorite barbecue sauce for chicken(yield: 2 to 3 broiler-fryer chickens)
directions: Measure all ingredients into saucepan.
Heat to boiling.
Keep warm, mixing thoroughly.

title: pineapple bake
directions: Drain pineapple and reserve juice.
Place pineapple chunks, cream cheese, and marshmallows in a dish.
Scramble egg with juice and cook over low heat, gradually adding sugar mixed with flour. Add optional Brandy.
Cook until thick.
Pour over top and cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Great served with ham and potato salad.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into large bowl.
Pour in Starter.
Mix to make a firm dough.
Grease 12-inch iron skillet with lard.
Pinch off balls the size of walnuts.
Place in pan. Set biscuits in warm place for 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake in 400° oven for 24 to 30 minutes.

title: applesauce fruit cake
directions: Boil
applesauce,
shortening
and sugar for 5 minutes, stirring
occasionally.
Let stand to cool.
Line 4 bread pans with wax
paper,
well greased.
Mix fruit and nuts in 3 quart bowl.
Sift flour, soda and spices over fruit and nuts, mixing until
fruit
is
coated.
Stir
in cooled applesauce mixture. Put in pans.
Bake
in	a
slow
oven
at 250° for about 2 1/2 hours. If cake gets too brown, cover with brown paper.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water.
Drain before preparing recipe.
Heat oil in large pot.
Saute onion until transparent. Stir in next six ingredients and saute three more minutes.
Add beans and 8 cups broth.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and cook until tender, 2 to 3 hours.
Add broth as needed.
Stir in turkey.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onions and seasonings.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Place biscuits in greased muffin tins, pressing to cover bottom and sides.
Spoon 1/4 cup mixture into lined cups and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 12 cups.

title: paula's maids of honor
directions: Beat together butter and sugar.
Add egg, almond flavor, flour and almonds and beat until smooth and fluffy.
Mix well the pastry ingredients.
Use plenty of flour to roll out.
Cut circles about 3-inches in diameter to place in cupcake pan that is well-greased. Add 1/2 teaspoon raspberry jam in pastry shell, then top with 1 teaspoon of almond mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Cool. Glaze with powdered sugar and milk.
Top with a cherry.

title: heavenly brownies
directions: Beat sugar and eggs together with electric mixer at high speed for 5 minutes.
Blend cocoa and flour together.
Mix into egg and sugar mixture.
Stir in
melted margarine by hand.
Then stir in pecans, vanilla and salt.

title: six calorie cookies
directions: Mix all together; spoon onto cookie sheet 2 inches apart. Bake for 8 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry surprise corn muffins
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease 12 medium muffin cups.
Combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine milk, egg and oil; add to dry ingredients, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill prepared muffin cups 2/3 full.
Place 1 1/2 teaspoons of relish in center of each muffin cup.
With tip of spoon, press lightly into batter.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes in muffin pan; remove to wire cooling rack.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions and pour into a greased 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Blend milk and pudding.
Beat into cream cheese.
Add pineapple.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled cake.
Sprinkle with coconut, cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to cut.

title: banana nougat cookies
directions: Sift together the dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening; add egg, banana, oats and chocolate chips.
Beat until thoroughly blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Remove immediately from pan.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: red punch
directions: Pour punch in large punch bowl.
Then put in sherbet.
Pour ginger ale over sherbet.
It will foam and fill the bowl.
Serve at any kind of party.
Makes a great punch.

title: chicken and dumplins
directions: Put cut up chicken to boiling in a large pot.
Cook until well done.
When done, take chicken out and let cool to touch, then debone chicken.
Don't discard the water and broth mixture.
Roll out biscuits in flour; cut up each biscuit into 4 sections.
Drop biscuits into water/broth mixture.
Alternate biscuits, butter and black pepper.
Have heat on medium-high.
After adding biscuits, it will tend to boil over, so adjust your heat accordingly.
Add the cans of soup and the chicken.
Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Salt to taste.

title: garden vegetable pie
directions: Grease pie plate.
Mix vegetables and cheese.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour over vegetables and cheese in pie plate.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bill's coating for fish
directions: Combine all the ingredients and place in a brown paper bag. Drop pieces of the fish into the bag and shake until the pieces are well coated.
Drop fish immediately into hot oil.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice as usual (do not drain broccoli).
Set aside. Saute onions and celery in butter or oleo.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Simmer until well mixed.

title: zucchini squash
directions: Cut squash into small pieces and simmer for 6 to 8 minutes; drain water.
Heat sour cream and sharp cheese.
Gently heat until cheese melts.
Remove from heat and blend in salt, paprika and egg yolk.
Mix squash and sauce thoroughly and place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until top is brown.

title: raspberry coffee
directions: Put the coffee in a large Ziploc bag.
Add the raspberry extract and vanilla.
Seal bag; shake well!!!
Brew coffee according to directions on the can.
Store unused coffee in the refrigerator.
Delicious when topped with Mundo Tropical Cayman Raspberry Chocolate Duster, just for a hint of chocolate.

title: dump cake
directions: Spread pineapple over a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Then spread cherries over pineapple.
Sift cake mix over cherries.
Sprinkle coconut over cake mix.
Melt butter and spoon over coconut.
Bake in a preheated oven at 375° for an hour.

title: toasted coconut cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding mix, water, oil and eggs; beat 4 minutes at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Stir in 1 1/3 cups coconut and pecans.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove layers from pans; let cool completely.
Spread Coconut Cream Cheese Frosting between layers and on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle top with 1/2 cup toasted coconut reserved from frosting recipe.
Yields one 3-layer cake.

title: orange punch
directions: Pour over ice in punch bowl.
Ice ring can be made with fruit in it for color.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes. Add to potatoes: salt, pepper, onion, cheese. Melt margarine and mix well with can of soup and sour cream. Pour margarine, soup, sour cream mixture over potato mixture and fold in until mixed. Pour into greased 9 x 13 casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, covered for the first 25 minutes, uncovered for the last 35 minutes. You may broil on high for and additional 5 minutes to brown the top.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Press crescent rolls into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook sausage, drain and crumble over crescent rolls.

title: christmas bells
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and vanilla thoroughly.
Measure flour by dipping method or by sifting.
Stir flour, soda and salt together; blend in.
Color 2/3 of the dough red or green.
Mold into 10 x 1 1/2-inch roll.
Mold this roll into a bell shape by squeezing the top together and leaving the lower half flared and curved; chill.
Save 1/4 cup white dough for clappers.
Roll out rest of dough on waxed paper into rectangle large enough to cover colored roll, about 10 x 4-inch; trim edges.
Wrap around roll; chill.
Heat oven to 375° (quick).
Cut 1/8-inch thick slices. Place 1/2 inch apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Press tiny ball of dough at bottom for clapper.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: venison roast
directions: Mix 1 tablespoon flour, salt, mustard, chili powder and pepper.
Rub well over meat.
Reserve any excess.
Place strips of bacon over meat and secure with picks.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Melt the butter in small pan and pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Brown the sausage; drain well and set aside.
Layer half the cubed bread in the buttered pan and sprinkle with half the basil, dill and cheese.
Then layer the rest of the bread cubes, herbs and cheese.
Sprinkle the sausage over all.
Beat eggs well.
Add milk. Pour over the contents of baking pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 1/2 hour or until set.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: cucumber slices
directions: Hollow out seed part of cucumber with apple corer. Stuff with mixture of tuna, mayonnaise, onion juice, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, salt, pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Chill and cut in 1/2-inch slices.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain the peas, green beans and corn.
Toss the rest of the ingredients together and mix with vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: banana pecan muffins
directions: Mix the yogurt and bananas.
Mix oil and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Stir in baking soda.
Fold in half the flour, then half the yogurt and banana mixture.
Repeat. Fold in the pecans.
Grease muffin cups or use foil or paper cups. Fill muffin cups about 2/3 full.
Bake about 20 minutes in 375° oven until lightly browned.
Let stand 2 to 3 minutes before removing from pan.
Delicious warm or cool!

title: cream puffs
directions: Measure water into medium saucepan.
Cut butter into pieces and add to water.
Heat until butter melts and water boils.
Add flour all at once.
Stir quickly until mixture forms a ball and leaves the sides of the pan.
Be sure not to overcook.
The mixture should not look greasy.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Beat well after each egg.
Shape puffs onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Lower heat to 350° and continue to bake for 25 minutes.
Prick with knife and let stand in oven for 5 more minutes.
Makes 16 medium puffs.
Large puffs (8) should cook a total of 50 minutes.
Small puffs (3 dozen) bake 20 minutes total.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, melt oleo in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over oleo, mix together and press into pan.
Pour milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Crush croutons.
Put sausage in bottom of a casserole dish; spread croutons on top.

title: hot peppered cheese biscuits
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine buttermilk and oil; add to flour mixture, stirring just until ingredients are moistened.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons flour over work surface.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2 inch thickness; cut with 1 1/2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place rounds on ungreased baking sheet; lightly coat tops with Mazola spray.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, until golden brown.
Yield: 2 1/2 dozen (38 calories and 1.2 fat).

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve the jello in water.
Let cool slightly before adding the rest of the ingredients.
Pour half the mixture into mold and let set. Spread the sour cream mixed with the sugar over the set jello.
Spoon remaining mixture over sour cream and let set.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Coarsely grind 10 cups (measure after grinding) zucchini, 4 cups onions and 5 tablespoons salt.
Mix and let stand overnight. Rinse and drain next day.

title: basic cookie recipe
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Blend all ingredients in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350 degrees for 10 minutes.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: crispy cheese wafers
directions: Cut oleo into flour; mix in cheese, pepper and salt.
Fold in Rice Krispies and mix thoroughly.
Roll into rolls and refrigerate.
Slice medium thickness and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sticks can be frozen and baked as needed.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into Bundt pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: cream chicken & biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 350.
Grease 11x7 dish.
Sauteed butter and onions in skillet.
Combine onions, chicken, soup and sour cream, milk and pimiento.
Mix well.
Spoon into dish.
Bake 15 minutes then sprinkle with 3/4 cup cheddar cheese.
Arrange biscuits on top, sprinkle rest of cheese.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt the first 3 ingredients in microwave.
Pour mixture over Rice Chex.
Put powdered sugar into a paper sack.
Put Rice Chex mixture in paper bag and shake.
Keeps a long time.
Tastes like Butterfingers.

title: terri's blueberry pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.
Grease and flour tube pan (or if you have a Stoneware Fluted pan from Pampered Chef, better yet).
Mix butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Beat well after each egg is added.
Add vanilla and beat until fluffy. Dredge berries with 1/4 cup flour and set aside.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder and salt, fold into cake batter until well blended.
Gently stir in the berries.

title: chess pie
directions: Cream together sugar and butter.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add corn meal and mix well.
Add lemon juice and mix well.
Add flour and mix well.
Add milk and mix well.
Spread mixture in an 8-inch pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add cheese and chile beans gradually. Mix occasionally until completely melted.
Serve with chips or flour tortillas.

title: purple plum cake cobbler
directions: Drain plums; save syrup.
Pit plums and arrange, skin side down, in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Mix 3/4 cup sugar and cornstarch in a pan; add reserved syrup.
Cook, stirring, until thickened.
Pour over plums.
Cream the oleo.
Add 2/3 cup sugar; beat until light.
Add egg, beaten well.
Mix dry ingredients together; add alternately with milk to first mixture, beating until smooth.
Spread over plums and bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream.

title: clam dip
directions: Mix all together and pat in 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with Romano cheese.
Bake in 350° oven 10 to 20 minutes until brown. Serve with "Great Crisps", tomato and celery crackers.

title: penuche
directions: Cook the first 4 ingredients to soft ball stage.
Add the butter and vanilla. Cool to 110°. Beat until stiff.
Add the walnuts and spread into greased pan.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs until light and add.
Press bananas through sieve or mash them and add lemon juice.
Blend with cream mixture.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and mix into banana mixture.
Add nuts or raisins. Bake in greased and floured loaf pan at 375° for about 1 1/4 hours.

title: baked coconut pie
directions: Three regular pie shells may be used instead of 2 deep dish pie shells.

title: fusilli pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to pkg. directions with 2 tsp. salt; drain, rinsing well with cold water.
Drain artichokes, reserving marinade; coarsely chopped.
In large bowl, combine fusilli, artichokes, reserved marinade, broccoli, cauliflower, carrots, red pepper, olives, pepperoni and mozzarella cheese.
Pour 1 cup dressing over salad; toss to coat.	Refrigerate covered several hours or over night.
To serve, toss salad, adding reserved dressing as needed.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Bring to a boil:
sugar, white vinegar, canning salt, celery seed and mustard seed.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place peaches in baking dish (8x8 or larger).
Trim crust from bread and cut each slice into 5 strips.
Place strips over peaches.
Mix remaining sugar, flour, egg and oleo.
Blend well and pour over bread strips.
Bake 35-45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Add yeast to 1/2 cup warm water.
Add sugar, salt, and oil to 2 cup hot water.
Let rise, then make into rolls and let rise again.
Bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: salad(diet)
directions: Mix all together; drain if too much juice and chill.
Add a small jar of pimentos.

title: shrimp in a blanket
directions: In a shallow dish, combine oil, garlic, salt and red pepper. Add shrimp and toss to coat well.
Refrigerate covered for 30 to 45 minutes.
Spray a cookie sheet lightly with Pam.
Individually wrap each shrimp in a basil leaf and then in the slice of Prosciutto and secure with a toothpick.
Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate up to 4 hours.
Bake in 350° preheated oven for about 10 minutes until shrimp are opaque.
Serve hot.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Mix well.
Pour in 1 large or 2 small graham cracker shells.
Refrigerate.
Also can be frozen. Delicious!

title: see's fudge
directions: Place margarine, chocolate chips, Marshmallow Creme, vanilla, salt and paraffin wax in a large mixing bowl.
Combine sugar and evaporated milk in a large pan.
Boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour hot mixture over ingredients in large bowl; beat until smooth.
Add walnuts.
Pour into buttered, 9 x 13-inch pan. Keeps for a long time in fridge.
Can also be frozen.

title: bitter-sweet game hens
directions: Line a casserole with foil.
It should have a cover and be just large enough to hold 2 game hens.
Brown Cornish game hens in butter.
Salt and pepper each inside and place in foil-lined casserole.
Pour sauce over; cover and bake at 400° for 1 hour. Serve with brown or wild rice.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, soda, salt and egg altogether; then add the can of fruit cocktail.
Place in ungreased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread 1/4 cup brown sugar and pecans on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: gingerbread cookies(makes 50 to 60 small cookies)
directions: Combine the sugar, ginger, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and baking soda. Mix well. Add the melted margarine, evaporated milk and molasses. Add the vanilla. Add the flour, 1 cup at a time, stirring constantly. The dough should be stiff enough to handle without sticking to the fingers. Knead the dough for a smoother texture. (You may need to add some additional flour, up to 1 cup, to prevent sticking.) When dough is smooth, roll it out 1/4-inch thick on a floured surface and cut it into cookies. Bake on floured or greased cookie sheets (I spray mine with Pam) in a preheated 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Cookies are done if they spring back when touched. Don't overcook!

title: graham delight
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers.
In a saucepan, mix sugar, butter, milk, egg and vanilla.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Pour over crackers and alternate with mixture, ending with whole crackers on top.
Cool.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Put all sugar, except enough to mix with flour, in frying pan with butter and brown, stirring constantly.
Warm eggs, milk and flour.
Mix both ingredients and boil until thick.
Put in two baked crusts.
Cover with meringue.

title: baked beans delish
directions: Brown together bacon, hamburger, onion and molasses.
Mix all together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.
