title: pecan-orange sweet potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes crosswise in 1/2-inch slices.
Alternate layers of potatoes and orange slices in casserole.
Combine cornstarch, brown sugar and salt.
Add peel and butter.
Pour in orange juice and cook until thickened.
Pour over potatoes and top with pecans. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Serves 8.

title: fruit cocktail cheese ball
directions: Drain juice from fruit cocktail. Remove grapes. Crush remaining fruit pieces. Add dry pudding to fruit and mix well. Then mix into cream cheese and form a ball. You may cover it with crushed walnuts or pecans, if desired. Refrigerate until ready to eat. Spreads best if allowed to soften some.

title: graham cracker cheesecake
directions: In a shallow pan, put the can of milk and put in freezer and let freeze until edges begin to crystalize.
While milk is freezing, crush package of graham crackers, 1/2 cup of sugar and 3 tablespoons butter and mix.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Save some mix to sprinkle on top.
Mix lemon Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and let stand to cool at room temperature.
Beat milk until whipped.
Beat cream cheese and 1 cup sugar and add to whipped milk.
Slowly add Jell-O mixture.
Pour over graham cracker mix. Let it get firm in refrigerator.
Then serve.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Mix cornbread stuffing with melted margarine.
Divide in half and put half on bottom of oblong casserole dish.
Cut chicken in chunky pieces and place over layer of stuffing.
Mix cream soups and broth.
Pour over chicken and scatter other half of stuffing on top of casserole.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Cook macaroni and rinse.
Combine all the ingredients in a large bowl.
Refrigerate for several hours or overnight to let flavors combine.

title: texas chocolate cake
directions: Boil margarine, oil, cocoa and water and pour over sugar, salt and flour, sifted.
Add buttermilk or sweet milk with vinegar, beaten eggs, soda and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.

title: cocktail(canape)
directions: Clean, devein and cook shrimp (not over 6 minutes).
Chop parsley and onion (I use chopped and frozen onion).
In a plastic bag, mix oil, vinegar and chopped garlic with parsley and onion mixture.
Add shrimp and toss.
Can be made up to 3 days in advance.
Prepare at least 24 hours in advance.

title: holiday fruit punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine juices and sugar.
Blend well. Just before serving, gently pour in ginger ale.
Garnish with ice ring.
Makes 16 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Press firmly in a loaf pan.
Bake about 1 hour.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: honey barbecue chicken
directions: Bake at 400° for 30 minutes; turn chicken.
Bake 40 minutes more.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Combine pecans and coconut and sprinkle in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pans.
Prepare cake mix by recipe on box.
Pour over pecans and coconut mixture.
Blend margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Bake at 400° to 450°.
Don't overbake.
Cake should be a bit gooey.
This cake cracks, that's where it gets its name, Earthquake.

title: stewed sweet potatoes
directions: Peel and slice the sweet potatoes.
Place in a heavy saucepan with all the other ingredients.
Simmer gently until tender, adding more water if necessary.
Allow the sweet potatoes to caramelize in the bottom of the saucepan.
Dish up with the brown, caramelized sides facing up.

title: pot pie dumplings
directions: Break 1 egg in measuring cup, and fill cup with milk.
Work 1/2 c. Crisco into 2-1/4 c. flour with salt.
Add milk and egg to flour mixture. Roll out dough on floured board, and cut into squares approximately 1-1/2 in.
Drop in boiling broth, either chicken or beef broth.
Cook 35 to 40 minutes.
Simmer with lid on pan.

title: josephine armour apple dumplins
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil. Add butter.
Peel and core apples.
Sift flour, salt and black pepper.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk all at once.
Mix just until flour is moistened.
Roll 1/4-inch thick.
Roll into squares. Place one apple in each square.
Fold.
Sprinkle generously with sugar and spices.
Dot with butter.
Place 1-inch apart in baking dish.
Pour mixture over apples.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Serve hot with cream.

title: homemade chili
directions: Fry onions and hamburger meat until it's cooked.
Add other ingredients and simmer.

title: calico beans
directions: Cook ground beef, bacon and onions until lightly brown.
Drain only if there is excessive amount of fat.
Stir in ketchup, salt, mustard, vinegar and sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients in large bowl and stir in meat mixture.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until bubbly.

title: cowboy cornbread
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; mix well.
Add eggs, milk and vegetable oil, stirring well.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Enjoy!!

title: holiday cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into one large or two small balls. Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: rice krispies cookies
directions: In large saucepan mix Karo syrup and sugar together.
Heat until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter, mixing thoroughly.
Add Rice Krispies, mix well. Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips in small saucepan then spread over Rice Krispies mixture.
Let harden and cut into squares.

title: patrick's soft pretzels(he can't eat just one)
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Put 1/3 cup brown sugar into 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Add dissolved yeast to this.
Add flour a cup at a time and knead.
If you have a bread machine, throw the flour in first, then pour in the liquid and push start. Let the machine knead for you!
Roll out pretzels.
Dip into baking soda water (2 tablespoons soda to 1 cup water).
Sprinkle on pretzel salt.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes and garlic in water and chicken broth, uncovered, until potatoes are tender and almost all liquid is absorbed, about 15 minutes.
Mash the contents; add salt and pepper to your taste and olive oil.
Mix well.
The basil olive oil adds a nice fragrant and flavor.

title: dumplings
directions: Mix; drop by spoon in hot broth.
Don't peek.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes, covered.

title: southwestern marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour over peeled and deveined jumbo shrimp of soft-shell crab and refrigerate 2 hours before grilling. Or brush on shrimp or soft-shell crab while grilling.

title: bread pudding with meringue
directions: Mix crumbs and milk and let soak for 10 minutes.
Add egg yolks, 1/3 cup sugar, fruit, butter and vanilla and stir.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: homemade gorp!
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in Ziploc bags.
Great for hiking and camping trips.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together; perk in coffee pot.

title: overnight lasagna
directions: Combine in a Dutch oven the tomato sauce, tomatoes, Accent, oregano, onion salt, pepper, garlic, mushrooms and onion.
In frying pan, brown beef and pork sausage.
Add to tomato mixture. Cook at simmer for 1 hour.

title: classic pecan pie
directions: In a large bowl, stir eggs, syrup, sugar, butter and vanilla. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven on a preheated baking sheet for 50 to 55 minutes or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Makes 8 servings.

title: favorite gingerbread
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; blend molasses and boiling water. Sift flour, soda, salt, ginger and cinnamon.
Beat all until smooth.
Batter is thin.
Pour into 9 x 9-inch pan, greased.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: baked whiskey cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar; add nuts, flour and whiskey.
Form into small crescents and bake on ungreased sheet at 400° for 4 to 7 minutes.
Cool and dust with powdered sugar.

title: german cole slaw
directions: Mix together vinegar, sugar and salad oil.
Hand cut cabbage. Chop green pepper and onion.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix altogether and let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food processor and add sugar.
Let sit overnight in refrigerator.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler until smooth; cool.
Whip the whipping cream and fold into cooled mixture.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crust.
Put in freezer.
Top with whipped cream, if desired.
Thaw in time for dinner.

title: pizza burger
directions: Brown ground beef and cook onion until tender.
Add tomato paste and seasonings.
Simmer 15 minutes uncovered.
Spoon hot meat mixture between buns.
Serve hot.

title: bean soup or fifteen bean soup
directions: Cover beans with
water
and soak overnight.
Drain off water, place in large kettle.
Cover with water and add baking powder. Boil about 15 minutes.
Drain and rinse beans.
(This helps in removing
gastric
"distress"
that
beans cause some individuals.) Place rinsed	beans into large kettle.
Add beer and 1 quart water
or
enough
to
cover.
Add ham bits or ham hocks, Italian seasoning,	carrots, celery and onions.
Cook 4 to 5 hours on simmer or in crock-pot on low.
Top with parsley and pepper to taste.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: lemon chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin in water.
Beat egg yolks; add 1/2 cup sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Cook over hot water, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add lemon rind and gelatin; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Cool.
Beat egg whites stiff; gradually add remaining 1/2 cup sugar, beating constantly.
Fold into cooled lemon mixture. Pour into a cooked pastry shell.
Chill until firm.
Whip some whipping cream and swirl on top but really isn't needed.

title: that good bread
directions: Slice bread every 2 inches, but not quite through.
Place 1/2 slice of Swiss cheese in every slit of bread.
Add all remaining ingredients to melted butter.
Place bread on heavy aluminum foil. Pour butter mixture over entire loaf.
Seal aluminum foil closed. Bake on cookie sheet 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: low-fat lemon-apricot soda bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; make a well in center of mixture. Combine buttermilk, apricots, margarine, egg and lemon rind.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter into an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan.

title: apple butter coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together 3 times. Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, and cream together until light and fluffy. Blend
in apple butter and vanilla. Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with sour cream. Turn half the batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with half the topping.
Spoon remaining batter into pan and spread evenly. Sprinkle with remaining topping. Bake for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve warm or cold, plain or with sweetened and flavored whipped cream.
Makes 12 squares.

title: creole greens
directions: Cook greens
minutes
and season with CHICKEN-STYLE SEASONING.
Saute other ingredients together.
Garnish edge of serving dish with sauteed vegetables.
Serves 5.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix wet ingredients together first (eggs, sugar, vegetable oil and shredded zucchini).
Mix well.
Then add flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Mix. Bake in 2 loaf pans at 325° for approximately 55 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and sugar, stirring until smooth.
Add cranberry sauce, pineapple and pecans; blend well. Beat whipping cream until foamy.
Gradually add powdered sugar, beating until peaks form; add vanilla.
Fold whipped cream into cranberry mixture.
Spoon into 8-inch square glass pan.
Cover and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before cutting into squares and serving.
Makes 9 servings.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Bake for 45 minutes at 325° for glass pan
and 350° for aluminum pan.
Serve with topping such as whipped cream, Dream Whip or Cool Whip.

title: chiffon cake
directions: Sift the first 4 ingredients together 3 times and set aside. Mix the next 4 ingredients and set aside.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar.
Mix all ingredients together and bake 55 minutes in an angel food cake pan.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter in microwave on Low heat until completely melted.
Sift cocoa and 1 box sugar together.
Add cheese and margarine to this a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add rest of sifted sugar.
Mix good.
Add pecans.
Press into two 9 x 12-inch pans.
Keep in refrigerator and cut into 3/4-inch squares when firm.

title: michelle's irish coffee
directions: In chilled bowl, beat cream, confectioners sugar and vanilla until stiff.
Refrigerate.
Prepare coffee.

title: vanilla caramels
directions: Put all ingredients, except vanilla in a large, heavy 8-quart pan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly (will scorch easily), until a temperature of 244° for a soft caramel.
If a firmer caramel is desired, cook to 246°.
Add vanilla after pan is removed from stove.
Pour into a buttered 10 x 12-inch pan.
Let cool and cut.
For turtles, add 3 pecans to each square of caramel and press together.
Dip into melted chocolate.
Lay on buttered wax paper.

title: four-flavor pound cake
directions: Coat the bottom of an 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan with cooking spray; dust with flour and set aside.
Combine 1 3/4 cups flour and next 3 ingredients in a large bowl.
Add oil and milk; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until batter is smooth (batter will be thick).
Add lemon rind and next four ingredients; fold in about 1/3 of egg whites; gently fold in remaining egg whites.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool pan 10 minutes; remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.
Serve 3/4 cup fresh strawberries with each slice.
Yields 16 servings.

title: chicken breasts in wine sauce
directions: Brown chicken in hot butter.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer, covered, 25 to 35 minutes or until chicken and carrots are tender.
Serve with rice.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Shape into ball and roll in chopped pecans. Chill.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix and bake cake, according to package, in a 9 x 13 pan. Cool.
After cooling, poke holes throughout the cake.
Pour on the following layers:
sweet and condensed milk, ice cream topping, cool whip, crushed candy bars. Refrigerate and serve.

title: sour cream fudge
directions: Cook everything except vanilla and nuts until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Let stand in pan of cold water until cool, then beat until creamy.
Just as it is ready to turn out onto a buttered pan, add the nut meats.
Cut in squares before it is entirely cold.

title: tortilla pie
directions: Layer the ingredients in a casserole bowl (in order).
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: six course casserole
directions: Crumble 1/2 ground beef in the bottom of an 11 x 3-inch pan (save 1/2 for top).
If using raw rice (not Minute), bring to boil and soak while preparing other ingredients.
Layer ingredients in order given, 1/2 meat last.
Pour soup over all (can thin with a little water, if desired).
Cover, bake at 325° to 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: vegetables and rice
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat and simmer 50 minutes or until moisture is absorbed.
Melt margarine in a heavy skillet.
Add water chestnuts and mushrooms; cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Add soy sauce, salt and pepper and stir in rice.
Yields 6 servings (158 calories, 10% from fat, per 1 cup serving).

title: hamburger soup
directions: In a large kettle, cook all ingredients except thyme until vegetables are done and barley is soft. Add thyme and cook for another 10 minutes.
Ready to serve!
Yummy!

title: busy day stew
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Heat.
Serve with toast or crackers. Serves 6.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown sausage or hamburg and drain.
Add tomatoes and juice, tomato paste, water, basil, garlic and salt.
Simmer covered for 15 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Cook noodles; drain.

title: chicken in lemon wine sauce
directions: Cut each chicken breast into 3 to 4 long slices.
Coat with flour; set aside.
Cut onions and peppers into long strips.
Saute onion and peppers in large frying pan.
Once done, remove and set aside.
In same frying pan use margarine to cook chicken until golden brown.
Add onions and peppers, squeeze lemons and add the juice (without seeds).
Add white wine and parsley.
Serve with egg noodles or rice.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Boil pineapple with sugar, margarine and cornstarch until it thickens.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Top with another crust.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then lower oven to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until top crust is browned.

title: shortcut chicken(gas grill recipe)
directions: Preheat gas grill on high for 10 minutes.
Turn control to medium flame setting.
Place chicken on cooking grids.
Close hood and cook 45 minutes, turning occasionally and watching closely. (Turn control to low, if necessary.) Meanwhile, combine preserves, dressing and dry soup mix.
Brush over chicken; grill 15 minutes longer, basting occasionally.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: venison casserole
directions: Boil noodles until tender in salted water and drain. Saute crumbled meat, green pepper and onion in small amount of fat.
Add other ingredients.
Put noodles in greased casserole dish and then pour other mixture into noodles.
Bake for about 30 minutes in a 275° oven.

title: south texas chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken. Let cool. Remove from bones and cut into bite size pieces. Mix soups, tomatoes and Velveeta in bowl. Heat in microwave until Velveeta is melted. Add salt, pepper and chicken. Crush enough tortilla chips to cover bottom of casserole. Pour 1/2 of chicken mixture over chips. Add more crushed chips over chicken. Pour remainder of chicken over 2nd layer of chips. Top with more chips. Sprinkle shredded Cheddar over top. Bake at 325° for 45 to 55 minutes or until Cheddar is melted. Top with chopped green onions and a spoon of sour cream.

title: donna's hash browns
directions: In pan, saute onion and bell pepper in margarine until tender. In a 13 x 9-inch pan mix soup, Cheez Whiz, sauteed vegetables and frozen hash browns together.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until brown and bubbly.

title: sicilian swordfishby - felicia r. mcclinton
directions: To clean and peel the tomatoes, briefly place them in boiling water.
Chop the onion and garlic.
Heat the olive oil in a frying pan then add the chopped onion and garlic until golden brown.
Place the sliced Swordfish in the frying pan and cover it.
Put the peeled tomatoes after a few minutes. Cook for at least 10 minutes.
Sprinkle chopped parsley and black olives on top before removing the Swordfish from the pan.
Serve while still hot.

title: crabby stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Toss crabmeat and lemon juice in medium bowl. Add next 5 ingredients and mix well.

Fill mushroom caps with mixture. Sprinkle with cheese. Rinse baking sheet lightly with water. Arrange mushrooms on sheet. Cover with foil and bake 12 to 15 minutes. Remove foil and continue baking until tips are golden, about 5 minutes. Serve immediately.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: giant and people casserole
directions: Mix soup into a bowl; pour 1 1/2 cans of the peas and carrots liquid to dilute.
Set aside.

title: hearty potato ham chowder
directions: In large kettle, melt margarine or butter; add onion and green pepper and cook until tender.
Add potatoes, 2 cups water and seasonings.
Cover and simmer until potatoes are tender.
Make paste of flour and 1/3 cup of water and stir into the potato mixture.
Add milk and cook until slightly thickened.
Stir in corn and ham.
Heat thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: cherry crisp
directions: Pour cherries into a 9 x 9-inch pan (sprayed with Pam).
Mix together flour, sugar, nuts and melted margarine.
Sprinkle over cherries.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Layer ingredients into 9 x 13 pan.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Combine margarine, oil, eggs and vanilla.
Add 1 cup sugar and blend well.
Add rest of dry ingredients and mix.

title: pealing bells
directions: In a large mixing bowl beat margarine with an electric mixer on medium to high speed about 30 seconds or until softened.
Add about half of the flour and all of the sugar, egg yolk, vanilla, baking powder and, if desired coconut flavoring to the margarine.
Beat until combined, scraping sides of bowl occasionally.
Beat or stir in the remaining flour.
Shape dough into two 6-inch rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper or plastic wrap.
Chill for 2 to 24 hours.
Cut dough into 1/4 inch thick slices.
Place 1 inch apart on a ungreased cookie sheet.
Place a cherry half on the bottom half of each slice for a bell clapper. then let dough stand for 1 to 2 minutes to soften for easier handling.
Fold in sides of each slice, overlapping at top and slightly covering cherry.
Pinch sides to resemble a bell shape.
Bake at 350 degrees oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are firm but not browned.
Remove cookies and cool on wire racks.
Makes about 48 cookies.

title: zucchini bake(very good)
directions: Mix
ingredients
well.
Put in a buttered baking dish. Pour 2 or	3
beaten eggs over top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: easy lemon cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package for 2 (8 or 9-inch) round cake layers. Cool completely.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Put in greased loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Makes 2 loaves or 18 muffins.

title: reunion salad
directions: Mix veggies and put in bottom of large Tupperware dish.
Add shredded lettuce.
Mix sugar, mayonnaise and Parmesan thoroughly and spread on top.
Cover tightly with lid and refrigerate overnight.
Mix and add bacon on top before serving.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Make one quart of rather stiff cornmeal (water, cornmeal and salt).
While still hot, add margarine and sugar.
Let stand until lukewarm, then add yeast dissolved in a little warm water.
Let it raise until very light, then mix in enough flour for a moderately soft dough.
Leave overnight, roll out what is needed and spread with butter and fold if desired.
Roll again.
Cut as biscuits and let raise again in warm place.
Bake in hot oven about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: quick and easy enchiladas
directions: Brown the hamburger; add 1/2 grated cheese, 1/4 cup salsa and the refried beans to the drained hamburger.
Let simmer until the cheese melts.
Mix 1/4 cup of salsa with the enchilada sauce and pour a small amount in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
You may need an 8-inch pan also.
Fill the tortillas with a nice amount of the mixture.
After rolling, place in the pans.
Top with the remaining sauce and the grated cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven, covered, about 30 minutes, until the cheese melts.
Let sit a few minutes and serve. May be cut in squares or give everyone the whole enchilada.
Add salad and dessert and enjoy.

title: cheesecake
directions: Butter sides and bottom of an 8-inch spring-form pan.
Crush graham crackers and coat bottom with crumbs.
Refrigerate pan until ready to use.

title: the impossible pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Grease baking dish or 2 pie pans with butter.
Pour pie mixture in pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Makes its own crust.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: beans and sour cream
directions: Cook beans as directed on package; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients; heat until hot.

title: cheese muffins(fargozas)
directions: Sift dry ingredients in bowl.
In separate bowl, beat egg with butter and stir in milk.
Pour into flour mixture.
Stir just to moisten ingredients, adding cheeses, garlic and onion.
Batter will look lumpy.
Grease muffin tray; fill 2/3 full with batter. Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: peach refrigerator dessert
directions: Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with whole graham crackers. Cream butter and powdered sugar.
Add eggs and salt.
Beat well and spread evenly over crackers.
Top with another layer of crackers.
Combine whipped cream, sugar, vanilla and peaches. Spread over second layer of crackers.
Crush a few crackers and sprinkle over top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: peggy's dirty rice
directions: Cook chicken gizzards and livers until tender.
Drain, reserving water, dice meat and set aside.
In heavy iron Dutch oven fry pork and beef until browned.
Remove from pot, and in remaining fat brown flour until very dark brown.
Add diced onions, bell pepper and celery and cook until all are soft and browned.
Add garlic, seasoning and broth from the chicken.
Let simmer about 20 minutes.
Add cooked rice and meat, mixing thoroughly.
Turn on very low heat, cover and let steam for 30 minutes.
Five minutes before serving time add green onion tops and parsley, lifting and blending with fork.
Serves 12.
Enjoy!

title: tuna fish salad
directions: Put the tuna, Miracle Whip, sweet and dill pickle into a large bowl. Chop up one of the boiled eggs and put in with the tuna mix.
Add salt, pepper, and onion powder or salt and garlic powder to your taste.
Mix all of these ingredients together.
Add a little dill pickle juice for added flavor.
Place the mixture into a serving bowl and flatten down the top. Slice the 2nd egg and place on top of the tuna.
Sprinkle a dash of paprika over the top for looks.
Serve with Ritz Crackers.

title: chicken divan
directions: Put cooked broccoli in a casserole dish.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry powder.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Cover with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts well.

title: lemon chess pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Mix together flour, meal and sugar.
Beat egg yolks; add to them the milk.
Add melted butter; add lemon juice.
Whip egg whites with a pinch of salt.
Add the liquid mixture to the egg whites, folding in until smooth.
Pour batter into two unbaked pie shells.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned and solid to the shake.

title: the ranch house sour cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate.

title: flapper pudding
directions: Spread half of wafer crumbs in bottom of 10x6x1 1/2 inch pan.

title: shortcake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together in large bowl.
Set aside. Mix the next three ingredients together.
Then combine all ingredients together and put into greased 9 x 9 inch pan.
Bake 12 - 15 minutes at 450°. Eat with fresh blueberries, or strawberries.

title: b.c.h. hermits
directions: Preheat oven to 360°.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together and set aside.
Cream Crisco and brown sugar together then add molasses, eggs and vanilla and mix well. Mix in the dry ingredients and add the raisins and nuts.
Shape into flattened logs (2 to a cookie sheet) and bake for 5 to 8 minutes.
Cool slightly then cut each log to form bars.
(To make things easier I put the dough into a large pastry bag without a decorating tip to form the logs and I cut the bars with a pizza wheel.
I also undercook slightly to get a chewier cookie.)

title: famous oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat together shortening, sugars, eggs, water and vanilla until creamy; add combined ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet. You may add raisins, chopped nuts, coconut or chocolate chips. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: crumb cake
directions: Mix together all the ingredients to form a batter.
Pour into a 15 x 11-inch jelly roll pan.

title: mom's peas and dumplings
directions: Cook peas in salted water with diced onion, butter, sugar and pepper until tender.
Do not drain.
Turn down to a slow boil and add dumpling mixture with spoon.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles or macaroni in salted water; drain.
Put in casserole.
Drain tuna.
Cut up onion.
Place soup in saucepan with 1/2 can of milk to each can of soup.
Cook until smooth. Add tuna.
Place onion, grated cheese and peas in casserole with macaroni.
Add soup mixture; mix.
Slice more cheese thin and place on top of dish.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts and browns a little.
Very good!

title: strawberry jam bars
directions: Combine all ingredients (except jam) together.
Spread 7/8 dough on cookie sheet.
Spread strawberry jam over entire surface. Sprinkle remaining dough on top and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Any flavor jam can be used.

title: holiday pears with creme chantilly
directions: Combine water, sugar, lemon juice and ground mace in a shallow 2-quart casserole, stirring until sugar dissolves.
Set aside. Peel pears, leaving stems intact.
Place pears in sugar mixture; spoon over pears.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 minutes, or until pears are tender but still hold their shape.
Carefully remove pears from sugar mixture.
Discard sugar mixture; return pears to casserole.

title: lime cooler
directions: Put sherbet in a punch bowl; pour ginger ale over.
Stir until sherbet is broken in small pieces.
Serve in glasses or punch cups.
Yield:
12 to 15 servings.

title: lunchbox apple bean salad
directions: In a medium size bowl combine apples, green onion, celery and chilies; mix well.
In a small bowl, mix together vinegar, oil, salt and hot red pepper sauce (if desired); stir into bean mixture.
Cover and refrigerate at least 30 minutes before serving.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: strawberry kringle cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Cool.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Gently stir in strawberries and sour cream. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake packaged cake mix according to directions on box (2 layers).
Cool.
Split layers into 4 layers. Put layers together with container in refrigerator.
Chill for 3 to 4 days.

title: goodie bars
directions: Melt the oleo in a 12 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle the graham cracker crumbs over the butter.
Spread the chocolate chips over the butter.
Spread the butterscotch chips over the chocolate chips.
Pour the Pet milk over the above and sprinkle with the chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Cut while still warm. Makes 30 (1 x 1 1/2-inch) pieces.

title: coconut date krispies
directions: Cook dates, sugar, egg and butter on top of double boiler for 15 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add vanilla, Rice Krispies and nuts.
Form into balls and roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.

title: fruit and fiber muffins
directions: In large bowl mix cereal and milk.
In separate bowl sift together dry ingredients.
Add egg and oil to the cereal; blend. Add flour mixture to cereal.
Fill muffin cups 1/2 to 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: orange date filling
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add beaten egg.
Stir and cook 3 minutes.
Cool before spreading.
Use between layers of plain cake; top with white frosting.
May sprinkle with coconut.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut all fruits in big chunks.
Cover with undiluted frozen orange juice which has been thawed.

title: black bottom cupcakes
directions: Combine flour, sugar, cocoa, baking soda, salt, water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Mix until blended.
Fill cupcake papers 1/2 full.
Combine softened cheese, egg and sugar until fluffy.
Drop a large spoonful on top of each cupcake.
Add about 10 chocolate chips to each.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes about 20.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Take 2/3 cup pineapple juice and 1/3 cup orange juice.
Combine with vanilla pudding.
Cook until it comes to a boil and until clear.
Pour over pineapple.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Add remaining fruit before serving.
Will keep several days.

title: holiday cranberries
directions: Place water, sugar and cranberries in saucepan.
Bring to boil and continue boiling until cranberries "pop."
Cool.
Add walnuts; mix together.
Keep a few for top decoration.
Cool in refrigerator until ready to serve or overnight.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Layer squash
in
bottom
of casserole dish.
Mix soup, sour cream, pimento and water chestnuts together and spread on top of squash.
Sprinkle
cheese
over
top.
Mix stuffing and margarine together and
layer
on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mary's chocolate oat chip cookies
directions: Heat oven at 375°.
Beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Beat well.
Stir in oats and chocolate chips.
Stir well. Drop by rounded measuring tablespoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for chewy or 12 to 13 for crisp.
Cool 1 minute on cookie sheet.
Remove to wire rack.
Cool completely. Makes 5 dozen (2 1/2-inch) cookies.

title: sourdough coffee cake
directions: Mix well and pour into greased 9-inch pan.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Mix together well.
Let stand; mix again until liquid is soaked in quite well.
Roast a bit in the oven.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and chill until starting to thicken.
Add the cherries and pineapple.
You may add nuts if you want.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Blend together salmon, 1 egg, flour, potato, onion, salt and pepper.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie
directions: Soften gelatin
in
cold water.
To slightly beaten egg yolks, add about
half of the sugar and add the pumpkin, milk, spices and salt.
Cook
until
thick
in a double boiler.
Add gelatin to hot mixture
and
let
cool.
Beat
the egg whites until frothy and slowly
add
the
rest
of the sugar and the cream of tartar; beat
until
it is very stiff.
Fold pumpkin mixture into beaten egg
whites.
Spoon
into
a
baked
9 or 10-inch pie shell. Awfully good with whipped cream when it is served!
This is Jim's mom's recipe.

title: cheese balls
directions: Let cheese
and
butter or oleo set at room temperature to soften.
Cream
well.
Sift
flour;
divide
into
thirds, adding a third of flour at a time to all other ingredients and mix well. Shape
mixture
into
small
balls with hands, then place on cookie
sheet
and
mash 3 times with fork.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and chopped onion.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Simmer very gently for 45 to 60 minutes in a covered skillet.

title: pineapple cream pudding
directions: Put half of
the
coconut
in
(4 ounce) ramekins or custard cups.
In
a
medium
saucepan, combine flour, 2/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon salt.
Whisk in the egg yolks.
Add the milk
gradually.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until thick, 6 to	8 minutes.
Drain pineapple and stir in with 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into cups.

title: country church pudding
directions: Place pie filling in a 2-quart casserole dish, then pour crushed pineapple with juice on top of filling.
Mix pecans with cake mix, then sprinkle on top of pineapple.
Melt oleo and pour on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chunky gazpacho
directions: In a large mixing bowl, mix tomato juice, garlic, sugar, salt, seasoned salt, olive oil, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and hot sauce.
Mix until oil and seasonings are dissolved.
Pour into a large refrigerator pitcher.
Stir chunky vegetables into juice mixture and add diced fresh tomatoes.
Chill overnight or 4 hours. Serve cold with seasoned croutons on top.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: beef and spanish rice
directions: Melt oleo in a 4-quart pot.
Add rice and brown slightly.
Add hamburger and brown.
Add remaining ingredients and cook together, covered, over medium heat on top of stove for about 25 minutes. Put in baking dish in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: pizza salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine macaroni, tomatoes, Cheddar cheese, green onions and pepperoni.
In small bowl, combine oil, Parmesan cheese, vinegar and seasonings; pour over macaroni mixture.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
Top with croutons (optional) just before serving.
Great for large barbecues.

title: walnut apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Mix and sift flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and mace.
Stir in vanilla, apples and walnuts.
Batter will be stiff.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes and then remove to rack.
During baking, a macaroon-type crust forms on the top, so it needs no icing.
Keeps very moist for many days.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Soak bread with milk in casserole dish.
Melt butter.
Saute onion, pepper and celery in butter.
Add crab and shrimp; saute until cooked.
Mix with bread in casserole dish.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350° or for 15 minutes in microwave.

title: southern indian pudding
directions: Prepare grits in salted, boiling water as directed on package. Stir in sugar and butter.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla to the mixture.
Fold in the raisins and almonds.
Pour into a greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake in preheated slow oven at 325° for approximately 50 minutes.
May serve hot or cold.
Garnish with whipped topping if desired.

title: orange treat cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed; substitute 1 1/2 cups whipped cream for oil or butter.
Bake in 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans for 30 minutes.
Cool in pans on rack for 15 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool.
Beat cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Beat in concentrate gently; stir in remaining whipped cream.
Fill and frost cake.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie crust.
Place pecans in pie shell.
Combine first 7 ingredients; pour over pecans in pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: easy sour cream biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto baking sheet and cook at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: picante sauce
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered, stirring often.
Pour into hot jars; seal.
Process in hot water bath for 35 minutes.
Yields 10 pints.

title: spinach and cheese puffs
directions: Cook spinach as directed with onion.
Drain and press well. Combine eggs, cheese, Blue cheese dressing, margarine and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Add the spinach and muffin mix.
Mix well. Cover and chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Cover and chill or freeze.
When ready to bake, place on a baking sheet and bake at 350° until light brown.
If chilled, bake 10 to 12 minutes.
If frozen, bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
They freeze well. Serves 60 puffs.
Each serving contains approximately 104 calories.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Parboil shells and rinse with cool water.
Drain spinach completely.
Mix ingredients together with the spinach.
Using a tablespoon, stuff each shell, placing shells on wax paper as you go along.
Flash freeze shells for 2 to 3 hours.
Store in Ziploc bag in freezer.
From freezer, place shells in a pan.
Do not let shells touch each other.
Cover each shell with sauce.
Cover pan with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Great to do ahead for parties!

title: sandra's soup
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain grease.
Salt and pepper to taste. Add remaining ingredients.
Serve with corn bread.
Great for a family on the run.

title: sunday school punch
directions: Mix oranges (juice and rind), sugar and water.
Stir well until sugar dissolves.
Pour equally into 3 (1 gallon) milk jugs. Fill each with water.
Color as desired.
Makes 3 gallons.
Serve in punch bowl with added ginger ale.

title: romance cookies
directions: In a large bowl, combine butter and sugar until creamy and well mixed.
Beat in salt and egg yolks.
Add flour and mix well, kneading with fingers to make a smooth dough.
Pat dough evenly into the bottom of a greased 12 x 17-inch pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° preheated oven until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and spread with jam and chocolate bits.

title: cream cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Make 2 balls and store in refrigerator overnight.

title: russian rocks
directions: Mix in order given and drop from tip of spoon on a greased cookie sheet and bake in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: bulgar wheat salad
directions: In a medium saucepan, bring water and bouillon cube to a boil.
Add wheat and remove from heat.
Let stand 30 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and wheat is tender.
Let cool.
Add broccoli, flax seeds, almonds, spices and dressing.
Toss gently. Transfer to serving dish.

title: water chestnuts and bacon(appetizer)
directions: Drain chestnuts.
Cut bacon strips into 3 pieces each.
Wrap 1/3 bacon strip around each chestnut.
Overlap ends of bacon and insert a toothpick into, but not through, chestnut.
Arrange on a cookie sheet, leaving 1/2-inch space between each.
Broil approximately 20 minutes or until bacon is crisp or bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until bacon is crisp.
Remove pieces to a plate with paper towels to absorb excess grease.
Serve hot. Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: hard sauce
directions: Beat butter at high
speed
of mixer until fluffy.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Makes 2 cups.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Mix ingredients and form 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated sugar, then place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook ingredients in large saucepan on simmer until almost tender.
Cool.
Transfer to a casserole dish of any shape.
Top with rolled out unbaked pie crust.
Bake in oven at 400° until crust is done.

title: blackberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain berries and pineapple, saving liquid to make one cup.
Add this liquid to jello.
Stir in berries and pineapple.
Pour into 2-quart flat Pyrex dish.
Cover and refrigerate until firm.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine ingredients, use half of the pecans, and mix well. Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Form into a ball and chill more if soft. Roll in other half of pecans.
Wrap in plastic until ready to use. The longer it sets, the better it gets.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix
all
ingredients in large bowl.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix first four ingredients together and let season overnight. Add rest of ingredients and chill.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: skillet fudge
directions: Melt margarine in skillet over low heat.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until all are dissolved.
Pour into a buttered 8x8 dish.
Cut when cool.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (10 x 1 1/2 inches). Brown beef and onion, drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in pie plate.
Beat Bisquick, milk and eggs until smooth, 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer.
Pour into plate. Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes, sprinkle with cheese.
Bake again until knife inserted in center is clean (5 to 8 minutes). Cool and serve.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: butter cookies
directions: Sift flour and baking soda together.
Cream butter and sugar in separate bowl.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix in dry ingredients and divide in two parts making a ball.
Roll on floured surface 1/8 inch thick and cut into desired shapes.

title: batter rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl combine 2 cups all-purpose flour and 1 package active dry yeast.
In a saucepan heat 1 1/4 cups of milk, 1/2 cup shortening, 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon salt, just until warm (115° to 120°) and shortening is almost melted.
Stir constantly.
Add to flour mixture and add 1 egg.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, lemon juice, mayonnaise, soup, pimentos, salt, Accent, and eggs.
Place in 11 x 7 inch rectangular dish. Top with cheese, chips and almonds combined.
Let stand overnight in fridge.
Bake at 400° for 20-25 minutes and serve.
Yields: 6-8 servings.

title: italian chicken
directions: Arrange chicken in single layer in ungreased baking dish. Pour dressing over chicken. Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken easy
directions: Mix soup, 1 soup can of water, onion soup mix and rice in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and paprika.
Cover and bake at 325° for 1 hour. Uncover, bake an additional 15 to 20 minutes or until chicken and rice are done.

title: italian chicken salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients, chilling until ready to serve in lettuce-lined bowl.
Garnish with tomato wedges.
Serves 6.

title: aunt sharon's chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine oatmeal and nuts in a big bowl.
Combine other ingredients and heat.
Let come to a good boil.
Add vanilla. Pour over oatmeal mixture and mix well.
Drop on waxed paper. Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: holiday cranberry mold
directions: Prepare light colored jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 of pineapple and oranges with 1 cup liquid.
Pour into top half of jello mold; chill until almost set.
Insert cherries, if desired, and allow to set.
Melt cranberry sauce over low heat.
Prepare cherry jello with 1 cup boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients, including melted cranberry sauce.
Pour carefully on top of set mold; chill thoroughly.

title: quick biscuit pudding
directions: Pour pineapple juice over biscuits. Let soak until soft. Stir in sugar, eggs, oil and all sliced apples. Stir in vanilla flavor. Pour into a well-greased pan. Place in a 400° oven until brown. Serve hot or cold.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Spread cooked chicken in bottom of baking dish.
In a small bowl combine soups, milk, tomatoes and chili powder.
Mix in chopped onion and pour over chicken.
Spread cheese and Doritos on top.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Blend onion, celery, soup, pimiento, mushrooms, mayonnaise, rice, green beans and chicken.
Pour into two 13 x 9-inch baking dishes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with potato chips to serve.
May be prepared ahead.
Freezes well.
Serves 16.

title: glazed fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring gently to mix.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.

title: melon balls with lime sauce
directions: Blend water, sugar and juice and grated peel of lime in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool.
Pour sauce over fruit and toss to coat.
Chill 4 hours. Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: daddy's coffee
directions: Pour water into water well on coffee machine.
Put coffee grounds into ground cup on coffee cup.
Turn on.
About 5 minutes Daddy will holler, "Don't forget the cream and sugar."

title: buckwheat stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook potatoes (in just enough water to cover) until done. Drain potatoes; save potato water.
Mash potatoes.
Add enough water to potato water to make a total of 2 quarts.
Add potatoes to the liquid.
Cook onion in 3/4 cup oil until soft; add to potatoes. Add salt and pepper.
Bring potato mixture to a boil; add washed buckwheat groats.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; cover.
Let stand until all liquid is absorbed. use 2 medium heads of cabbage for the above filling.
Roll us usual. Arrange halubtsi in roaster; add water to cover.
Drizzle with cooking oil.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until cabbage and filling are done.
Serve with sour cream.

title: toasted holiday pecans
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan.
Mix in next 3 ingredients.
Stir in pecans and spread in a glass baking dish. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Turn out onto paper towel and sprinkle with salt.
Let season one day before serving.
Yield: 4 cups.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix in bowl the pie filling and pineapple.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spread dry cake mix over the top and pat the cake mix evenly to cover pie filling/pineapple mixture.
Slice butter thinly and completely cover every tiny part.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix with your hands. After mixing well, place in a well prepared glass baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours, covered with foil. Take foil off to brown the last 1/2 hour.

title: soapsuds
directions: Mix soap and water in large bowl.
Beat with electric mixer until clay-like.
Mold into objects.
Dries to hard finish.
This recipe makes 1 cup.
You can double or triple it.

title: chili
directions: Brown beef and onions together until done.
Drain excess grease.
Add all ingredients and cook slowly for 1 hour, stirring often.
Can be cooked in crock-pot.
Add water if you don't like the chili thick.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in melted butter until tender.
Stir in mushroom soup and juice; mix well.
Add cheese, mushrooms and almonds.
Mix with rice and put in buttered casserole.
Bake 20 minutes at 350° or until bubbly.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and onions.
Add half of each cheese. Divide this into 2 unequal halves.
Add chicken to the smaller half.
Use this to fill the tortillas, rolling up each around some of the filling.
Spread half of the remaining soup mixture in bottom of 10 x 13-inch pan.
Add filled tortillas.
Top with remaining soup mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until hot.
Serves 10.

title: double corn muffins
directions: Prepare muffin mix according to package directions.
Stir in corn.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Drop spoonfuls of deviled ham on center of each muffin.
Bake at 375° about 20 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: peanut butter ball
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and salt.
Add butter.
Add pecans and mix well.
Roll into ball.
Bake at 325° and then cool.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: brown rice pilaf
directions: Combine bouillon cube and water in a 1-quart casserole; stir until dissolved.
Add remaining ingredients, except celery; stir. Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes; add celery, cover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: marinated turkey
directions: Cut turkey with the grain into 1-inch slices.
Combine 7-Up, soy sauce, garlic powder and horseradish in bowl.
Add turkey. Marinate in refrigerator for 5 to 7 hours.
Broil or grill over medium heat.
Turn frequently.

title: chicken scallopini
directions: 1. Pound each chicken breasts to 1/4 - 1/8 thin. Dredge in flour, salt, and pepper.
2. Fry chicken in pan with some oil until cooked.
3. Add parsley, lemon slices, and sherry. Cook and stir
several minutes. Serve immediately.

title: mexican cheese ball
directions: In a food processor fitted with steel blades or mixer, combine all ingredients except chiles and walnuts; blend thoroughly.
Stir in chiles.
Divide mixer in half.
Chill 15 to 20 minutes.
Shape each portion into a ball.
Press each into walnuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix together sour cream, salad dressing and seasonings. Marinate tomatoes, avocados and beans in this mixture for 1 to 3 hours.
Just before serving, add lettuce and corn chips.
Toss.

title: nine bean soup mix
directions: Combine all beans and mix well.
Divide into 2 cup packages for storing and gift giving with recipe for soup.
Yield:
10 (2 cup) packages.

title: ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and orange segments.
In large bowl, combine pineapple, mandarin oranges, banana, grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts.
In 1-quart measure, combine sour cream or yogurt and brown sugar.
Stir into fruit mixture.
Refrigerate, covered, 1 hour or overnight.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix sugars, shortening, eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and buttermilk with baking soda. Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake 420 degrees for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Peel tomatoes and cut in quarters.
Place in saucepan and mash slightly to press out some juice.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add onion and butter.
Place alternate layers of tomatoes and crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt butter in baking dish and spread potatoes over butter. Mix onions with the soup and sour cream and spread over the potatoes.
Sprinkle cheese over top.
Crush potato chips or cornflakes and place over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate cupcakes
directions: Melt oleo and chocolate.
Put sugar, flour, eggs, nuts and vanilla flavoring in a bowl.
Add melted oleo and chocolate to this mixture.
Stir just enough to mix.
Bake at 350° for approximately 35 minutes.
Makes 18 cupcakes.

title: chili
directions: Chop onion.
Brown beef, onions and seasonings.
Drain fat. Add to hamburger mixture the water and tomatoes.
Add chili powder.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours until flavors are blended.
Stir frequently.

title: smoky venison burgers
directions: In a food processor, chop the venison and the bacon to medium fineness.
In a large bowl, mix the meat with the remaining ingredients.
Divide into 6 portions and form into patties while you prepare the grill.
When coals are ready, toss in four soaked wood chunks.
Position and fill the water pan.
Position the grate and arrange patties over water pan.
Cover grill, adjusting vent holes for outside temperature.
After a half hour, rotate and flip the burgers.
Cook 30 to 45 minutes longer, until desired doneness. Makes 6 servings.

title: favorite deviled eggs
directions: In a bowl, mix together first 7 ingredients until creamy. Form 1-inch balls.
Roll in cheese.
Cover and refrigerate until serving.

title: broiled chicken sandwiches
directions: Mix all the above ingredients except cheese and bread.
Pile on the buttered slices of bread, then sprinkle cheese on top. Broil 4 inches from broiler until cheese is bubbly, about 3 minutes.

title: crescent caramel swirl
directions: In a small saucepan, melt the margarine.
Coat bottom and sides of a 12 cup fluted pan with 2 tablespoons of the margarine. Sprinkle pan with 3 tablespoons of chopped nuts.
Add 3 tablespoons chopped nuts, brown sugar and water to butter in pan. Heat to boiling.
Remove rolls from cans.
Do not unroll.
Cut each section into four slices, separating each pinwheel slightly to allow sauce to penetrate.
Put slices from one can in the pan. Spoon half the sauce over dough.
Top with remaining slices, then rest of the sauce.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes, until golden brown.
Cool for 3 minutes.
Turn onto serving platter.

title: cheese balls
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl and mix with mixer. Mold and serve chilled.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients except for bacon.
Place in baking dish and lay strips of bacon over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bacon is done.

title: seafood-sausage-chicken gumbo
directions: Place cut up chicken in a pot; add salt and pepper.
Boil for 30 to 40 minutes.
Wash and clean shrimp.
Chop onions and celery. Cut sausage into small pieces.
If sauce is not precooked, cook in small skillet until done.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Cook meat in oil with green pepper and onion in a skillet until red color leaves meat, stirring continuously.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well to blend.
Cover tightly and simmer for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir often to prevent sticking.
Makes enough for 10 to 12 servings and freezes well.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Blend the cranberries and lemon juice with a fork.
In a separate bowl, mix together the confectioners sugar, pineapple, mayonnaise and pecans.
Mix both together and place in the dish you will freeze in.
Spread whipped topping on top and freeze.
Remove from freezer 15 minutes before use.
Doubles easily.

title: squash dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and sugar.
Layer first 5 ingredients and top with mayonnaise mixture.
Top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Do not mix until ready to serve.

title: macaroni-cheese-ham casserole
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions for 5 minutes; drain well.
Combine egg, milk, dry mustard, pepper and paprika in a lightly greased (with margarine) 2-quart casserole dish.
Layer macaroni, ham and cheese.
Repeat.
Mix melted margarine and bread crumbs; sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until top is brown.

title: clam pie(a hot dip)
directions: Simmer together the butter, green pepper, onion, parsley and oregano for 15 minutes; mix all together.
I use a skillet that goes in the oven which also looks nice to serve in.
Sprinkle to cover with either American, Cheddar or Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender.
Drain.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine next 7 ingredients and spread over top.
Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Stir in crumbs. Spread over top.
Bake, uncovered, in a 375° oven for about 25 minutes until browned and hot.
Serves 6.

title: venison steaks
directions: Combine vinegar, water, onions and spices and boil briefly. Pour hot over the meat and let stand in the refrigerator for several days.
To cook the meat, sear both sides in the butter. Reduce heat and turn the meat often.
Allow 12 minutes per pound for rare or up to 30 minutes for well done.
(Do not cook or use high heat as venison tends to cook dry easily.)
Serve with currant or wild plum jelly.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients, 1/3 at a time alternately with the water.
Add nuts and beat thoroughly.
Bake in well-greased bread pans or loaf pans.
Will make 3 bread loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corned beef and tomato scramble
directions: Break up corned beef and brown in shortening.
Stir in soup, pickles and seasonings.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.
Yields 6 portions.

title: overnight pecan rolls
directions: Put pecans in greased Bundt pan.
Place frozen rolls on pecans. Mix pudding, sugar and melted margarine; pour over rolls. Cover with waxed paper and towel.
Let rise overnight.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Let set for few minutes, then invert onto plate.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Alternately place asparagus, peas, mushroom soup, mushrooms and cheese in casserole dish, ending with a layer of cheese on top.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dry chops.
Dip in egg and coat with crumbs.
Gently saute in oil or hot fat.
In saucepan combine remaining ingredients except corn flakes.
Heat almost to a boil. Pour some sauce in baking dish.
Put chops in dish and cover with remaining sauce.
Bake covered for 1 hour.
Remove cover.
Top with corn flakes.
Spoon sauce over all.
Bake uncovered approximately 15 minutes.

title: mint jellies
directions: Chop mint fine and leave in about a week to allow flavors to blend. Rewarm and strain herb leaves out. Recipe or use immediately.

title: corn casserole
directions: Fry bacon;
drain and crumble, reserving drippings.
In bacon drippings,
saute
green peppers, onion and celery until tender. Combine sauteed vegetables and bacon, eggs, evaporated milk, corn, green chilies and corn bread mix.
Add salt and pepper to taste. Melt
margarine
in
bottom
of
9 x 13-inch casserole.
Add corn mixture
and
bake
at
350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease an 11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch casserole.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Mix macaroni, onion, sweet pepper, carrot and bacon bits.
Mix mayonnaise and Ranch dressing together, then put all together.
Make a large amount or a small amount, whatever.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Peel the green outer rind from the watermelon.
Some, but very little of the pink should be left.
In a pan, cover rind with cold water and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer until rind is tender enough to pierce with fork easily.

title: glazed walnuts
directions: Bake walnuts in 375° oven for 10 minutes.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, water, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Turn off heat; add vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Mix well.
Quickly drop on waxed paper with a slotted spoon.
Separate nuts with a fork.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Put shortening, sugar and raisins in hot applesauce.
When cool, add spices, flour and soda. Mix, then add nuts. Bake in
8 x 8 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: pinwheel tea sandwiches
directions: Spread bread with marmalade.
Roll slices and secure with toothpicks.
Toast under broiler, turn to brown both sides evenly. Remove toothpicks, serve warm.

title: heavenly delight
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions in 9 x 13 inch cake pan. Put pineapple with juice on top of cake. Slice bananas and layer on top of pineapple. Drizzle Hershey's syrup on top of bananas. cover entire top and sides with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle cake with pecan pieces. Decorate top with cherries.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Rinse
peas
and
combine
with
cups water in large saucepan;
bring
to boil.	Boil for 2 minutes and remove from heat letting stand for 1 hour.
Drain, reserving 6 cups of the cooking
liquid.
In
a
heavy
3-quart
saucepan, cook bacon, onion
and garlic until bacon is crisp and onion is tender but not brown.
Remove bacon and drain on paper towel.
Set aside while stirring peas into mixture in saucepan.
Bring to boil, cover
and reduce heat.
Simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Stir in crumbled bacon.
Serve immediately.

title: rocky road frosting
directions: Melt chocolate over hot boiling water.
Combine butter, sugar, milk and vanilla; beat in egg.
Add chocolate, stirring until blended.
Stir in walnuts and marshmallows.
Yields icing for 2 (8 or 9-inch) cakes.

title: microwave self-icing chocolate cake
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into microwave-safe Bundt pan.
Bake on High for 11 to 14 minutes.
Allow cake to cool for 5 to 10 minutes before inverting onto serving plate.
Spread any chips on top, or you can sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in water and let cool; When cool add half of the rest of ingredients to 9x13 pan and refrigerate till set. Spread 1 c. sour cream on top mixture, spread remaining half on top of sour cream. Refrigerate until firm.

title: pumpkin custard
directions: Mix pumpkin with eggs, sugar, salt and spices.
Stir in milk. Pour into custard cups.
Set cups in shallow pan of hot water to 2/3 of sides.
Bake at 225° for 45 minutes to 1 hour or until firm.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix flour, oats, baking soda, cinnamon and salt in bowl. Beat butter, sugar and brown sugar in a large bowl until fluffy. Add pumpkin, eggs and extract; mix well. Gradually add flour mixture. Add nuts and raisins. Drop 1/4 cup dough onto greased baking sheet. Spread into 3-inch circle. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 14 to 16 minutes until firm and lightly browned. Cool on baking sheets for 2 minutes.
Remove to wire racks.
Decorate with icing as desired. Makes 40 large cookies.

title: prize winning meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Press firmly into ungreased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni until tender.
Mix with Miracle Whip dressing, eggs, green peppers, some pimento for color (optional), salt and Cheddar cheese cubes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Dissolve the soda in water and set aside.
Mix oil, sugar and eggs.
Mix well and add pumpkin.
Continue to mix and add soda water.
Add dry ingredients.
Add cherries and walnuts (optional). Divide into 3 loaf pans, greased and floured.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Layer Doritos (crushed or whole) in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chicken on top.
Mix cream of celery, chicken, mushroom and Ro-Tel in a pan on medium heat. Pour over top of chicken.
Top with Velveeta and cook until cheese is melted.

title: pistachio nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Pour into a greased tube or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Any type squash or combination will do; cook squash and onion in bouillon water until tender.
Use just enough water to cover squash well.
When tender, add butter, crackers and cheese.
Stir together well and season to taste.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini in water approximately 5 minutes.
Use 1/2 to 3/4 stuffing mix with all ingredients.
Pour in pan.
Top with rest of stuffing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mustard ring
directions: Soak the gelatine in 1 tablespoon cold water in top of a double boiler.
Dissolve in boiling water.
Mix sugar, salt and mustard together to remove lumps in mustard. Add vinegar.

Add to this mixture the beaten egg, then mix with gelatine and water. Cook in double boiler until thick (about like boiled custard). Remove from fire. Cool. When cool, but not set, fold in whipping cream.
Put in ring mold and chill.
Can put cole slaw in center, if desired.
Serves 12.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare mix as directed on back of box and add 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring and frozen coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Punch holes all over top of cake with a toothpick.
Heat the following ingredients together and pour over hot cake: milk, sugar, 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring and enough water to make 2 cups.
Let cake cool.
Ice with 9 ounces of Cool Whip and sprinkle with 9 ounces of fresh frozen coconut on top.

title: janitor jim's goulash
directions: Put macaroni (or seashells) in a saucepan.
Add water 1 to 2 inches above macaroni.
Add butter and 1 tablespoon salt; bring to a rolling boil.
Let macaroni sit in this water solution, covered, off of the heat for 20 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all seasonings.
Add to other ingredients.
Put in greased bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: patsy's blueberry delight
directions: Whip the milk and Dream Whip until stiff.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar. Fold these two mixtures together.
Fold this into angel food cake.
Mix blueberries and pie filling.
Layer in trifle bowl in this order: cake, blueberries, cake, blueberries. May be made with strawberries also.

title: confederate stew
directions: Cut carrots in small circles and boil while preparing apples. Peel and slice apples.
Drain carrots and combine with apples. Mix in sugar, cinnamon, and nutmeg.
Mix well, and beef.
Cook in a Crock Pot 5-6 hours on high, serves 4.
YUM-YUM

title: candied fruit cake
directions: Mix the flour, baking powder and salt in a very large bowl. Mix the dates and cherries into the flour mixture and mix until well coated.
Beat the eggs until frothy and slowly add the sugar. Pour on the fruit and mix well.
Add the pecan halves with hands and pack into 3 bread pans that are well greased or make 8 little loaves.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 275°.

title: egg rolls
directions: Put 1 tablespoon oil in skillet; heat to medium-high heat. Cook meat on medium-high for a few minutes.
Add onion, green pepper and Oriental vegetables to meat in skillet after the meat has cooked about 4 minutes.
Stir often.
Add soy sauce.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients for 1 minute.
Take off burner; add oatmeal, peanut butter and vanilla.
Drop by tablespoon on aluminum foil.

title: charlotte's apple butter
directions: Put pulp in crock-pot (5 quart) with sugar and spices.
Cook on high for 8 hours without lid.
Stir occasionally.
Put in jelly jars and seal.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Thaw shrimp soup and soften cream cheese.
Add lemon juice, garlic powder, dash of paprika and soup.
Do not overbeat (makes dip thin).
Chill.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Lightly brown meat in 1/4 cup olive oil; add onions, pepper and garlic.
Mix sauce, paste and juice in large saucepan; add meat and rinse skillet with bouillon and add to mixture.
Add celery (whole) and remove when ready to serve.
Cook slowly about 3 hours.
Add mushroom pieces 30 minutes before serving.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Bake pie crust for 10 minutes.
Prick crust in the bottom with a fork and bake another 10 minutes.

title: szechwan hot and sour soup
directions: * Mix 1 Tbsp. minced garlic, 1 Tbsp. chili powder, 1 Tbsp. oil, white and cayenne pepper.

title: crab muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on English muffins.
Place on cookie sheet under broiler until lightly brown.
Cut into quarters and serve.

title: best doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs and sugar until light.
Add milk and cooled shortening.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth. Chill.
Roll 3/8 inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut with floured cutter.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Fry in hot deep fat (375 degrees) until brown, turning once.
Drain.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: mango relish
directions: Wash and grind peppers and onion with a food grinder.
Add 1/2 cup of salt and cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes; drain and squeeze out all liquid.
Cover again with boiling water and let stand 10 minutes; squeeze out all liquid.
Heat vinegar, sugar and spices to rolling boil.
Add vegetables to boiling mixture and cook for 20 minutes.
Place hot mixture in jars and seal.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix well and bake at 350° until done.

title: jello mold
directions: Mix altogether with the Jell-O.
Put half of the mixture into 2 bowls and put in the refrigerator until Jell-O is set, about 1 1/2 hours.
Take out of the refrigerator and spread the sour cream over the Jell-O mixture.
Add the rest of the mixture on top and return to fridge.

title: quick - easy cobbler
directions: Combine fresh peaches and 3/4 cup sugar; let stand for 20 minutes, or you can use a can of peaches, but drain them a little. Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart (or larger) baking dish in a 350° oven.
Sift together remaining sugar, flour and baking powder and add milk.
Stir briskly.
Lumps will remain.
Pour into baking dish of melted butter.
Top with peaches.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Beat brown sugar, white sugar, oil and eggs together.
Sift flour, baking soda and baking powder together.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 10 or 12 minutes.

title: lemon bars
directions: Sift together 2 cups of flour and confectioners sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture clings together.
Press into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: egg custard(makes crust)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and flour.
Add milk, vanilla, melted butter and coconut (if desired).
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: steak teriyaki
directions: Combine ingredients in blender.
Marinate meat in closed container for 24 hours.
Turn meat several times.
Cook on grill until done.

title: french fried onion rings
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in a little water until just tender; peel and slice.
Toss gently with pitted prunes, orange marmalade and softened butter or margarine.
Season with lemon juice and pepper. Cover; heat in oven or microwave.

title: italian chicken
directions: In a large skillet, brown chicken on all sides in oil Add celery, garlic and parsley.
Cook 2 minutes and stir.
Add salt, bay leaf and wine.
Cover and simmer until chicken is tender, about 40 minutes.
If desired, thicken sauce with 1 tablespoon of flour that has been blended with 1 tablespoon of water.
Serves 4.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butterscotch almond bark on low heat.
Add peanut butter.
Pour over remaining ingredients.
Cool on wax paper; ready to eat.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti and rinse.
Place spaghetti in a large bowl and sprinkle with salad seasoning.
Pour Italian dressing over spaghetti.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
This makes a large bowl of salad.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Combine first 5 items.
Cook until custard.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream and stiffly beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle half of crumbs in pan.
Add filling, then rest of crumbs.
Refrigerate for several hours.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown meat in frypan and drain excess fat. Add tomatoes, green peppers, onion, rice, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally. Cover with grated cheese before serving and while still hot.
Can be reheated.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package.
Combine beef, macaroni, soup and milk in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Add chips after removing from oven.

title: kahlua
directions: Mix 6 cups of water with sugar.
Cook over low heat until dissolved.
Let cool.
Mix coffee with 4 cups water and simmer 2 minutes.
Don't boil.
Mix with first mixture.
Let cool.
Add vanilla and alcohol.
Bottle in brown bottles.
Store in cool place.

title: banana split cake
directions: Crush graham crackers in dish.
Pour pineapple and juice over crackers.
Slice bananas over this.
Mix sugar-free instant jello pudding and pour over.
Put whipped topping on top.

title: golden cheese chowder
directions: Bring water to boil in kettle. Add potatoes, celery, carrots, onion, salt and pepper. Cover and simmer 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Melt butter in large saucepan. Blend in flour. Stir in milk gradually. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to boil. Boil 1 minute, then stir in Cheddar until melted. Add to vegetables. Heat, but do not boil. Can add 2 cups cubed cooked ham and hot pepper sauce to taste. Tabasco works well.

title: cooked venison
directions: In skillet, brown venison with sliced onion and bell pepper. Add water (not oil or grease).
Brown meat, onion and pepper in covered skillet until all water is evaporated.
Seasoned salt to taste.
Dump mixture into crock-pot.
Pour in 2 to 4 cans of beefy mushroom soup, brown gravy mix and 1 cup water and cover crock-pot.
Cook on medium about 4 hours, stirring occasionally. Use cornstarch to thicken if needed.

title: chicken tortilla casserole
directions: Cook chicken; cut in large pieces.
Mix soups, broth, onion and chile pepper.
(Rinse and take seeds out of pepper.)
Dice. Butter a large 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Pour in a small amount (1/3 cup or more).
Make a layer of tortilla squares, chicken, then soup and broth mixture.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese. Repeat layers, ending with soup mixture.
Top with Cheddar cheese. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mandarin orange molded salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Chill until thickened but not set.
Fold in whipped topping and orange segments. Pour into lightly oiled 1-quart mold.
Chill until firm. Unmold.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: mushrooms ala king
directions: Slice mushrooms to desired size. Add to melted butter in a large frying pan and cook slowly to desired consistency.
As the mushrooms cook, mix the flour with sour cream.
When mushrooms are practically done, add the sour cream and flour mixture. Stir until sauce starts to thicken. Add salt and very little pepper.
A few drops of fresh lemon juice may be added.
"Voila!
Mushrooms ala King!"

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice one gallon cucumbers and 8 onions, let stand in salt water for 3 hours.
Put one tray of ice over them and let stand until all the ice is melted.
Put in saucepan and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
Use wooden spoon for stirring.
Put in jars and turn upside down.
Makes 11 pints.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until crisp-tender. Saute onions in 3 tablespoons butter until tender. Stir in soup, salt, pepper and cheese. Drain carrots. Add to the onion mixture. Pour into a greased baking dish. Sprinkle with croutons. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: blackberry wine cake
directions: Mix all.
Cook in greased Bundt pan at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: cheddar cheese biscuits
directions: 1. Preheat oven 400°. 2. Combine the first six ingredients in processor and blend.
Add butter and using on/off turns until meal forms. 3. Transfer to large bowl.
Mix in cheese.
(This can be prepared 4 hours ahead.
Cover and chil). 4. Mix enough butermilk into flour mixture to bind dough.
Turn out unto floured surface and knead until combined (about 10 minutes). 5. Pat out dough to 3/4-inch thickness.
Using 3-inch diameter cookie cutter cut out biscuits.
Gather scraps and pat out 3/4-inch thickness and cut out additional biscuits. 6. Transfer biscuits to ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush biscuits with egg glaze and sprinkle with poppy seeds. 7. Bake at 400° until golden brown and firm to the touch about 18 minutes.
Makes about 10.

title: egg salad sandwiches
directions: Mix together and add mayonnaise to make a spreading consistency.
Pickle relish may be added if desired.
Yields 6 sandwiches.

title: our favorite meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Combine tomato sauce, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard in a small bowl.
Set aside.
Combine egg, onion, cracker crumbs, ground beef, salt and pepper in a mixing bowl.
Add 1/2 of the tomato mixture and blend thoroughly.
Shape into an oval loaf and place in a microwave-safe oblong dish.
Make a depression in top of loaf.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over top of meat.
Cook, uncovered, for 18 to 20 minutes or until center of loaf is cooked. Cover meat and let stand about 10 minutes before serving.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Add all ingredients except mayonnaise.
Mix good with hands. Add mayonnaise.
Taste and cover.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: frozen corn
directions: Mix corn, sugar, salt and butter. Cover with water and bring to boil. Stir well. Cool completely and put in freezer bags and freeze.

title: lentil soup(fahki)
directions: Prick lamb; salt and pepper well all over.
Spike about 10 garlic buds into lamb.
Sprinkle all over with lemon juice. Marinate overnight.
Next day, cook uncovered until browned. Then, add a little water to make gravy.
Also, place peeled potatoes that have been cut into large chunks down in pan with lamb.
Baste with some of the juice.
Cover and cook until tender.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: wiener gravy
