directions: Lightly brown flour with onions in oil; do not burn onions. Add all the liquids, salt, pepper to taste plus 1 teaspoon sugar. Add sliced wieners.
Cook over low heat for about 45 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: low-fat turkey gumbo
directions: Put cornstarch to brown in a pan in 350° oven.
Stir occasionally until brown. In a large pot sprayed with Pam, put onions and celery.
Cook at medium-high until they become brown, then add browned cornstarch.
Blend well in pot, then add the rest.
Bring to a boil and then turn heat down.
Cover and cook about 15 to 30 minutes.
Serve over rice, sprinkled with 1/4 teaspoon file gumbo to each dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Cook raw rice as usual.
Meanwhile in large skillet, saute onion in butter.
Add cheese and soup to onion.
Stir until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli and cook 8 more minutes.
Add cooked rice and pour into casserole.
Use a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: easy divinity
directions: Mix sugar and water; bring to boil.
Hard boil for 2 minutes (high heat).
Take off heat; add marshmallow cream.
Add nuts. Working fast, spoon onto wax paper; let cool.

title: popsicles
directions: Stir boiling water into jello and Kool-Aid until dissolved. Add cold water and stir well.
Cool slightly before freezing.
Pour into plastic cups, insert popsicle sticks and freeze until hard.

title: janice's pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour; add corn syrup, eggs and margarine. Beat well.
Stir in vanilla and pecans.
Pour into pastry shell. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: pastor's lasagne
directions: Broil bacon until crisp.
Drain and let cool.
Boil noodles until tender; drain and let cool.
Brown hamburger with onion, celery, salt and 1/2 teaspoon oregano.
Mix remaining oregano, pepper and garlic powder with Ragu and catsup.
(If mixture doesn't look like enough, add 1 small can tomato paste, thinned according to directions.)
Heat enough to blend; mix with hamburger.
Cook in pan suitable for serving.
(If you use an old biscuit pan, cover the outside with aluminum foil before you put it on the table.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 of meat.
Shape into ball. Cover with remaining meat.
Serve with crackers.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place cracker crumbs
in
bottom
of greased casserole. Layer remaining ingredients
in
order given, with pimento cut and scattered on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350°, covered, for 45 minutes.

title: carrot ambrosia salad
directions: Combine all ingredients well.
Chill for several hours.
Good holiday salad.

title: cinnamon roll-ups
directions: Make a light brown mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Cream together butter, cream cheese, egg yolks and 1/2 cup sugar. Spread creamed mixture on bread and roll up.
Brush with butter and roll in cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Freeze! Bake for 15 minutes in a 400° preheated oven.
Do not thaw before baking. Serve warm.
Yields 48 roll-ups.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.
May be left in pan.
Really stays fresh and moist.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: banana smoothie
directions: Combine all ingredients in a blender and serve.
This is also great for breakfast or an after school treat.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl except melted butter. Pour the melted butter into a 9 x 13-inch pan, then put the hash brown mixture in the pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Salt and pepper to taste.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Blend in Crisco; mix milk, egg and vinegar last.
Roll in ball.
Can be used immediately or store in refrigerator in sealed bag for later.
Makes 1 cobbler and 2 pan pies.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put defrosted potatoes in dish and cover with 1/2 cup melted margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle pecans on bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix according to directions on the box. Pour batter over pecans.
Melt butter and add cream cheese, vanilla, and powdered sugar.
Blend until creamy and add coconut. Dab on top of cake mixture by spoonfuls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate mochi
directions: Place dry ingredients in mixing bowl.
Mix.
Melt margarine and chocolate.
Add milk, vanilla and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir into dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool, then serve.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and press in 9 x 13-inch loaf pan. Mix last 3 ingredients and pour over batter; bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp linguine(serves 6 to 8 people)
directions: Cook linguine al dente.
Rinse thoroughly with cold water; set aside.
In a medium saute pan, add butter, garlic and shrimp. Cook 1 minute or until shrimp are done, adding wine during cooking process.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together in bowl, beat for 7 minutes, mix 1/2 cup sugar and cinnamon and walnuts (optional).
Place 1/2 batter in tube pan, sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mix on top.
Add rest of batter, sprinkle little sugar mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: date balls
directions: Melt butter and sugar.
Mix in dates.
Cook up to 8 minutes. Take off fire.
Add vanilla, Rice Krispies and pecans.
Roll into balls, then roll in powdered sugar.

title: stir-fried chicken, green beans and peanuts
directions: Mix water, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar, vinegar and sesame seed oil in a measuring cup, until blended.
Heat oil.
Add peppers, onions and green beans.
Stir-fry 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken, peanuts and soy sauce.
Bring to boil.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease baking sheet with butter flavored Crisco.
Combine Crisco, light brown sugar, egg, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat until well blended.
Combine oats, flour, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix into creamed mixture slowly until well blended.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop rounded tablespoonfuls of dough 2 inches apart onto baking sheet.
bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool for 2 minutes on baking sheet.

title: decorator frosting
directions: In medium mixing bowl, cream shortening.
Add powdered sugar, vanilla and enough milk for decorating consistency.
Beat until smooth and well blended.
Thin with a few drops milk if necessary. Divide into small bowls, coloring as desired.
Makes about 3 cups frosting.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Put 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in small frypan.
Add diced chicken and fry until brown; stir continually.
Put 1 tablespoon vegetable oil in large frypan.
Add vegetables and sliced onions; stir continually until thoroughly warmed.
Add diced chicken to cooked vegetables.
Serve cooked vegetables over rice on individual plates.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Crumble up sausage and add to cheese.
Mix well.
Add flour all at once and work with hands; form into walnut size balls.
Freeze on baking sheet; remove and place in plastic freezer bags.
Remove as many as you want to bake, let thaw for 1 hour before baking on cookie sheet. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch pecan squares
directions: Mix together.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch square pan, 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Ice with a thin powdered sugar icing while warm.

title: kelly's favorite potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in large saucepan in water, or add 1 cube of chicken bouillon for added flavor.
Cook about 5 to 7 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread in flat casserole. Melt 1/4 cup margarine and toss with 1 cup corn flake crumbs or cracker crumbs. May also use potato chip crumbs.
Sprinkle over rice mixture and bake 25 minutes at 350° to 375°.
Can mix up night before and add crumbs right before baking.

title: pumpkin pie(servings:  16)
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Pour into pie pans and bake in 400° oven for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Put all ingredients together.
Cook as for cream or chocolate pie.
Cook in a heavy saucepan, stirring constantly, on low heat until it thickens.
Pour into 9-inch baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites stiff with 1/4 teaspoon vinegar.
Add 1/3 cup sugar to egg whites and swirl over filling, sealing meringue well to pastry. Bake in slow oven at 325° for 15 minutes, or until meringue is brown.

title: cranberry pie
directions: Mix cranberries and raisins.
Combine the sugar and flour and mix this with the fruit.
Add the water and lemon peel and place the filling in an unbaked pie shell.
Cover with the top crust and bake at 400° for about 45 minutes.

title: stewed apples
directions: Slice apples in pan with water.
Boil until tender.
Add Sugar Twin and cinnamon.
Can add diet butter.

title: citrus crown cake
directions: Grease and flour Bundt pan. Prepare cake according to package directions. Combine marmalade, coconut and margarine in a small mixing bowl; pour into Bundt pan. Pour prepared cake mix over marmalade mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Remove from pan immediately.

title: golden punch
directions: Reconstitute orange juice and lemonade as directed on cans. Combine in punch bowl with apricot nectar, pineapple juice and lemon juice.
Pour bottled carbonated beverages or ginger ale slowly down side of bowl.
Drop scoops of pineapple, orange, lime or raspberry sherbet into punch.
Makes about 3 1/2 quarts without sherbet.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Stir together peas, soup and cheese.
Put in a casserole bowl, arrange asparagus across top of mixture.
Add crackers and some grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes until bubbly, uncovered.

title: hot shrimp appetizers
directions: Meat butter and Cheez Whiz; add all other ingredients. Let cool. Spread on 12 halves of English muffins. Cut each half into quarters. Place on an ungreased cookie sheet and freeze. Pour into a freezer bag.

title: mexicali cheese-corn pudding
directions: In large bowl with fork or whisk, beat eggs until blended. Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes or until firm. Makes 4 servings.

title: lemon-yogurt salad dressing(or dip)
directions: In small serving bowl combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apple cobbler
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and mix into melted stick of butter or margarine.
Cover bottom and sides of pan with crust dough.
Put raw apples in pan and pour margarine or butter mix over apples.
Cover apples with remaining dough.
Bake in a preheated oven at 325°
for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix green beans, soup, pepper and milk in casserole dish.
Add 1/2 can of fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: mexi dip
directions: Brown hamburger or sausage in a skillet; drain.
Stir in the salsa; let meat simmer or "marinate" for 5 minutes.
Chop up the cheese; add to mixture.
Stir until melted and blended.
Serve while warm with chips.
Can reheat.
(This is a great dip; men love it!!)

title: chicken and corn pudding
directions: Brown chicken lightly in oil.
Add water, wine, broccoli and soup.
Bring to a full boil, separating broccoli pieces.
Stir in rice.
Cover, remove from heat and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cool & colorful salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions.
Do not overcook. Rinse with cold water.
As pasta cooks, cut up vegetables into bite size chunks.
Mix with pasta.
Add salad dressing and seasoning.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving.
Serves 6-8.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill at least 3 hours.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Boil the washed cabbage for 8 to 10 minutes or until the leaves become pliable.
Drain and carefully remove about 16 large leaves. Mix beef with sausage.
Add rice, minced onions and season well. Place one or two tablespoons of mixture on each cabbage leaf.
Fold the ends over meat and roll up the rest of the cabbage.
If necessary, pull off more leaves until the meat is used up.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cabbage rolls and place the sauerkraut and onions in casserole and add tomato paste. Top with bacon and bake uncovered 45 minutes in 300° oven.
If needed, add a little water.
Serve with sour cream.

title: shipwreck
directions: Layer in casserole with meat on bottom.
Cook 15 minutes at 400°, then 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: crock-pot cream of potato soup
directions: Potatoes should be scrubbed, peeled and diced into medium chunks.
Onion should also be peeled and chopped.
Put all ingredients into slow cooker and stir.
Turn pot to medium temperature (about 375°); cook for 7 to 8 hours.

title: chocolate sauce
directions: Bring whipping cream to a boil in sauce pan, on medium heat. Remove from heat and add chocolate morsels, margarine, sugar, and vanilla; stir until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth. Serve warm. Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine soft cream cheese and mayonnaise until creamy. Add all other ingredients and blend well. Chill. Before serving, hollow out the center of the loaf of bread in pieces.
Place pieces of bread around the loaf on platter.
Place dip in the hollowed out portion of bread.
Use pieces of the bread to dip into shrimp dip.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a bowl until well blended.
Add milk and continue mixing until a loaf shape can be made that will hold together.
Place in a loaf pan and top with bacon strip.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Beat 2
eggs
with
cup
milk.
Mix
flour and cocoa together;
mix
dry
ingredients
together, then add to liquid ingredients.
Pour in a 9-inch pie crust which you bake 3 to 5 minutes before adding filling.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: apple cider punch
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lime slices, in a punch bowl. Float the lime slices on top.
Serve over ice.
Serves 20 (4-ounce) cups.

title: swiss potato soup
directions: Saute onion in butter in soup pan.
Add 3 cups water and potatoes.
Cook until potatoes are tender.
With a hand potato masher, gently mash potatoes.
Add dry mustard, milk and Swiss cheese slices.
Cook on low heat until cheese is melted.

title: hot rolls
directions: Put water in a large bowl.
Sprinkle yeast on top and let dissolve.
Add sugar, salt and 1/2 cup flour.
Beat well for 2 minutes.
Add egg and oil and mix again.
Add remaining flour; mix all together well.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours before making rolls.
Push down everyday and keep covered with damp cloth.

title: suzie's super cocoa
directions: Put cocoa and sugar into saucepan.
Put in water and milk and stir until smooth.
Keep on low heat for 5 to 6 minutes.
Put marshmallows in each cup and pour cocoa into cup.

title: party hot dogs
directions: Cook on low heat about 45 minutes.

title: sausage and apple quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage over medium heat.
Drain; add apples and cook until barely tender.
Place in pie crust.
Mix liquid ingredients together and pour over sausage mixture.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until firm in the center.

title: ice cream crunch
directions: Melt margarine and mix together with pecans, oats, brown sugar and flour.
Spread on an ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 35 minutes, stirring often; cool.

title: cowboy potatoes
directions: Fry bacon and remove from pan.
In bacon grease, fry cubed potatoes, onion and pepper until tender.
Dice bacon and add to mixture.
Add seasoned salt and pepper.

title: citrus cider punch
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine all ingredients; mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Remove spices.
Serve hot in punch bowl or pitcher.
If desired, garnish with clove-studded orange slices.
Makes 26 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: stuffed green peppers
directions: Cut a thin slice from stem end of peppers.
Remove all seeds and membranes; wash insides and outsides.
Cook peppers in boiling water 5 minutes; drain.

title: macaroni puff
directions: Cook macaroni; pour milk over bread crumbs and cheese.
Add macaroni, egg yolks, pimento, oleo and onion.
Mix and fold in beaten egg whites with 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Bake 55 minutes at 325°.

title: seasoned salt
directions: Mix with fork and store in airtight container.

title: quick and easy candy
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave or double boiler on stove, then add cereal and peanuts and mix together.
Place mixture flat on wax paper and let dry.
After it dries, just break in little pieces and eat.
It's real good.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix pineapple and pudding mix well.
Add rest of ingredients and refrigerate overnight.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Mix well. Add buttermilk and yeast. Mix well.
Cover bowl and put in refrigerator.
Use as needed.
Dough will keep a week if kept refrigerated.

title: good salad dressing for potato salad
directions: Mix all together and put in jar and keep in refrigerator and it will keep for weeks. Use as needed.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in the order given.
Mix thoroughly. Prepare a loaf pan by oiling thoroughly, then coating with cracker crumbs.
Fill with chicken mixture.
Set pan in a pan containing about 2 inches of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until a knife inserted comes out clean.
Serve hot with olive sauce or cold with Hollandaise sauce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: wine stew
directions: Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
Sprinkle the meat with garlic salt and Accent.
Combine the soup, onion, wine and mushrooms. Stir into meat.
Pour into casserole baking dish.
Bake for about 2 1/2 hours or until the meat is nice and tender at 325°.
Serve over noodles.

title: nan's sugar cookies(christmas cookies)
directions: Cream together sugar, brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Chill batter.
Roll out dough and cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen.

title: tuna pate
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve on crackers.

title: sicilian salad
directions: Make dressing:
In jar with lid, combine oil, vinegar, garlic, salt, pepper, basil, oregano and parsley.
Shake well to combine. Refrigerate to chill well and to blend flavors.
Remove and discard garlic.

title: trail mix
directions: Mix together.
Store in an airtight container.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix together the pudding and buttermilk.
Fold all ingredients together.
Refrigerate. Yummy!

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and pulp sweet potatoes.
Mix with next 7 ingredients. Spoon mixture into pastry prepared cake pan.
With electric mixer, blend next 5 ingredients.
Beat until smooth and syrupy.
Stir in pecans.
Pour this mixture atop sweet potato mixture.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours until a knife inserted in middle comes out clean.
Serve with whipped cream.
Serves 12.

title: norwegian meat balls
directions: In a large bowl, mix milk and 1/4 cup of the cornstarch until well blended.
Add meat, onion, salt, nutmeg, pepper and egg; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate for 20 minutes, then shape into 1-inch balls.
In skillet over medium heat, heat oil until hot.
Cook meat balls, 1/2 at a time, until browned (8 to 10 minutes).
Remove and drain on paper towels.
Pour off all but 1/4 of the drippings, adding oil if needed to make 1/4 cup.

title: caramel apple salad
directions: Wash and chop Apples with skin left on. Chop candy bars. In large bowl, add apples and candy; Mix in cool whip. Better if made couple of hours before serving.

title: the inabinets' lime pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake in 400° oven until it browns.

title: seven-bone roast
directions: Mix flour,
salt
and pepper together.	Coat roast with this mix.
Put a
rack
in the bottom of a 12-inch Dutch oven. Put in bay leaves and sugar and pour in the broth.
Place meat on rack. Sprinkle any
leftover flour mix on top of the roast and spread catsup
over
this.
Bake
2 1/2 hours at low heat (300°).

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add sifted flour and salt; stir until combined.
Add vanilla. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan for ten minutes, then cool on rack.

title: hamburger patties
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients. (Best if mixed with hands).
Patty out hamburgers.
Grill patties.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together butter, eggs and sugar.
Add bananas (mashed). Mix well and add flour, soda and walnuts (optional).
Put in greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 large loaves or 3 medium-size.

title: burrito hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger.
Add refried beans and mix.
In another pan, mix soup, chili, peppers and hot sauce; heat.
Take 1/2 cup of this gravy and add to the hamburger mixture.
Fill flour tortillas with meat and bean mixture. Add cheese to each one and roll up. Put in casserole.
Pour rest of gravy over the top of all. Add cheese to the top and heat until it melts.
Bake at 350°.

title: peg's pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta spirals.
Drain, rinse and cool.
Add to pasta the cherry tomatoes, Monterey Jack cheese, cucumber, bell pepper and Parmesan cheese.
Pour Italian dressing (Wish-Bone is good) over salad, enough to moisten.
Chill and serve.

title: baked corn
directions: Grease (margarine) a baking dish.
Pour in can of cream-style corn.
Add butter, cornstarch and sugar.
Stir together.
Separate egg yolks and whites and beat.
Add to the foregoing mixture the separated, beaten yolks and then the milk, stirring for smooth mixture.
Fold in the beaten egg whites and sprinkle black pepper on top, if desired.
Salt may be omitted or used according to cook's wisdom.

title: microwave no-bake peanut butter cookies
directions: In medium glass bowl, blend sugar and syrup.
Microwave on High 2 1/2 to 3 minutes (full boil).
Stir in cereal and peanut butter.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper or shape into balls. Makes 36.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Beat or blend pudding, eggs, Pet milk, sugar, salt and vanilla about 5 minutes.
Add milk.
In skillet, brown margarine and chopped pecans.
Add to other mixture.
Freeze.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: napolean cream bars
directions: Combine 1/2 cup butter, sugar, cocoa and vanilla in top of double boiler. Cook over boiling water until butter melts. Stir in beaten eggs. Continue to stir until mixture is thick, about 3 minutes. Blend in crumbs and coconut. Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: hot apple and cranberry punch(serves 10)
directions: Combine apple juice, cranberry juice, cinnamon sticks and brown sugar in saucepan.
Heat to serving temperature.
Ladle into mugs.

title: onion rings and fritter batter
directions: Place first 5 ingredients in a bowl and mix well.
Allow batter to rest, covered, and refrigerate for 3 hours to 3 days. Just before using, add 2 stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: no bird dressing
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: banana-nut bread
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking soda in measuring cup.
In mixing bowl, beat eggs, butter and sugar.
Add bananas.
Beat, then add flour and milk and beat.
Then add chopped nuts.
Pour into loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit fritters
directions: Drop by tablespoons into deep oil and fry until browned well.

title: prune cake
directions: Read all directions before starting!!

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix together macaroni, celery, green pepper, spring onion, sweet pickle, eggs and other 4 listed ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Dip cabbage leaves in hot water. Combine ground beef, salt, pepper, oats and milk. Mix well. Place a small amount of meat mixture into a cabbage leaf and roll up. Place oil in a large pan and place cabbage rolls in pan. Mix tomato soup, brown sugar and water. Pour over cabbage rolls and cook until meat is done and cabbage is tender.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut French bread into medium size slices and layer them in the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Brown sausage and drain excess grease.
Beat eggs and add milk and mix.
Fold in mushrooms. Pour 1/2 egg mixture over bread.
Spoon 1/2 sausage on top of this, then sprinkle cheese.
Sprinkle crumbed bacon over this.
Layer again in same order.
Let sit overnight or at least 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator so that the bread soaks up the egg mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Boil spaghetti and drain.
Brown hamburger and drain grease. Mix hamburger and spaghetti sauce.
Layer half of spaghetti, half of sauce, half of Cheddar cheese and half of Mozzarella cheese. Repeat.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce and seasoning mix; simmer for 5 minutes.
Unroll crescent rolls.
Press onto bottom and sides of ungreased 12-inch pizza pan.
Prick dough with fork. Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Remove from oven.
Cover crust with meat mixture; top with cheese. Return to oven; bake until cheese is melted.
Top with remaining ingredients.
Serve with sour cream.

title: chili dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and heat.
Add jalapeno peppers to taste. Serve with Doritos or tostados.

title: easy chili con carne skillet
directions: In skillet, brown beef and cook onion until tender; drain and add chili powder.
Add soup and beans.
Cook over low heat 10 minutes; stir occasionally.
Serve with fried eggs, if desired.

title: steam pudding
directions: Put in a mold or pan and steam for 2 hours.

title: barbecued beef for a crowd
directions: Brown ground beef, onions, green peppers and celery until onions are transparent.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook for 1 hour or more at low temperature.
Serve on split hamburger buns. Serves 50.

title: guava and ginger marmalade
directions: Add
cup
sugar to the sliced guavas and set aside for 10 to 20 minutes.
After the 20 minutes have passed, pour the guava
paste and slices into a large pot.
Add the ground ginger and
bring to a boil.
Add the sugar and the Sure Jell. Turn heat off.
Pour into pint jars.	Makes about 6 pints.

title: sugar-free coleslaw
directions: Combine coleslaw mix, onions, celery and garlic in bowl. Combine remaining ingredients except raisins and pour over vegetables; toss well.
Stir in raisins.
Chill several hours before serving.
Yields 4 cups.
Contains 41 calories per serving.

title: ruby red punch
directions: Place all ingredients in a gallon container.
Fill with water.
Mix well. Pour into a punch bowl.
Add bottle of 7-Up or Sprite.

title: chocolate toffee bars
directions: Cream brown sugar, oleo, shortening, egg and vanilla.
Add 2 c. flour.
Put in ungreased 10 x 15 pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15-20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips over. Bake 2-3 minutes.
Spread melted chocolate chips evenly over top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: five minute cake
directions: Use your own favorite icing.

title: hot dungeness crab appetizer
directions: Chop artichoke hearts into 1/4-inch pieces; drain well.
Drain crab well.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in an oven-safe, shallow baking dish.
Heat in a 350° oven for 6 to 8 minutes or until internal temperature is 140°.
Garnish with minced parsley.
Serve with assorted breads.

title: stella d'oro cream puffs
directions: Slice top off Anginetti; hold aside.
Drain crushed pineapple leaving a little juice.
Mix whipped topping and cream cheese together in a bowl about 1 minute at medium speed.
Add crushed pineapple and blend for about 1 minute at low speed.
Drop filling from tablespoon onto bottom layers of cookies; replace tops. Refrigerate puffs until ready to serve.

title: hot rolls
directions: Put yeast, shortening and sugar in a large bowl.
Heat milk to lukewarm.
Pour over ingredients in bowl.
Beat well; add 2 cups flour and mix.
Add eggs and mix.
Stir in remaining flour.
Knead on a floured board.
Place in a large bowl.
After it rises, punch down.
Let rise a second time, then make into rolls or loaves. Let rise.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheesy cauliflower soup
directions: In a saucepan, cook the cauliflower and carrots in water until tender; set aside (do not drain).
In a skillet over medium heat, brown the onion in butter. Add flour, salt and pepper. Gradually add the milk; bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Add cauliflower and carrots with cooking liquid; heat through.
Stir in the cheese until melted.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers thin. Add onions, peppers, garlic and salt. Mix. Cover with ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Drain.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cucumbers.
Heat to boil. Seal in pint jars.

title: hot mustard
directions: Mix equal amounts of dry mustard and brown sugar until smooth. Slowly add beer until you get mustard medium thick.
Very hot.
Use on beef or ham, etc.

title: grilled trout
directions: Rinse and pat dry each whole trout.
Salt and pepper each cavity of trout and stuff with 1 tablespoon butter, 1 tablespoon onion and 1 slice of lemon.
Wrap each trout with 2 or 3 slices bacon in aluminum foil.
Place on grill 3 to 4-inches above coals. Cook 10 minutes per side or until bacon is crisp and trout flakes easily in thickest part of flesh.
Don't overcook.
Serve immediately.

title: cheese fondue
directions: Slightly beat egg yolks.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold egg yolks and egg whites into cheese mixture.
Bake in a greased casserole for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: spiced sweet potatoes with apples and raisins
directions: In a small bowl let the raisins soak in water combined with Grand Marnier for 20 minutes.
In a steamer basket set over simmering water, steam the sweet potatoes, covered, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until they are just tender.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown sausage and pour off grease.
Add cubed Velveeta cheese and heat until cheese is melted.
Add salsa and heat through.
May keep dip in a crock-pot to maintain heat.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: broccoli and shrimp casserole
directions: Chop onion, pepper and celery.
Saute in butter until tender. Add soup, cheese, broccoli, rice, half and half and shrimp.
Pour in casserole.
Cover.
Cook in microwave for 25 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake for 15 minutes at 400° followed for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: spinach dip
directions: Allow spinach to thaw, then rinse.
Add remaining ingredients. Serve with broken French bread or chips.
Hollow out a large loaf of sourdough or French bread; put dip inside.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove skin and bones.
Cut in small pieces.
Place in buttered 3-quart casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Crumble chips and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Soak Doritos in 2 cups chicken broth. Place on bottom of sprayed 9 x 13 dish. Mix soups, then stir chicken in. Spread on Doritos. Spread relish on chicken mixture. Sprinkle cheese on relish. Sprinkle chili powder on top. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple and cranberry casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in a large baking dish. Cover with topping and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Use as side dish or top with ice cream for dessert.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix together and make into balls.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Put in a slow cooker.
Cover with sauce.

title: squash casserole
directions: Combine squash, water and salt in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer 10 minutes or until squash is tender.
Drain well and set aside.

title: creamed chicken tacos
directions: Mix soup, chilies, chicken and bacon.
Layer pan with Doritos and cream mixture and so on until mixture is gone.
Top with cheese.
Heat until cheese is melted and bubbly at 350°.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Bring to a boil.
Brown vermicelli and rice in butter.
Add water and cook over low heat until water is absorbed, about 25 minutes.

title: burrito roll-ups
directions: Mix ingredients together; refrigerate overnight.
Spread mixture on burritos, roll up and refrigerate again for approximately 4 hours.
Slice 1-inch thick; dip in salsa.

title: barbecued bacon-shrimp skewers
directions: Peel and devein shrimp, leaving tails intact.
Butterfly (cut halfway through along outside curve).
Place in medium bowl; add Cajun seasoning.
Toss to coat.
Add barbecue sauce; stir to coat. Let sit 30 minutes.

title: red delicious meatballs
directions: Combine ingredients; mix well.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs and fry 5 to 10 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Place meatballs in 14 x 12 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Mix at low speed the cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add 1 cup Cool Whip; spread on cooled crust.
Mix chocolate and vanilla pudding.
Add milk and vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Spread over cream cheese.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and nuts.

title: brownies
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Pour into a greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown onion, garlic and ground beef, stirring until crumbly and drain off fat.
Add spaghetti sauce mix and tomato sauce; mix well and simmer for 20 minutes.
Alternate layers of noodles, cheese and ground beef in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle top with extra Mozzarella cheese and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix well and blend all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Use ungreased tube or Bundt pan.
Cool upside down.

title: lemon bars
directions: Mix flour, butter and confectioners sugar.
Press lightly into greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Mix granulated sugar, eggs, flour, baking powder and lemon juice; blend well.
Bake 25 minutes or until firm.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar until top is covered, while warm.
Cut into bars and remove from pan.

title: vegetable-salmon pasta salad
directions: Cook broccoli in large saucepan of boiling water until crisp-tender and green, 2 to 3 minutes.
Remove with slotted spoon.
Add pasta to same water and cook until tender, 15 minutes. Drain.
Rinse in cold water, drain again and pour into a large serving bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Do not refrigerate.
Serve pasta salad immediately.
Serves 8.

title: cuban beef with rice(serving size:  6)
directions: Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Brown in frying pan.
Add remaining ingredients except olives.
Cover and simmer 2 hours, or until meat is tender.
Can use pressure cooker for 12 minutes instead.
Uncover.
Simmer until nearly all liquid evaporates. Stir in sliced olives and serve over rice.

title: zucchini pecan bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour three 8 x 4-inch loaf pans.
Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla together until thick. Add zucchini and stir well.
Sift together the 3 cups of flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg. Gradually
add sifted dry ingredients to zucchini mixture, stirring only until batter is blended.
Dust raisins and nuts with 1 tablespoon of flour and gently fold into batter.
Pour into loaf pans, dividing evenly.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.
Let cool in pans 20 minutes.
Remove from pans to racks to continue cooling.

title: speedy dinner rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir in shortening, sugar, salt, milk and eggs.
Whisk until blended. Gradually add flour at first.
Add 1 cup; beat well.
Keep batter smooth and add remaining flour.
Turn onto oiled surface.
Dough should be smooth and workable.
If not, add 1/4 cup more flour.
Divide into 3 parts.

title: hot spiced wine
directions: Combine ingredients and simmer slowly.
Serve hot.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Drain.
Cook egg noodles.
Mix soup, sauce and mushrooms.
Mix everything together.
Top with cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: milky way bars(tastes like caramel brownies -- "gewy & chewy"!)
directions: Combine and mix dry cake mix, 2 eggs, 1/2 cup evaporated milk (save other 1/2 cup for later) and melted butter.
Spread 1/2 of this batter into a 9 x 11-inch metal greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 20 minutes.
Melt in double boiler unwrapped caramels and 1/2 cup evaporated milk. Pour caramel mixture over cooled baked batter.
Sprinkle 12 ounce bag of miniature chocolate chips and 1 cup chopped pecans over caramel.
Spread remaining uncooked batter over chips and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool minimally 1 1/2 hours before cutting.

title: blender pie
directions: Grease pie pan (9 inches).
Beat in blender all ingredients for 3 minutes.
Bake at 375°
for 30 minutes.
Cool on rack; refrigerate leftovers.

title: cinnamon discs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix oleo, egg, vanilla, flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Mix cinnamon and nuts.
Roll into 1-inch balls in cinnamon and nuts.
Bake at 375° until golden brown (7 to 10 minutes).

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and let cool. Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add eggs, dissolved yeast and 4 cups bread flour to cooled mixture.
Beat well with mixer until smooth.
Add remaining 2 cups of bread flour and beat with a large spoon. Leave dough in an airtight bowl in refrigerator overnight or longer, if you wish.

title: oven chicken stew
directions: Combine soup, wine, mushrooms, Kitchen Bouquet, celery, onions and peppers.
Mix all ingredients well and put into Dutch oven or 5-quart Corning dish.
Bake 2 hours at 350°, covered.
Stir about half-way.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli approximately 10 minutes or until barely tender. Mix all other ingredients together.
Place broccoli in casserole dish and pour sauce over.
Then cover with grated cheese and buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lively lemon roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In small saucepan, melt butter; add lemon juice, bouillon and hot pepper sauce.
Heat slowly until bouillon dissolves; set aside.
In medium bowl, combine rice, broccoli, cheese and 1/4 cup lemon butter sauce; mix well.
Divide broccoli mixture equally among fillets.
Roll up and place seam-side down in shallow baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over roll-ups.
Bake 25 minutes or until fish flakes with fork.
Spoon sauce over individual servings.
Garnish with paprika.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Put Spam through meat grinder.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Spread on one-half of hamburger bun; broil until cheese melts.
Good for children's party or brunch.

title: chili chuck
directions: Cut meat into thin strips; sprinkle with flour.
Brown; pour off fat.
Add tomatoes, water, onion and chili powder.
Cover on low heat for 1 hour.
Add soup and green peppers.
Cook 1/2 hour, covered.
Pour over rice and serve hot.

title: apple crunch
directions: Put apple filling in a pie plate.
In a mixing bowl, put the sugar and flour, then put the egg in the middle and beat.
Mix all with a spoon, then crumble with hands.
Pour mixture onto apple filling; pour on melted butter.
Put in oven at 300° until lightly browned.
Cut oven off; leave in oven with door closed until ready to eat.

title: cheddar cheese soup
directions: Heat 1/2 cup margarine or butter in a 4-quart saucepan over medium heat.
Add vegetables and cook until tender, stirring occasionally.
Add water and chicken bouillon; heat to boiling. Cover and cook over low heat for 10 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in large bowl.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°
for 12 minutes.

title: herb and garlic blend
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store, covered, in airtight container.
Shake to blend before using.
Makes 1/3 cup.
Great on Italian bread that is to be warmed in the oven.

title: fish dish
directions: Put single layer of fish in greased baking dish.
Combine all ingredients and pour over fish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Cut carrots into thin strips.
Cook until tender in salted water.
Place in 6 x 10-inch baking dish.
Mix together rest of the ingredients (except crumbs) and pour over carrots.
Sprinkle with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: jiffy doughnuts
directions: Let dough thaw but not rise.
Cut loaf in 3 strips lengthwise, then cut crosswise into chunks to look like 1-inch squares.
Drop in hot shortening.
Drain on brown paper.
Roll in white sugar and serve.

title: tiny timmies
directions: Drain the pineapple, saving the juice.
Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, pouring 3 tablespoons of the pineapple syrup over it.
Beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients; stir well.
Add pineapple, butterscotch bits and nuts, mixing well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet, leaving plenty of room for the cookies to spread, 2 inches apart.
Put a bit of cherry in center of each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes about 24 soft cookies.

title: s'mores
directions: Place 2 marshmallows on stick and toast over campfire.
Place chocolate square on graham cracker.
Place marshmallows on top of chocolate.
Top with another graham cracker.
Eat like a sandwich. A Girl Scout tradition!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° until done.

title: quick cocoa cupcakes
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add egg, baking soda, vanilla, flour, salt, buttermilk and Rhubarb.

title: scripture cookies
directions: Beat together first four ingredients, then add all the rest. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
But not before reading History of Joseph Smith 1:37 and D&C 133:11.

title: caramel candy
directions: Melt caramels and 3 tablespoons cream or milk in double boiler.
When melted, add the coconut, nuts and Rice Krispies. Mix real well.
Butter hands and roll into little balls.

title: cocoa
directions: Mix together.
Combine two heaping teaspoonfuls of mix and 1 cup boiling water.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Mix egg yolks and lemon juice in a blender.
Bring margarine to a bubbling boil and pour into egg yolk mixture while blender is running.
(The secret to success is pouring slowly.)

title: hamburger steak
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into large patty.
Fry in skillet as you would a hamburger.

title: bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Saute onion in bacon fat.
Brown hamburg; drain.
Add to bacon and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole dish until bubbly.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with Veg-All, then add Tater Tots.
Spread soup on top of this (do not add water to the soup before spreading).
Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix the cake mix, butter and 2 eggs by hand until moistened. Spread batter into heavily greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix the cream cheese, 2 eggs and powdered sugar (use mixer or sifter) and pour over batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs slightly. Add sugar, salt and spices; mix well, then add milk. Beat all together. Pour into a pastry-lined pie plate. Bake in hot oven (450°) 10 minutes. Reduce heat and bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until pie is firm.

title: quick pizza casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni until done; drain.
In a 2-quart casserole, combine all ingredients, except Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover; bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: mushroom-chicken casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain; add butter.
Cover bottom of deep dish with buttered noodles.
Alternate layers of chicken, chopped onion, peas, asparagus and soup.
Add milk.
Cover with cracker crumbs; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 8.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Melt 2 sticks margarine in pan; stir in 1 cup flour.
Add 1 cup milk at a time, stirring over medium heat to thicken.
When thick, add next cup of milk.
Use beaters if mixture gets lumpy. When thick, after all 4 cups of milk have been added, drain chicken and peas and add them to mixture.
Turn heat to low and heat through.
(Takes about 1/2 hour of standing on stove.)

title: potato salad with sour cream
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients on medium heat.
Add butter; cook about 3 minutes or until thick.
Remove from heat and let cool. Add sour cream, eggs and potatoes.
Optional:
sweet pickles and onions.

title: squash casserole
directions: Roll squash slices in flour and fry until golden brown.
Fry potato cubes separate.
Combine squash and potatoes in baking dish.
Place bacon strips across squash and potatoes.
Dilute mushroom soup and pour over squash and potatoes.
May also sprinkle bread crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° until hot through.

title: cinnamon swirl loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine 3 1/2 cups of the flour and the yeast. In saucepan, heat together milk, 1/2 cup sugar, Crisco, water and salt until warm, stirring occasionally to melt Crisco.
Add to dry ingredients in mixer bowl.
Add eggs and beat at low speed of electric mixer for 1/2 minute.
Scrape sides of bowl constantly. Beat 3 minutes at high speed.
By hand, stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Combine sugar, oil, vanilla and eggs.
Beat.
Add apples and pecans.
Mix. Pour mixture into tube pan and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Mix flour, salt, soda and wheat germ.
Set aside.
Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Add 2 eggs and apple juice.
Fold in flour and banana mixture.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable soup mix
directions: Boil vegetables, salt and sugar in tomato sauce according to package directions, stirring occasionally.
Add spices and allow to cool completely.
Pour into 1-quart freezer bags and freeze until needed.

title: potatoes deluxe
directions: Melt in a large bowl, onion, soup, sour cream, melted butter and cheese.
Mix in frozen potatoes; blend thoroughly.
Pour into a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for about 1 hour.

title: cranberry jello stuff
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix jello and cranberry mixture.
Let cool.
Add grapes, nuts and pineapple chunks. Return to refrigerator until set.

title: kidney bean and vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 1 1/2-quart round casserole, combine beans, corn, onions, tomato sauce and red pepper; mix lightly. Bake 40 minutes.
Top with cheese and bacon.
Continue baking 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Put water, meat, soup bone and a handful of salt in large cooking pot.
Cook one hour.
Add onions, celery and tomatoes and cook 1/2 hour.
Add potatoes and cabbage; cook 20 minutes.
Add package of frozen vegetables and noodles and cook for an additional 15 minutes.
Approximate cooking time: 2 hours and 15 minutes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Place bread evenly in 8-inch square baking dish coated with cooking spray.
Layer ham, red pepper and cheese over bread; set aside.
Combine milk and next 4 ingredients; pour over cheese. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Remove from refrigerator; let stand 30 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes; sprinkle with paprika.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6 (196 calories and 5 fat grams per 3/4 cup serving).

title: grandma's bread pudding
directions: Break or cube bread.
Cover with hot water.
Squeeze out excess water.
Add remaining ingredients, except milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Add milk.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Grease baking dish with butter and bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° or until top is firm.

title: one-cup cottage ring
directions: Dissolve lime-flavored gelatin in the boiling water.
Add mayonnaise or salad dressing and beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in the cottage cheese, celery and green pepper.
Pour into a 4 1/2-cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 6 servings.

title: steak supper in foil
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, place an 18 x 24-inch piece of heavy-duty foil.
Place meat on foil.
Stir mushroom soup and onion soup.
Mix together.
Spread on meat.
Top with vegetables.
Sprinkle water on vegetables.
Fold foil over and seal securely.
Cook for 1 1/2 hours until tender.
Serves 4.

title: cream cheese ball
directions: Mix all, except nuts.
Form into a ball.
Roll in the nuts until covered.
Best made a day or two ahead of time.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift flour and dry ingredients and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add berries and vanilla; mix well. Bake in an oblong pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: lauren's sugar cookies
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients.
Beat the next 2 ingredients. Stir in the last 3 ingredients.
Then, drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on lightly greased baking sheet.
Grease bottom of a glass.
Dip glass in sugar and flatten each cookie.
Sprinkle cookies with nutmeg.
Bake 8 to 11 minutes until light golden. Cool on a rack.
Makes about 3 dozen cookies.

title: rum cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts over bottom of 10-inch tube pan which has been greased and floured.
Mix all ingredients and pour over nuts. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool, prick top and spoon glaze over all.

title: baked blueberry-pecan french toast
directions: Butter a 9 x 13 baking dish.
In a large bowl, whisk together eggs, milk, nutmeg, vanilla and 3/4 c. brown sugar and pour evenly over bread.
Chill mixture, covered, until all liquid is absorbed by bread, at least 8 hours and up to one day.
Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a shallow baking pan, spread pecans evenly and toast in middle of oven until fragrant, about 8 minutes.
Toss pecans in pan with 1 teaspoon butter and salt. Increase oven temperature to 400 degrees.
Sprinkle pecans and blueberries evenly over bread mixture.
Cut 1/2 stick butter into pieces and in a small saucepan heat with remaining 1/4 c. brown sugar, stirring until butter is melted.
Drizzle butter mixture over bread and bake mixture 20 minutes or until any liquid from blueberries is bubbling.

title: strawberry balls
directions: Mix milk, 2 packages jello, nuts and coconut.
Shape and refrigerate overnight.
Roll in jello and trim.

title: grandma's corn pudding
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.
Serves 8.

title: prosciutto and melon
directions: Cut each piece of Prosciutto into 2 or 3 long strips.
Wrap it around melon pieces.
Grind fresh black pepper over.
Should not be made too far in advance.
Apples or kiwi can also be used.

title: syrup cookies (2)
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful and bake until golden.

title: pizzas
directions: Brown sausage and beef; drain off fat.
Add cheese, a little at a time, until it melts.
Add seasonings and let cool to a paste.
Spread on party rye slices.
May be frozen on cookie sheets and stored in Ziploc bags.
Place on cookie sheet; cook 8 minutes at 350°.

title: apricots with ricotta
directions: Combine the Ricotta cheese, powdered sugar, orange rind, 2 tablespoons Amaretto and vanilla in container in an electric blender or food processor; top with cover and process until smooth.
Transfer to a bowl and set aside.

title: black walnut - coconut cake
directions: Combine sugar, salad oil and eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; stir in nuts, coconut and flavoring.
Pour batter into a well-greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake 65 minutes at 325° or until
cake tests done.
Pour hot coconut syrup over hot cake.
Allow cake to remain in pan 4 hours to absorb syrup. Wrap well.
(Cake will be very moist.)

title: graham cracker pie crust
directions: Combine crumbs, cinnamon and sugar in a bowl; blend butter into mixture.
Press firmly against sides and bottom of a greased 9-inch glass pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until lightly browned.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
More water may be added, if desired.

title: 7 up pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time and continue beating.
Add flour gradually.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Last, slowly add 7 up.
Pour into greased and floured tube or bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately one hour, five minutes.
Let cool for 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: ham and cheese log
directions: In bowl, mix cheeses until blended.
Add ham.
Stir in other optional items.
Chill.
Shape into 2 logs and roll in pecans. Chill until time to serve.
Serve with crackers.

title: frozen fruit punch
directions: Mix first 2 ingredients.
Boil 3 minutes and cool; add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and freeze.
Thaw mixture until mushy to serve.
Add 3 quarts chilled ginger ale.
Serves 35 to 40.

title: microwave lasagne
directions: Combine spaghetti sauce, meat, seasonings and 1/4 cup water in bowl.
Combine cottage cheese, egg, Parmesan and seasonings in another bowl.
Using a greased 3 quart shallow oblong glass casserole, layer and spread as follows:
1/3 of meat sauce (about 2 cups), 1/2 noodles (uncooked), 1/2 of cottage cheese mixture, 1/2 of cheese slices (3 crosswise).
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Cook at full power (High) for 15 minutes, then 15 minutes at 50% power (Medium).
Let stand about 10 minutes.
Dish should be covered with plastic wrap before cooking; corner should be turned up.

title: orange chicken and rice
directions: Heat juice, sugar and brown sugar on medium-low heat until dissolved.
Dissolve the cornstarch in about 1/4 cup of water, then mix into juice.

title: apple roll
directions: Combine the flour, shortening and milk to moisten.
Roll out into a sheet.
Spread with the chopped apples.
Sprinkle brown sugar and cinnamon over apples.
Roll up, slice and place in a pan or dish in which the water, butter, white sugar and vanilla are boiling.
Put in oven; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: milk shakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing until foamy.
Spoon into glasses.

title: key west key lime pie
directions: Beat the egg yolks until light and lemon colored.
Add 1/2 cup Key lime juice.
Beat in the contents of the can of sweetened condensed milk and green food coloring to attain a natural lime tint.
Pour the custard into a baked pie crust.

title: triple cheese spread
directions: Grate the cheeses and mix together.
Add mayonnaise, sugar, salad, mustard and tabasco.
Mix in the rest of ingredients and blend well.
Delicious cracker spread.

title: tuscan-style fettuccine with artichokes
directions: Cook and drain fettuccine.
Keep warm.
In a large skillet over medium-high heat, melt butter or margarine. Add artichokes, cilantro, oregano, garlic and pepper.
Cook, stirring, for several minutes until ingredients are combined and mixture is hot.
Pour over warm pasta and toss to coat evenly. Sprinkle generously with Parmesan cheese and serve.

title: rhubarb bread
directions: Bake approximately 60 minutes at 325°.
Do not overbake as this is a moist bread.
It is usually best to test when it appears a golden brown.

title: chocolate coffee cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, salt and cocoa, then add oil, milk and baking powder.
Put baking soda in boiling coffee.
Add to the rest.
Bake at 350°.
Pour into 2 round or square cake pans.
Bake for 35 minutes.

title: peach kuchen
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into cake mix until crumbly. Mix in coconut.
Pat mixture lightly into greased oblong pan (13 x 9-inch).
Build up slight edges.
Bake 10 minutes.
Arrange peaches on warm crust.
Mix cinnamon-sugar; sprinkle on peaches. Blend sour cream and yolks.
Drizzle over peaches.
Bake 25 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Do not overbake.
Serve warm or cold.

title: regina's broccoli dip
directions: Saute onion in oleo.
Add broccoli and simmer until tender. Add remainder of ingredients and serve hot with corn chips.
Makes 4 cups.

title: chicken "n" noodles
directions: Add soup to broth. Add carrots, celery and onions. Simmer until vegetables are tender. Add the noodles and chicken. Cook until noodles are tender. You may need to add more water.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften for easy mixing.
Chop onion and pepper.
Mix all ingredients, reserving a few pecans for the top. Form into a ball; sprinkle remaining pecans on top.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.
Serve with crackers.

title: candy
directions: Prepare a cookie sheet greased with butter.
Assemble all premeasured ingredients, gather all required utensils, including two pot holders, because when the candy reaches a certain point, one must work quickly!

title: hearty potato soup
directions: Bring potatoes, water and salt to boil in medium-size saucepan.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Without draining them, mash potatoes until the size of peas.
Meanwhile, in large saucepan, cook onion in margarine 3 minutes until translucent.
Sprinkle with flour; cook and stir 1 minute.
Gradually stir in milk and cook, stirring frequently, 5 to 7 minutes until simmering and thickened.
Stir in potato mixture and remaining ingredients.
Makes 4 generous servings.

title: baked corn custard
directions: Separate eggs and beat whites to fold in last.
Bake in greased pan in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and ham dish
directions: Dip chicken in egg, then bread crumbs.
Brown in oil, lightly. Butter casserole; layer chicken, ham and cheese.
Top with mushrooms.
Melt butter and add wine.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil.
Can be made ahead of time.
Serves 8.

title: party time salad
directions: Heat pineapple to boiling point. Add jello and dissolve. Chill until partially set. Soften cream cheese. Add pimento to cheese and then add to jello. Fold in Cool Whip, celery and nuts. Chill until firm.

title: baked tomato parmesan
directions: Halve the tomatoes; sprinkle with onion salt and herbs.
Put tomatoes in a Pyrex dish; place in a warm oven (275° to 300°) for 5 minutes.
Set aside and cool.
Mix mayonnaise, onion and Parmesan cheese; spoon over tomatoes.
Just before serving, place in oven on broil setting until puffed and lightly browned, about 3 to 5 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Put all ingredients in large stock pot and simmer until potatoes and meat are done.

title: beef roll-ups
directions: Mix stuffing as directed on package.
Cover and microwave 3 minutes.
Uncover.
Fluff with fork.
Spread a layer of prepared stuffing on each slice of steak. Roll up each steak, tucking in ends.
Secure each with a toothpick.
Place in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until steak is done.
Roll-ups can be cooked in electric skillet, slow cooker or rangetop skillet.
(Add small amount of water or broth to prevent sticking.)
Or microwave at 5 minute intervals to desired meat doneness, about 15 minutes total.

title: lobster bisque
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour.
Mix and then add chicken broth.
Add cream and wine.
Mix. Boil for 10 minutes. Add lobster pieces.

title: fancy bread spread
directions: Whip together and serve with breads such as zucchini, banana and cranberry.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Saute vegetables until softened.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl; stir to combine. Pour into a 9 or 10-inch quiche or pie pan which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 8 servings.

title: minestrone
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil.
Combine remaining ingredients, except macaroni.
Cook until vegetables are tender, about 1 1/2 hours.
Add macaroni.
Serve hot.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: honey bread
directions: Mix eggs and 1 cup sugar.
Add melted margarine, honey, sour cream, soda and vanilla; mix well.
Add flour until consistency of sour cream.
Put into pan; bake for ?? minutes.
Preheat oven to 400° and reduce to 300° when put into oven.

title: fruit topped cake
directions: Spread pie filling over cooled cake.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and whipped cream.
Spread over
pie
filling.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: barbecue meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients well together.
Make into meatballs about the size of walnuts.
Place meatballs in baking dish sprayed with Pam spray.
Pour barbecue sauce over each meatball.
Bake about 1 hour at 350°.

title: cole slaw
directions: Grate cabbage, carrots and onions; set aside.
Add pickle juice, milk and celery seed to mayonnaise; stir well.
Add mixture to cabbage, carrots and onions.
Blend; cover tightly and store in refrigerator.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind first 5 ingredients and drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar and spices; bring to a boil.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Can in hot jars and seal.

title: mounds candy bars
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients and make into mounds or small shaped balls.
In double boiler, melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax.
Using a toothpick, dip mounds into chocolate mixture.
Lay on wax paper to cool.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Add remaining ingredients and mix together.
Put together 6 or 8 tortillas in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add a layer of meat mixture, then a layer of nacho or tortilla chips, meat, then top with a layer of chips.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tom thumb squares
directions: Mix Crisco, salt and 1/2 c. brown sugar together. Add flour. Press mixture tightly into a 8-inch pan. Bake 15 minutes at 300°.

title: asparagus with lemon sauce
directions: Cook asparagus according to package directions, omitting salt and fat. Drain well.
Place in a serving dish.
Combine egg and cornstarch, stirring to blend. Melt margarine over low heat in a small skillet. Add egg mixture.
Stir in lemon juice. Continue to cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly.
Pour over asparagus and sprinkle with lemon rind.
Exchanges:
1 vegetable/1/2 cup.

title: candied yams
directions: Peel and boil sweet potatoes until tender.
Place in baking dish.
Mix syrup, melted butter, sugar and water until well blended.
Sprinkle cinnamon to taste over potatoes.
Pour syrup mixture over potatoes.
Bake at least 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Separate cabbage leaves.
Put in boiling water for about 2 minutes.
Mix hamburger, rice, onion, peppers, salt and pepper. Roll small amount of mixture in hand to form ball.
Wrap in cabbage leaf.
Put in greased baking dish.
Pour tomato juice over until about 3/4 covered.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: nobby apple cake
directions: Mix all of the above together and pour into an 8x8 pan. Sprinkle coconut on top (optional). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or more. Frost like any other cake or eat plain.

title: peaches 'n cream cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, pudding mix, butter, egg and milk and beat for 2 minutes with electric mixer.
Grease a 10-inch pie plate.
Pour batter into dish, spreading evenly.
Place peach slices over the top of batter.
Combine cream cheese, honey and orange juice and beat well.
Spread topping over peaches to within 1 inch of the edge of the baking dish.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar with cinnamon and sprinkle over cake.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: a-1 hot buttered rum mix
directions: In a saucepan, cook butter and sugars over medium heat beating gently with a whisk until it becomes light in color, about 10 minutes.
Stir in the spices and the ice cream; blend well. Refrigerate or freeze until ready to use.
Use a heaping teaspoon per drink, adding a shot of rum and boiling water to fill the mug.

title: pistachio congealed salad
directions: Drain and mix fruit cocktail and crushed pineapple with pistachio pudding, then add one medium size Cool Whip.
Keep in refrigerator until ready to eat.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion in margarine until done. Add remaining ingredients.
Cook over low heat about 45 minutes. This is good with most meats. It can be brushed on meat while cooking or used at the table.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until falls off bones.
Spread the chicken in pieces in the bottom of a large casserole.
Layer with the broccoli.
Mix the next 4 ingredients together and spread on the broccoli.
Top with the cheese.
Add the bread crumbs mixed with butter.
Bake in 350° oven for approximately 1/2 hour or until golden and bubbly.

title: corndogs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Dip wieners in batter.
Cook in Crisco in a small frying pan, turning several times until golden brown.

title: squashage casserole
directions: Cook sausage and onion in skillet until done; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with additional cracker crumbs if desired.

title: beef burgundy
directions: Brown meat in melted margarine and put into a 2-quart baking dish.
Blend flour and seasonings.
Mix flour with wine and beef bouillon.
Pour over meat. Cover and bake at 325° for 2 hours. Add onion and mushrooms.
Cover and continue cooking 1 hour more. Serve over hot rice.

title: rich cream scones
directions: Combine flour, salt, baking powder and sugar in a bowl.
Cut in the butter with a pastry blender, or rub in with fingertips. Mix in egg and cream with a fork.
Stir in currants.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured board and pat out in a circle about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut in wedges.
Brush tops with slightly beaten egg white and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 18 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: wine cookies
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl.
Mix together.
Add 1/4 to 1/2 cup more flour if dough is too sticky.
Drop by teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Frost with your favorite icing.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: grape-nut pudding dessert
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
Let set in refrigerator.
Fold in Cool Whip and Grape-Nuts.

title: rosemary biscuit muffins
directions: Melt butter in microwave.
Stir in rosemary and pepper.
With pastry brush, brush the insides of 12 tin muffin cups with mixture.
Preheat oven to 400°.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Heat oil; add cabbage, bell pepper, salt and pepper and water. Cover and turn heat down to simmer and cook until cabbage is tender.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Slice and boil squash with onion until tender.
Salt and pepper; drain.
Add Pet milk, butter and mushroom soup to desired consistency.
Mix well and pour into a large baking dish (glass). Place slices of Velveeta cheese on top.
Bake uncovered at 350° until cheese melts.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine flours, sugar, baking powder, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg, dates and walnuts; set aside.
Whisk egg, pumpkin, milk, butter, honey and orange zest; blend well.
Add liquid ingredients to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.

title: yummy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add evaporated milk that has been mixed with warm water.
Then add oil, sugar, salt and egg. Mix well and add bread flour.
Cover with wax paper and towel. Let rise until double (1 to 1 1/2 hours).
Knead well and make out into rolls 1/2-inch thick.
Dip in melted butter.
Place on pan and let rise 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 425° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: creamy beef stew
directions: Boil your meat and potatoes until tender; drain water.
Cook your soup and milk; add onions and carrots.
Add meat and potatoes.
Let simmer, covered, for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: barbecue ham sandwiches
directions: Cut meat in bite-size pieces.
Fry in a little butter. Sprinkle some flour over meat, then add the rest of ingredients. Simmer 1 hour.
Makes 15 to 20 sandwiches.

title: cranberry bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cranberries and nuts.
After blended well, fold in nuts and cranberries.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Immediately remove from pan and cool on rack.

title: scrambled egg muffins
directions: In a skillet, brown sausage and drain. In a bowl, beat eggs and add onion, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Spoon by 1/3 cupfuls into well-greased muffin cups. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Yield: 1 dozen.

title: waldorf coleslaw
directions: More raisins and nuts may be used if you so desire.

title: creamed chicken with vegetables
directions: In skillet, cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in soup and milk. Add chicken; cook until tender.
Stir in vegetables and potatoes.
Heat through.
Makes 4 to 6 servings. (Easy way to use leftover chicken or turkey.)

title: cherry fruit salad
directions: Drain cherries.
Measure juice; add water to make 1 cup. Dissolve jello in boiling water; add measured liquid and undrained pineapple.
Chill until thickened.
Stir in cherries; chill until firm (4 hours).
Use for salad to accompany ham.
Use for dessert by omitting celery.
Makes 12 to 14 servings.

title: seafood fettuccine alfredo
directions: Melt the margarine in a saucepan.
Put in 2 tablespoons flour to thicken.
Add 2 cups milk.
Simmer on low heat.
Add Parmesan and seasonings.
Serve over cooked fettuccine.

title: potato rolls
directions: Mix 1/2 cup warm water, 2 tablespoons yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar.
Set aside.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease and flour two 9-inch round pans. Combine flour, baking powder, salt and soda; set aside.
Beat together shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Blend in bananas.
Add flour mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until done.
Cool on wire rack for 10 minutes.
Loosen edges and remove from pans; cool completely. Fill and frost with frosting.

title: fruit bowl cake
directions: (NutraSweet glaze can be substituted for regular.
Lite Cool Whip may also be substituted.)

title: sour cream strawberry pie
directions: Combine 2 cups Cool Whip and sour cream and mix well.
Fold in strawberries and spoon into crust.
Chill and serve.
Top with remaining strawberries before serving.

title: italian herb chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing and seasoning.
Brush chicken with half of salad dressing mixture.
Place chicken on grill over medium hot coals.
Grill for 8 minutes.
Turn; brush with remaining salad dressing mixture.
Continue grilling for 8 minutes or until tender.

title: potato soup
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in
a large saucepan.
Drain.
After meat is browned, add water and celery.
Let cook 15 to 20 minutes over medium heat.
Add the tomatoes, salt and pepper.
Let simmer about 5 minutes. Add the potatoes. Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix ingredients; roll into balls.
Put into oven at 350° until brown.
Makes approximately 84 balls.

title: small cocktail pizzas
directions: Oil party rye on both sides. Spread sauce followed by grated sharp cheese, pepperoni, parsley flakes, oregano and Parmesan cheese. Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 350°. Serve warm.

title: hot rolls
directions: Heat sugar, corn oil and milk almost to boiling point.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in warm water and add to lukewarm mixture.
When it cools to lukewarm, fold in 3 cups flour and mix well.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Then add 2 1/4 cups plain flour, salt and soda.
Let rise 1 hour and roll out or refrigerate to be rolled out later.

title: poor man linguini salad
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place in container with tight seal.
Refrigerate overnight.
Shake container to mix ingredients several times.
Serve cold.

title: microwave turkey meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl with hands or spoon until blended.
Place a 4-ounce glass custard cup, right side up, in the center of a 9-inch deep dish microwave-safe pie plate.
Place turkey mixture in a ring around custard cup.
Loosely cover turkey mixture with waxed paper.
Microwave on High 12 to 15 minutes, rotating dish 1/4 turn every 4 minutes, until meat is opaque at center, no longer pink and thermometer registers 160°.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes to finish cooking.

title: country ham 'n' potato soup
directions: In 2-quart saucepan over medium heat in hot margarine, cook cabbage and ham 5 minutes or until cabbage is tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low.
Heat through.
Makes 3 1/2 cups or 2 servings.

title: mini-grasshopper cheesecakes
directions: Line muffin tin with paper liners; place one cookie in each liner.
Mix cream cheese, mint flavoring and sugar on medium speed until well blended.
Add eggs and food coloring; mix well.
Pour over cookies, filling 3/4 full.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan when cool.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix mayo, soup, eggs and onion.
Add cooked broccoli and toss all ingredients well.
Place in greased casserole dish and top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions and set aside.
Mix together milk and pudding mixes; set aside.
Combine 1/2 of cake into a large bowl.
Spread 1/2 of pineapple over crumbled cake. Spread 1/2 of pudding mixture over pineapple.
Add 1/2 Cool Whip over pudding.
Top with 1/2 cherry pie filling.
Repeat layers. Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Cream oil and sugar; add eggs (one at a time) and beat well together.
Sift flour with soda, salt and cinnamon and add to oil mixture along with vanilla extract.
Fold in finely cut apple and chopped nuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 hour at 375°.
Frost with Penuche Icing.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May heat in saucepan to melt and smooth.

title: minehaha cake
directions: Cream butter, gradually adding sugar.
Beat well.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Combine flour, baking powder, and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition, stir in flavoring.
Beat egg whites (at room temperature) until stiff peaks form.
Fold into batter.
Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool in pans 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool completely.
Frost.

title: easy cake icing
directions: Mix all the ingredients, combining dry ingredients first and adding milk, margarine and vanilla.
Mix well and cook in Teflon skillet, stirring often until mixture thickens and becomes clear. Great on angel food cake.

title: prune cake
directions: Cream eggs
and
sugar.
Add
oil.
Alternate flour and baking powder
with
buttermilk.
When
of
buttermilk is mixed, add soda
to remainder of milk.
Proceed with milk and flour alternately.
Add
cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and salt. Add prunes and
nuts.	Pour into ungreased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Beat egg whites; set aside.
Combine flour and sugar; add egg yolks, beating well.
Add remaining ingredients, folding in egg whites last.
Pour batter into well greased and floured tube pan. Place in cold oven.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together into a large bowl; make well in center.
Beat eggs slightly and add with other "wet" ingredients. Do not beat, just stir well, adding coconut and nuts last.
Spoon into well-greased and floured tube pan and bake at 300° for about 1 hour and 15 minutes, until top is nicely browned.
Cool in pan at least 15 minutes before removing.
This cake needs no icing and remains moist for as long as it lasts which isn't usually very long!

title: fruit liqueur
directions: Fill a 1 gallon wide-mouth jar 2/3 full of any kind of berry or fruit, which should be quite ripe and washed.
Add cubed sugar and press down with wooden spoon.
Fill jar with vodka.
In a few days, fruit will rise to top.
Press down and fill with vodka. Let stand 6 weeks, then strain into a bottle.

title: sweet potatoes delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place sweet potatoes in a large baking dish, top with apple, raisins and cranberries.
Drizzle with honey; pour orange juice over all.	Bake approximately one hour or until tender.

title: tomato aspic salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and add other ingredients when it starts to jell.
Can be made ahead a day or so.

title: wranglers pot roast
directions: Rub roast with salt and pepper. In skillet, brown beef in oil; transfer to slow cooker. Saut onion and
garlic

until brown. Add wine and coffee. Cook over medium, stirring to loosen bits from bottom. Pour over meat. Push bay leaf in liquid. Cover and cook for 9 to 10 hours or until tender. Using slotted spoon, remove garlic and bay leaf. In small bowl, stir water and cornstarch until smooth. Stir into hot liquid in slow cooker. Cook on high 10 to 15 minutes, until thick. Slice meat and serve with gravy.

title: chicken in the grass
directions: Heat oil in frypan over medium heat.
Cut peppers and onions into strips.
Add garlic, peppers and onions to frypan and saute until barely tender.
Cook noodles
until just tender.
Line deep casserole with double thickness of foil.
Spread noodles over bottom of the casserole.
Place Fri Chik on noodles.
Cover Fri Chik and noodles with peppers, onions, artichoke hearts and mushrooms.
Add reserved juices.
Cover with foil and bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Remove top foil and spread sour cream over casserole.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: john's classic oven baked beans
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook bacon until crisp, drain, crumble. In a one quart casserole, combine all. Bake uncovered 30 to 35 minutes or until thickened and bubbly, stirring every 15 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: spinach dip
directions: Spinach needs to be drained and press dry between paper towels. Combine all ingredients together in large bowl.
Mix well. Chill before serving.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix all together.
Add buttermilk.
Stir to get the lumps out. Put some oil in a heavy cast-iron skillet.
Heat and sprinkle some flour in the pan.
Add the cornbread mixture.
Bake in 500° oven for 15 minutes.

title: cream corn bread
