directions: Mix together; bake in a glass dish at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes, until golden brown.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter, white sugar and brown sugar together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir until all are mixed well.
Drop on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.
Cool on cake rack.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Bake cake as box directs in a sheet pan.
Cool.
Mix pudding mix using 2 1/2 cups milk.
Drain pineapple well.
Mix with pudding; spread over cake.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts, if desired.

title: gourmet meatballs
directions: Combine ground beef, sausage, egg, bread crumbs, onion, green pepper, celery, salt, garlic, basil, chili powder, thyme and red pepper in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Brown on all sides in oil in skillet; drain.
Spoon meatballs into baking dish.
Cover with Red Wine Sauce.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes. May prepare ahead and freeze uncooked meatballs in sauce for up to 2 months.
Yield:
96 servings.

title: microwave macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter in 2 quart casserole on 100% power for 1 to 1 1/2 minutes.
Stir
in	flour, salt and then milk.
Cook on 50% power 8
to
minutes,
until	mixture
thickens.
Add mustard and cheese;
stir
to
blend.
Mix in cooked macaroni and cook	on 50% power for 10 minutes, until bubbling.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chilli reliono
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain.
Add marinating sauce, garlic powder and chili powder. Simmer until liquid is absorbed.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix and pour into ice cream freezer and freeze.

title: rosie's chicken
directions: Bread chicken cutlets with 1/2 bread crumbs and 1/2 Parmesan cheese; brown in margarine and chopped garlic.
Remove from pan. Saute mushrooms in margarine and garlic.
Put cutlets back into pan with mushrooms.
Pour enough wine to cover chicken and boil, then simmer, for 15 minutes.
Put slice of Mozzarella on top of each cutlet and cover.
Place in oven for about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve over noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix stuffing with melted margarine.
Put half of mixture in bottom of pan. Add chicken, then soups mixed with chicken broth. Cover with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: steak in oven
directions: Prepare steak as for frying.
Brown in small amount of oil. Spray a 9 x 13-inch glass Pyrex dish with Pam.
Cover bottom of dish with sliced onions.
Place browned steak on onions.
Cover with mushroom soup.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove foil for last 1/2 hour of baking time.

title: summer pudding
directions: *Use raspberries, stoned cherries, blueberries, strawberries, red or black currants.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Mix
all together; cook at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over Chinese noodles.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour in medium pot.
Stir in water and cook in double boiler until clear.
Grate rind from lemons and squeeze juice out.
Add rind and lemon juice to cooked mixture.
Add egg yolks mixed with a little cooked mixture.
Add butter.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Pour in baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue.

title: mounds bars
directions: Melt chocolate with oil, spread half on wax paper and cool. Mix milk and gelatine, heat until dissolved and ready to boil. Stir in nuts and coconut.
Cool to warm and spread over chocolate. Then spread the rest of the chocolate over coconut mixture.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chili
directions: Cook meat until brown; drain.
Add onions, garlic and chili powder.
Cook until onions are done.
Add flour to meat.
In a large pot, combine beans, soup, tomatoes and meat mixture.
Stir occasionally; simmer at least 1 1/2 hours.
Freezes well.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O as directed on package.
Refrigerate until partly set.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and let jell. Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: debbie's dessert
directions: Mix well, pineapple and pudding.
Add whipped topping and mix well.
Refrigerate

title: veggie salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and toss well.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and margarine until creamy.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing after each one.
Add soda to buttermilk, then add flour and buttermilk alternately.
Add flavoring and beat until well mixed.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients with melted butter.
Put cherry pie mix into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Spread the flour, oatmeal and sugar mixture over the cherries.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Clean and hull peppers. Boil 5 minutes and drain. Saute onion lightly with ground beef until beef is lightly brown. Mix together with salt, pepper, cheese, cooked rice, egg and 1/2 cup tomato sauce. Stuff peppers. Put in a pan. Pour rest of tomato sauce over peppers. Sprinkle with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mmmeat patties
directions: In a bowl, stir together egg, oats, onion powder, salt and pepper.
Add meat and mix well.
Shape mixture into four 3/4-inch thick patties.
Place patties in frypan or on grill to cook.

title: stuffed pasta shell tacos
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add cream cheese, sour cream and chili powder to beef; stir until well blended.
Boil pasta per package; drain.
Stuff meat mixture into shells; place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread taco sauce over shells.
Cover with foil; bake for 15 minutes at 375°.
Cover with crushed chips and cheeses; bake for another 15 minutes, uncovered.
Top with toppings that you like.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Beat eggs and add to mixture.
Add syrup and beat well.
Place mixture in microwave until margarine is melted and mixture is slightly thickened.
Beat until margarine is blended.
Pour into pie shell and cover with pecans.
Bake at 350° until done, approximately 4 or 5 minutes.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Melt butter, brown sugar and milk; bring to a boil.
Add powdered sugar and mix until spreading consistency.

title: date balls
directions: Cook dates, sugar, brown sugar and egg, then add Rice Krispies and vanilla.
Shape into balls and roll in coconut or colored sugar.

title: dill pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a crock-pot or large pot. Cover with a plate so that plate fits into the pot and can be pressed down onto the pickle mixture.
Place a rock or heavy weight (large bottle of water will do) and press down to secure tightly.
Let stand for 2 days.
Remove from crock and divide into jars and refrigerate.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with additional shredded cheese if desired.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mrs. field's ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Whisk together the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Mix sugars together and add butter, then cream together.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix together and add to flour mixture.
Fold chips into dough.
Use an ice cream scoop to drop cookies onto ungreased silver cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen cookies.
Store in airtight container.

title: texas style baked beans
directions: Place beans in baking dish. Combine syrup and brown sugar. Pour over beans and mix well. Add tomato sauce and onions. Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: mock turkey
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Very good with cheese melted on top last 10 minutes of baking time.
A delicious, simple hamburger dish.

title: spinach with parmesan
directions: Cook spinach according to instructions using 1/2 cooking time. Be sure to mash and drain all moisture.
In large skillet, saute garlic in olive oil, stopping just before brown.
Stir in spinach and saute until coated with oil.
Stir in eggs and cook until eggs are almost done.
Stir in Parmesan cheese and cook until blended, 2 or 3 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix together yeast, 1 teaspoon sugar and warm water; set aside for 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix flour into yeast mixture; add eggs, 2/3 cup sugar, butter and sour cream, then knead.
Put into greased bowl and cover; let rise approximately 4 hours.
Divide in 4 sections.
Roll out each and brush with butter.
Sprinkle cinnamon, brown sugar, raisins and nuts and roll up.
Cut and put in greased pans and let rise.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Drizzle with powdered sugar and water mixture.

title: harbor house crab cakes
directions: In a bowl mix eggs, bread crumbs, mayonnaise and seasonings. Salt to taste.
Add crabmeat and mix gently but thoroughly.
Shape into cakes and fry or saute until golden brown.
Serves 5 to 6.

title: fruit salad in orange cups
directions: Cut oranges in half crosswise, remove pulp and membrane. Reserve the shells.
Mix orange pulp, grapes and pineapple. Sprinkle with sweetener.
Add lemon juice and chill for several hours.
Just before serving, add sliced bananas, mix and fill orange shell with mixture.

title: sour cream chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Boil the 2 chicken breasts with onion.
Cool and then cut into bite-sized pieces.
Combine chicken, sour cream, Ro-Tel tomatoes and undiluted soup.
Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put about 2 tablespoons of mixture into the tortillas and roll.
Place into pan with seam side up and continue to make enchiladas, reserving 1/4 to 1/3 of the mixture.
Place the reserve mixture on top of the enchilada seams to seal them.
Cover with remaining cheese. Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: fran's glass cake
directions: Dissolve each package of Jell-O in 1 1/2 cups of boiling water (works well to set in pie plates or 9 x 9-inch square pans). Chill until firm.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Cook peas according to directions; drain and refrigerate.
In medium bowl, combine peas, tomatoes, green pepper and onion; mix well.
Combine vinegar and sugar; pour over pea mixture and toss. Chill at least 30 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oreo cookie freakout
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with crushed cookies.
Spread the softened ice cream over cookies.
Heat sauce and pour on, then nuts, Cool Whip and more crumbs.
Freeze.
Cut in small squares. Very rich.

title: pedigreed pork chops
directions: Brown chops in oil.
Add onion, barbecue sauce and water. Simmer, covered, until tender, about 45 minutes.
Remove chops to serving platter.
Spoon drippings over chops and keep them warm.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots and onion until tender; drain.
Melt margarine and cheese.
Mix carrot mixture, cheese and parsley.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with crushed chips.
Bake for 20 minutes or until golden in color.

title: company salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Cool.
Add bananas, marshmallows and pineapple.
Chill until firm.

title: mardi gras punch
directions: In punch bowl, stir together orange juice, lemonade and apple juice.
Stir in ginger ale; scoop sherbet into balls and spoon into punch.

title: tang pie
directions: Put Tang, Eagle Brand milk and sour cream in bowl.
Mix with spoon, not mixer.
Pour into pie crust.
Let set overnight.

title: family style swiss cheese fondue
directions: Melt butter in fondue pot over a moderate direct flame or in a pot on the stove.
Stir in next 5 ingredients.
Stir in milk; cook.
Stirring constantly until sauce is smooth and thickened, turn down heat.
Add cheese, a small amount at
a time, and stir until cheese is melted after each addition.
Serves 6 to 8.
Cut in half for a smaller amount.

title: wacky cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Sift flour, soda, cocoa and salt into an 8-inch pan.
Make 3 holes in mixture.
In one hole pour vanilla.
Next pour vinegar.
In third hole, pour oil.
Pour water over all and stir until smooth.
Sprinkle nuts on top of batter.
Bake 25 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients, except croutons.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle croutons over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: carrot pie
directions: Combine
carrots,
brown sugar, evaporated milk, vanilla and eggs in bowl.
Mix cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg, salt and flour in small
bowl.
Add to carrot mixture, mixing well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake in preheated 425° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until set.
Garnish with whipped topping and pecan halves.

title: pork and bean salad
directions: Add enough mayonnaise to flavor mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: baked caramel corn
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan melt margarine.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring mixture to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil over medium heat without stirring for 5 minutes. Remove from heat.
Stir in baking soda and vanilla.
In a large bowl gradually pour hot syrup over popped corn, mixing well.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream shortening, sugars, vanilla, water and egg until light and fluffy.
Mix flour, soda and salt; blend into cream mixture.
Stir in chopped nuts and chocolate chips. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove from pan immediately.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: oatmeal-chocolate chip cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and preheat oven to 350°.
Pour boiling water over oats and let stand for 10 minutes. Add sugars and margarine to oats.
Stir until margarine melts.
Add eggs and mix well.
Add flour, soda, salt and cocoa to oat mixture. Add half the chocolate chips.
Stir (do not user mixer).
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle remaining chocolate chips over top of cake. Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done with toothpick.

title: little devils
directions: Combine melted butter and dry cake mix.
Mixture should be crumbly.
Make sure butter is not too hot.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups of mixture for topping.
Pat remaining mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Combine peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Put in the pan on top of other mixture.
Place remaining 1 1/2 cups of mixture on the top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Let cool.
Cut into bars. Makes 3 dozen (1 1/2-inch) bars.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Put Eagle Brand, chocolate and salt in top of double boiler. Cook over rapidly boiling water for about 10 minutes. Remove from heat. Slowly stir in water, amount depending on consistency desired. Cool. Stir in vanilla. Serve over ice cream, cake or pudding.

title: kentucky pound cake
directions: Cream
sugar
and oil; add flour gradually with pineapple, egg
yolks,
water, cinnamon
and nuts.
Beat egg whites until stiff
and fold in mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes in greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: herbed meat loaves
directions: In a medium-size mixing bowl, combine egg, stuffing mix, milk, onion soup mix and the 2 tablespoons barbecue sauce.
Add the ground beef and mix well.
Shape into 5 loaves.
Arrange the loaves around the edge of a 1 3/4-quart casserole.
Cover with waxed paper and cook on High in microwave for 25 to 30 minutes. Remove and let stand for 5 minutes.
Heat the 1/4 cup sauce and spoon over loaves before serving.
Makes 5 servings.

title: joe's mountain goulash
directions: Saute onions and ground beef in large skillet until meat loses red color.
Transfer to large pot and add tomatoes (chopped), kidney beans, limas and English peas.
Simmer for 30 minutes. Then add corn and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: stretch-a-tuna salad
directions: Pour water over oats and let stand 20 minutes.
Combine with remaining ingredients and stir gently.
Cool thoroughly.
Serve as sandwich filling or use to stuff a tomato or serve as is on a lettuce leaf.

title: karo crunch
directions: Combine popped corn, pecans and almonds on cookie sheet.

Mix well. Combine sugar, butter and Karo in pan. Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil for 10 to 15 minutes until mixture turns caramel colored. Remove from heat. Add vanilla. Pour over popcorn. Coat well and store in airtight container.

title: toasted almond party spread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well. Spread mixture in a 9-inch quiche dish or 9-inch pie plate.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes, stirring after 8 minutes.
Garnish with additional toasted almonds.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: lemon-garlic orange roughy
directions: Finely chop garlic.
Mix with spices and salt with rounded side of spoon.
Add lemon juice and olive oil.
In bottom of glass baking dish, put a couple of tablespoons of mixture to coat.
Then add fish and rub rest of mixture into fish.
Broil until flaky.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine everything except chili powder.
Beef can be cut in small pieces or put in blender.
Form into a ball and coat with chili powder.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt together.
Blend mayonnaise and sugar together.
Add flour mixture.
Add water and beat until smooth.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast and soda in water.
Mix sugar with flour.
Cut shortening into flour and sugar mixture.
Dump yeast mixture into flour.
Stir.
Add buttermilk.
Cover and refrigerate.
Divide when ready to make biscuits.
Pat out and cut with large cutter. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes or until brown.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Spoon into foil cupcake liners in muffin pans or cake pan.
Freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer 20 to 30 minutes before serving.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain liquid from clams into a pan and add water to make 3 cups.
Bring liquid to a boil; add potatoes and onions.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Blend flour and cold water; add to potato mixture slowly.
Boil until thickened.
Add salt, pepper, butter and clams.
Bring to a boil.
Add heated milk to clam mixture.
Serve with crusty cheese toast slices.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Melt chocolate with 6 tablespoons butter over low heat, stirring constantly.
Cool.
Cream remaining butter with cheese. Gradually add 1/2 cup sugar; cream well after each addition. Blend in 2 eggs, 2 tablespoons flour and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Set aside.

title: jump for joy jello salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; cool.
Add pineapple, nuts, celery and milk.
Stir well.
Pour into oiled 6 cup ring mold. Chill until firm.
Invert mold onto plate.
Fresh red or green grapes can be added for garnish around the bottom and in the center of the mold.
Makes 12 servings.

title: rolled sugar cookies
directions: In large bowl combine first 4 ingredients.
Blend well.
Stir in remaining ingredients; blend well.
Chill dough.
Heat oven to 400°.
Roll dough, 1/3 at a time, on floured surface to 1/8-inch thickness.
Cut with floured cookie cutters.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate if desired.
Bake at 400° for 5 to 8 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet.

title: layered bean dip
directions: Mix taco seasoning mix and refried beans.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer other ingredients in order listed. Serve with nacho chips.

title: alsgood pie
directions: Cream
sugar
and oleo.
Beat eggs with fork.
Add eggs to creamed sugar and oleo, then add vinegar, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour
into
unbaked
pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then
turn oven to 325° and bake until done, approximately 35 minutes.

title: sure good sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add egg and oil.
Beat until well mixed.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Refrigerate dough 1 hour. Roll out for cut out cookies or roll into walnut-sized balls and press with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar.
Sprinkle sugar on top.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Roll in finger shape.
Bake at 325° until brown, then roll in confectioners sugar.

title: fried cheese bites
directions: Dip cheese cubes in egg; dredge in flour and again in egg. Roll in bread crumbs, pressing firmly so crumbs adhere.
Place on waxed paper and chill 30 minutes.
Deep fry cubes in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain and serve immediately.

title: strawberry yogurt dip
directions: Combine Cool Whip and yogurt.
Add strawberries.
Mix well. Serve as a dip with fresh fruit.
Makes 5 cups.

title: chicken pie(club member: terah smith)
directions: Measure and sift flour. Mix flour with shortening and ice water. Divide into 4 balls. Roll balls out thin and cut into dumplings, saving enough dough for top crust. Bring broth to a boil; add chicken and drop dumplings into broth.

Pour into baking dish. Place top crust on and slit in several places. Lift crust in about 3 places around edges and add 1/4 cup milk at each. Place under crust. Top with thin slices of oleo. Place in 400° oven and bake until crust is brown.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Dissolve brown sugar in cranberry juice, pineapple juice and water.
Pour into a coffeepot.
Put cloves, allspice and cinnamon in the basket of coffeepot.
Perk until good and hot.

title: hot shrimp dip
directions: Chop eggs and scallions and mix well with cream cheese and shrimp.
Heat in 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: ham and cheese on doggie rolls
directions: Toss everything together.
Spread in 12 split doggie rolls. Wrap in aluminum foil and twist ends shut.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: grilled onions
directions: Cut onions in half.
Coat both sides well with butter and put back together.
Wrap in aluminum foil.
Cook on a low-medium grill for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Place in saucepan.
Mix well and boil for one minute.
Pour mixture over 2 gallons popcorn.
Toss and mix well.
Bake at 250° for one hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: dream whip dessert
directions: Cream sugar, cream cheese and vanilla; set aside.
Mix Dream Whip according to directions minus vanilla.
Combine cream cheese ingredients and Dream Whip.
Pour into a 9 x 12 x 2-inch graham cracker crust.
Top with pie filling.
Refrigerate.
Very rich dessert.

title: cucumber tarragon dip
directions: Whirl cucumber in blender until mushy.
Add cottage cheese gradually.
Add the remaining ingredients and blend well.
Add the tarragon a pinch at a time until you get the taste you want. Chill thoroughly.
Serve with raw vegetables, crackers or chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in a casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour melted butter into mixture.
Stir.
Pour into the casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until light brown.

title: easy mexican dip
directions: Stir together.
Heat and serve with Doritos, Fritos or taco chips.

title: no bake fruit pie
directions: Mix.
Pour into pie shells and chill.
Makes 2 pies.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, oil and baby food. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown onion, sirloin and mushrooms in skillet.
When brown, add soup and sour cream; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer. Cook noodles according to package instructions.
Drain noodles and mix in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add noodles and mixture together.
Ready to serve.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: blueberry jam
directions: Bring to boil the rhubarb, sugar and water.
Add pie filling. Boil 6 to 8 minutes.
Add jello and pour into containers.
Cool and freeze.
Makes 4 pints.

title: lime pickles
directions: Slice cukes in 1/4-inch slices.
Cover with lime and water. Soak 24 hours.
Rinse well.
Cover with ice water for 3 hours. Drain and cover with other ingredients.
Let stand overnight. Boil gently about 35 minutes.
Pack in jars.
This makes a crisp pickle.
Add a little green coloring if desired.
Makes a pretty garnish around meats etc., also.

title: turkey meatballs with lemon sauce
directions: Combine egg, cereal, Worcestershire sauce and lemon peel.
Add the turkey and mix well.
Shape into 8 balls.
In a 10-inch pan, brown the meatballs on all sides in hot oil; drain off the oil. Add broth.
Transfer the meatballs to a serving dish and cover to keep warm.
Reserve the broth in the pan.

title: quiche without crust
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Mix in milk, salt, pepper, nutmeg, bacon and cheese.
Pour into buttered 2-quart baking dish (square or rectangular).
Drizzle top with melted butter.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until set.
Cut in squares. Serves 6 to 8.

title: zucchini bars
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well until thoroughly blended. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes until done.
Frost with cream cheese or dust with powdered sugar just before serving.

title: comfort cake
directions: Combine
cake
ingredients
in a large bowl and beat at medium speed
for 2 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube
or
12 cup Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Set
on rack
to
cool.
Invert
on serving plate.	Prick top immediately. Drizzle
and brush half of glaze evenly over top and
sides. After
cake has cooled, reheat remainder of glaze and
brush evenly over cake.
Sift 1 tablespoon powdered sugar over cake just before serving.

title: potato casserole
directions: Layer thawed potatoes into a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex baking dish. In medium size bowl, mix ingredients well and pour over thawed potatoes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti until tender; drain.
Mix all ingredients. Refrigerate until cold.
The longer it sets, the better it will taste.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill for several hours.
Great for picnics.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; add sugar and oil, then flour.
Let set 1 hour, then roll out and cut out rolls.
Let set 1 hour. Bake at 350° until done.

title: sunrise special
directions: In a serving bowl, layer cereal, prunes and yogurt.
Drizzle with honey; top with sunflower seeds.
Makes 1 serving.

title: grandmother aldrich's hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1/2 teaspoon sugar; let stand 10 minutes.
Add 1 1/2 cups water and 1/2 cup flour to yeast mixture.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Add butter, sugar, salt, eggs and flour.
Knead and store in refrigerator until ready to knead again and make into rolls.
I let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen small or 2 dozen large.

title: cream cheese-olive spread
directions: Combine cream cheese, mayonnaise and pepper.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in onion and olives.
Mixture may be used to stuff celery, tomatoes or as finger sandwich spread.
Yields about 1 1/4 cups.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 375° in greased 9 x 13-inch.

title: gingerbread men
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening until light and fluffy.
Add sugar, beating well after each addition.
Add egg in thirds, beating well
after
each
addition.
Blend
in the molasses and vinegar.
Stir
in the dry ingredients.
Add more flour, if needed.
Chill
dough
in
refrigerator
hours or overnight.
Roll dough out on lightly floured surface 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: ham delight sandwiches
directions: Cream margarine, poppy seed, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and onion together.
Slice the whole pans of rolls in half.
Spread the creamed mixture on both sides of sliced rolls.
Put cheese on bottom layer, then ham. Put top on and slice into individual rolls.
Wrap pan and all in aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes.
May freeze. Thaw before cooking.

title: bannock bread
directions: Mix and spread dough in a hot frypan, greased with a spoonful of shortening. Cook both sides until brown.

title: bourbon bonbons
directions: Combine butter, bourbon and milk.
Add sugar and knead until mixture is blended and does not stick to hands.
Knead in pecans. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Shape into 1-inch balls; freeze.
Dip each ball of candy into melted chocolate pieces.
Place on wax paper to cool.
Store in refrigerator.
Yield: 6 dozen.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 1 1/2 cups flour and yeast.
Heat milk, sugar and butter until melted (warm not hot).
Add milk mixture to flour and eggs.
Beat with electric mixer 30 seconds; scrape sides, then high speed 3 minutes.
Add remaining flour (soft dough).
Knead on floured board until smooth, 3 to 5 minutes.
Put in lightly greased bowl.
Cover; let rise 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Shape to form 2 balls.
Cover; rest 10 minutes.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Mix baked beans, ketchup, Karo syrup and mustard in casserole dish.
Brown hamburger and onion in skillet until onion is tender. Drain and add to bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: baklava
directions: Mix nuts with sugar and set aside.

title: chocolate nut loaf
directions: Cream butter and sugar in bowl until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Add mixture of flour and soda alternately with buttermilk, beating well after each addition.
Mix in nuts. Pour into 2 greased 4 x 8-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except Town House crackers. Place in Pyrex cooking dish and top with crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Blend butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 325° in a lightly greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake, should be light brown.

title: texas caviar
directions: Mix together.
Stir well.
Marinate several hours or overnight.
Keeps one week.
Can be used as side dish or as dip with chips.

title: red clam sauce and pasta
directions: In a large frying pan, put in oil; chop the garlic.
Saute until garlic turns golden.
Pour in marinara sauce, 2 cans red clam sauce and 2 cans chopped clams with juice.
Cook on low heat 5 minutes.
Chop parsley and put in sauce.
Cook on low heat 10 minutes.

title: sandy's strawberry shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mix the angel food cake mix and pineapple with a whisk or large spoon. Pour mixture into a 9 x 13 pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool.

title: florence's scandinavian puff(everyone who tastes this puff asks for more.)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add 1 teaspoon sugar and rye flour, making a "sponge".
Add remaining ingredients except white flour; mix well.
Add white flour until right consistency.
Mix and knead well.
Let rise 2 to 3 times.
Make into loaves and bake.

title: chicken salad
directions: Use cooked chicken and cut up into bite size pieces, not too small.
Combine chicken and celery with French dressing and allow to stand 1/2 hour.
Season with salt, pepper and seasoning salt. Toss together lightly with mayonnaise.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Put oil in loaf pans and pour mixture in.
Bake at 350° until browned.
Yields 2 small loaves.

title: ground beef potato bake
directions: Saute beef in skillet with onion.
Put in greased casserole dish.
Put potato cubes on top.
Mix soups with water and pour over meat.
Top with onion rings and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: smothered pork chops
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops.
Melt shortening and brown chops well on both sides.
Mix together soups and water.
Pour over chops.
Add sliced onion on top.
Cover and simmer over low heat for 1 1/2 hours or until chops are tender.

title: blackened chicken breast
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Heat a medium cast-iron skillet over high heat for 15 minutes, or until very hot.

In a small bowl, combine all the dry seasonings; mix well and set aside. Spray one side of the chicken with nonstick vegetable cooking spray and sprinkle with half the seasoning; reserve the remaining seasoning.
Place in the very hot skillet, seasoned side down. Repeat procedure with top side of the chicken; cook for 1 minute on each side.
Remove from the skillet and place on a small baking sheet that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable cooking spray. Bake for 5 minutes.

title: smooth creamy gravy
directions: Melt butter or any grease you are using.
Add flour to hot grease.
Mix with spoon.
Add mix and stir continuously with spatula.
Add or decrease milk to your preference.

title: ice cream torte
directions: Mix crumbs with oleo.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes; cool.
Mix pudding, milk and ice cream until well blended.
Pour over crumbs and chill.
Do not freeze. Top with whipped cream and Heath bars.

title: green bean and corn casserole
directions: Mix corn, beans, soup, pepper, onion and sour cream in a buttered casserole dish. Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.
Melt butter and add cheese, nuts and crackers. Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake 10 additional minutes.

title: suriname nasi(fried rice)
directions: Heat oil and drippings in wok or Dutch oven.
Stir-fry onion and garlic for one minute.
Add chicken, soy sauce, cinnamon, nutmeg, black pepper and bouillon cubes in this order.
Let simmer about five minutes, covered.
Stir in rice about one cup at a time, until all six cups are added.
Turn off heat.
Add celery, cabbage and scrambled eggs and mix well.
Serve with salsa, if desired.
Serves six.

title: heavenly onion casserole
directions: In large skillet melt butter.
Saute onions and mushrooms until tender.
Place in 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish or 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top.
Combine soup, milk and soy sauce.
Pour over cheese.
Top with bread, place cheese slice on top of bread.
Cover and refrigerate 4 hours or overnight.

title: overnight coleslaw
directions: In a large bowl, combine first four ingredients.
Sprinkle with sugar, set aside.

title: pecan pies
directions: Beat up and pour into crust.
Bake at 325° until filling is set.
Makes two pies.
Bake approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburg and macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni.
Cook remaining ingredients until tender.
Add to cooked macaroni.

title: perked party punch
directions: Combine juices, water and sugar in a 30-cup automatic coffee maker.
Be sure to melt sugar and use filter.
Place whole cloves, salt and cinnamon sticks in basket.
Plug in and perk.
Serve piping hot.
Store leftover punch in refrigerator.
Reheat later.

title: pickle squash
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in salt.
Let set 1 hour; drain well. Mix sugar, vinegar, celery and mustard; let boil.
Add squash; boil 3 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Seal in sterile jar.
Makes 6 pints or 3 quarts.

title: impossible pie
directions: Spray 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate with cooking spray. Sprinkle meat or vegetable, cheese and onion in plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth for 15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with a hand beater.
Pour in plate.
Bake in preheated oven at 400° until knife inserted between edge and center comes out clean, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes before serving.
Can be reheated.

title: mama's pound cake
directions: Shortening or margarine should be at room temperature.
Put all ingredients in a large bowl.
Beat on low speed until ingredients are blended.
Then beat on medium for 10 minutes. Pour into a sprayed tube or Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Test for doneness with finger.
If no depression is left, it is done.

title: butterscotch frosting
directions: Place butterscotch morsels over hot water in double boiler. Beat the cream cheese with salt until light.
Blend with melted morsels.
Beat in sugar gradually, making it a spreading consistency.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Combine apples, egg, flour, cinnamon, chopped nuts, oil, sugar, salt and vanilla in one bowl.
Mix well.
Bake 45 minutes in a 325° oven in a 7 1/2 x 11 1/2-inch pan.
Top with confectioners or whipped cream to serve.

title: sour cream-chicken squares
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Grease rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Mix baking mix and water until soft dough forms.
Beat vigorously for 20 strokes.
Gently smooth dough into ball on floured, cloth-covered board.
Knead 5 times.
Roll dough into rectangle, 14 x 10-inches.
Place dough in dish so edges are 1/2-inch up sides.

title: t-bone steaks with sauteed onions(4 servings)
directions: Peel and slice onions.
Heat 1 tablespoon of the butter and 1 tablespoon of oil in a large frying pan over medium heat.
Add the onions, 3/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon pepper and cook until onions are soft and golden, about 10 minutes.
Remove onions and cover to keep warm.
Melt remaining butter and oil in the same pan over medium heat.
Add 2 of the steaks and cook 3 to 4 minutes per side for medium-rare.
Remove the steaks from the pan and keep them warm while cooking the remaining 2 steaks with the sauteed onions.

title: dietetic ambrosia
directions: Heat part of the 7-Up to boiling point.
Stir in gelatin until well blended.
Add rest of 7-Up and then the coconut extract. Pour this over the fruits, which have been stirred together. Chill.
Store in covered container.

title: mexican sauce
directions: Cook and stir onion, bell pepper and garlic in oil in 2-quart saucepan about 5 minutes or until bell pepper is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 15 minutes, or until slightly thickened.

title: mexican fried ice cream
directions: Stir together egg and vanilla. Dip each ice cream ball in egg mixture, then roll them in remaining cereal mixture. Freeze several hours or until firm.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Reserve 1/4 cup cheese and 8 to 10 tater tots for top.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
In a large casserole dish place a layer of tots.
Cover with mixed ingredients. Repeat layers until dish is full.
Cover top with reserved cheese and tots.
Cook until bubbly and brown.

title: alfredo sauce
directions: Melt butter; add remaining ingredients (except cream), stirring constantly.
When blended, add cream and cook on low heat until cheese melts.
Make roux with equal amounts of butter and flour.
Add roux to strengthen (be cautious).
Simmer additional 10 minutes.
Pour off butter after sauce separates.
Add cream to desired texture.

title: knepfla
directions: Mix all ingredients to make a medium dough.
Let rest.
Cut dough with scissors into boiling salted water and cook 30 minutes. After you cook the Knepfla there are various ways to use them.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until lemon color.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Beat in dry mixture alternately with hot milk.
When it is well mixed, fold in whites of eggs which have been beaten, not too dry.
Put in greased and floured angel food pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pick-me-up drink
directions: Chop all vegetables and puree them in blender.
With motor running, add tomato juice, a little at a time, and continue to process until the mixture is smooth.

title: huckleberry buckle
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, egg and milk together.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix all together.
Fold in blueberries.
Spread in greased and floured pan.
Make a topping by blending together 1/2 cup sugar, 1/3 cup flour, 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 cup soft butter.
Blend until crumbly.
Spread on top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.
